title: dirt cake
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs, sugar and melted margarine.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 5 minutes.
Mix pudding as directed.
Pour 1/2 of pudding on crust.
Put 1/2 of Cool Whip on top of pudding.
Put layer of crushed cookies on top of Cool Whip. Repeat.
Refrigerate.

title: angel flake rolls
directions: Cut Crisco into flour.
Add sugar and buttermilk, mix with spoon.
Dissolve yeast in warm water; add to flour mix.
Make into rolls and let rise 30 minutes.
Bake at 450 degrees until brown. Can refrigerate to use later, but will have to let rise 45 minutes after you take them out of the refrigerator.

title: apricot bars
directions: Cream margarine and sugar..
Add egg.
Combine flour and baking powder.
Add to margarine mix.
Add coconut, nuts and vanilla.

title: quick chocolate frosting
directions: In a saucepan, combine butter, cocoa and milk. Bring to boil. Add sugar and vanilla. Beat until smooth.

title: halloween treat
directions: Put candy corn in top of fingers and fill with popcorn. Close with rubber band, twisty or ribbon to secure.

title: fried, dried apple pies
directions: Cook apples in a heavy saucepan until tender, about 45 minutes.
Add sugar and spices.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix well.
Pour into unbaked pie crust.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: hominy casserole
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Mix all ingredients and pour into baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: oven roasted potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
In large plastic bag or bowl, add all ingredients.
Close bag and shake or toss in bowl until potatoes are evenly coated.
In 13 x 9-inch baking or roasting pan, arrange potatoes; discard bag.
Bake, uncovered, stirring occasionally, 40 minutes or until potatoes are tender and golden brown.
Serves 4.

title: crawfish etouffee
directions: Saute onion and celery to a pulp.
Add soups and water.
Cook over low heat for 25 minutes.
Add crawfish and simmer about 5 to 10 minutes.
Turn off heat; let set for 15 minutes.
Serve over rice.
Parsley can be added.

title: haystacks
directions: Melt butterscotch pieces in large bowl in microwave, add noodles and peanuts.
Place haystack "clumps" on wax paper, let cool

title: seafoam candy
directions: Beat egg white to stiff froth and let sugar boil until it will form a hard ball when tried in cold water.
Pour slowly into egg, stirring egg all the time, then beat until cold and put on buttered plate.

title: california casserole
directions: In a large skillet, cook ground beef with green pepper and onion until the meat is browned and the vegetables are tender; drain.
Add the next 11 ingredients; mix thoroughly.
Add noodles, mix well.
Pour into a Dutch oven or large baking dish.
Cover; bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Return to the oven for 10 minutes, or until the cheese melts.
Yields 12 to 16 servings.

title: beer biscuits
directions: Mix ingredients together; divide into 12 greased muffin cups. Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: sour cream rosemary cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar well.
Add eggs, sour cream, flour, vanilla, soda, baking powder and salt.
Add rosemary.
Mix and beat well.

title: cheese pineapple salad
directions: Dissolve sugar in pineapple syrup over low heat.
Add gelatin softened in cold water.
Chill until partially set.
Add pineapple and cheese.
Fold in whipped cream; chill.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Cook sugar, milk and oleo until butter is melted, about 1 minute. Add peanut butter while still hot. Beat until smooth. Pour over oatmeal to which cocoa and vanilla have been added. Add coconut and nuts last. Make out while still warm in balls or pour into pan and chill in refrigerator.

title: a man's favorite(try it on your husband)
directions: Blend shortening, sugar and egg.
Add raisins and applesauce. Sift spices and salt with flour.
Add in several portions to mixture before last of flour is added.
Dissolve soda in hot water and add to mixture.
Beat well.
Pour in a greased loaf.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Ice if desired.

title: golden pecan pie
directions: Combine dry ingredients in large mixing bowl.
Add eggs, syrup, vanilla and margarine.
Beat with electric mixer until blended.
Stir in pecans.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.

title: hoppin' john
directions: Soak the peas overnight in a large pot of water (or boil them for 2 minutes; cover and let stand 1 hour).
Drain, then cover with 4 cups fresh water and bring to a boil. Add the onion, garlic, bay leaf, black pepper and cayenne.
Bring to a boil; cover and simmer 1 hour, stirring occasionally.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Wash and slice tomatoes thick. Salt and pepper each side. Coat with flour and let sit. Cover bottom of frypan (cast-iron skillet works best) with oil and heat on medium-high. When oil is hot, coat tomato slices again in flour and place in pan. Do not overlap slices.
Fry until golden brown. Turn and fry the other side. Drain on paper towels. Add more oil to pan, if necessary, and continue to fry all slices as directed.
Serve while hot and crisp.

title: sausage souffle(good breakfast dish)
directions: Beat eggs.
Add milk and dry ingredients.
Pour over bread and sausage that have been placed in a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Add the cheese to the top of the mixture.
Mix gently with a fork down through the mixture.
Put in refrigerator overnight.
Bake 45 minutes at 325°.

title: bragiole
directions: Clean and chop parsley (use only leaves not stems); clean and chop fine 5 to 6 cloves from fresh garlic.
Lay out beef sandwich steaks flat.
Spread one clove chopped garlic per sandwich steak. Add one tablespoon flat parsley.
Sprinkle one rounded tablespoonful fresh Romano cheese; sprinkle 1/4 teaspoon crushed red pepper over meat.
Roll up Bragioles tightly and stick 5 toothpicks on meat ends to keep it together.
Warm up 3/4 cup olive oil in skillet (cover skillet).
Then add Bragioles.
Cook on medium heat to brown on both sides, 6 to 8 minutes total.
Add Bragioles to your favorite Italian red sauce and heat on low for 1 hour.
Serve with pasta.

title: cabbage soup
directions: Bring enough water to boil to cover the cabbage when it is added.
Add cabbage and let cook one minute.
Drain.
Cook bacon in a casserole or small kettle until rendered of fat.
Add the onion and cook, stirring, until the onion is wilted.
Sprinkle with flour and stir.
Add the broth, stirring rapidly with a wire whisk.
When the mixture simmers, add the cabbage, carrots, potatoes, salt and pepper.
Add vinegar and sugar.
Cook, stirring often from bottom, about 30 minutes.
Stir in cream and simmer 5 minutes.
Serve.
Sprinkle each serving with fresh dill (optional, 1/4 cup).

title: ranch style potatoes
directions: Put fries in bottom of baking dish.
Dot pats of margarine on top.
Sprinkle dry Ranch dressing on top.
Mix over all.
Cover with foil.
Bake in a preheated oven at 325° for 1 hour.

title: south carolina chicken bog
directions: Boil cut-up hen and onion until the meat falls off bone on chicken.
Wash rice and add to chicken, making sure to have about 6 cups water in pot.
Add salt and pepper.
Bring to a good boil, stir a couple of times while boiling.
Cut heat to very low. Place lid on pot and cook for 40 minutes or until the rice is soft.
Serves about 10 to 12.

directions: Bake at 350°

Cool, cut into bars and serve.

I use a glass one for this recipe.

title: cole slaw
directions: Mix cabbage, pepper, onion, and salt. Pour hot watter over cabbage and let stand 1 hour. Add remaining ingredients and chill over night. Will keep for days.

title: mashed potatoes with roasted garlic
directions: Place potatoes in large saucepan and cover with water.
Boil until tender.
Drain well.
Mash potatoes with remaining ingredients.
Season with salt and pepper.
Add more milk if needed to moisten.
Yields 4 servings.

title: frosted salad
directions: Mix lemon jello and boiling water.
Stir in 2 cups 7-Up and chill until slightly thickened.
Fold in pineapple, marshmallows and bananas.
Pour in 9 x 12-inch pan and chill until firm.

title: nacho dip
directions: Brown hamburger and drain.
Add 1/2 jar or picante sauce.
Add soups and cheese.
Heat until cheese melts.

title: old fashion stack cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar together.
Add eggs and molasses. Mix well: add soda to buttermilk.
Mix dry ingredients together. Add alternately with milk to batter, beginning and ending with dry ingredients.
Bake in thin layers (about 1/2 in.
thick) in either 9 in. cake pan or old- fashion black griddle for about 12 minutes at 350 degrees.
I use biscuit pan 9 x 13 x 1/2.
Cut to size.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Stir together margarine, sugar and milk in heavy saucepan. Bring to full boil, stirring constantly.
Boil 5 minutes over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat; gradually stir in peanut butter chips.
Pour into greased 9 x 9-inch or 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cool at room temperature.
Cut into squares.
Makes about 3 pounds.

title: cheese filled meat loaf
directions: Combine beef, 1 can tomato sauce, egg, bread crumbs, onion and seasonings.
Divide mixture in half.
Lightly pack 1/2 mixture in a foil lined pan.
Arrange 4 slices of cheese on top, then pack the remaining meat mixture over cheese layer.
Cut remaining cheese slices into strips and arrange on top of loaf.
(This may be done the last 30 minutes of baking.)

title: taco filling
directions: Mix all ingredients and saute in margarine.
Yield: filling for 12 tacos.
Carbohydrate 2 g, protein 7 g, fat 4 g, calories ???.
One serving = 1 meat lean exchange.

title: crab dip
directions: Place all ingredients in crock-pot.
Mix occasionally until cheese is melted.
Sprinkle paprika on top for color.
Serve warm with crackers.

title: vegetable salad dressing
directions: Blend mayonnaise and sour cream. Add chopped vegetables. This is an appetizing dressing for all fresh vegetable salads.

title: frosted apple cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix egg in enough water to equal 1/2 cup liquid.
Mix together dry ingredients, butter and 1/2 cup liquid. Roll this out in 2 pieces, one for the bottom crust and the other for the top.
Place the bottom crust into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour in the sliced apples and sprinkle with white sugar and cinnamon. (You may choose to use less sugar as it is very sweet.)
Place the top crust on the top of apples.
Prick the top crust several times for venting and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: salad dressing
directions: Boil all ingredients and stir until thickened.
Beat very well.
Makes 1 pint.

title: 8-minute cheesecake(makes 1 pie)
directions: Beat cheese until smooth; gradually beat in sugar.
Blend sour cream and vanilla.
Fold in whipped topping, blending well.
Spoon into crust.
Chill until set, at least 4 hours.
Garnish with strawberries if desired!
Good!

title: seven-up pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Have ingredients at room temperature. Cream
oleo,
shortening and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time.
Beat well.
Add flour alternately with 7-Up and flavorings.
Bake in a tube pan for 1 hour.

title: finger paint
directions: Mix cornstarch, sugar and water in saucepan.
Cook and stir over medium heat about 5 minutes, or until thickened; remove from heat.
Divide the mixture into separate cups or containers.
Tint mixture in each container with a different food color.
Stir several times until cool.
Store in an airtight container.
(The paint works best if you use it the same day you make it.)

title: hershey's original cocoa fudge
directions: Combine
cocoa,
sugar and salt in large saucepan.
Add milk gradually.	Mix

soft
ball when dropped into cold water.
Be sure bulb of thermometer is not resting on bottom of saucepan.

title: spinach dip
directions: Drain spinach.
Pat dry.
Put all ingredients in a bowl.
Mix well and chill overnight.
Serve with King's Hawaiian bread.

title: grace's cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a shallow 2-quart baking dish. In a small bowl, stir and set aside brown sugar and 2 tablespoons cocoa.
In a large bowl, stir flour, sugar, 3 tablespoons cocoa, baking powder and salt.
Add and stir until moistened the milk, oil and vanilla.
Stir in chocolate chips and nuts.
Spread in baking dish.
Sprinkle brown sugar-cocoa mixture over batter. Slowly pour hot water over batter.
Do not stir.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes until top of cake is set.
Let stand 30 minutes and top with whipped topping.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Mix soup and water together.
Wash rice.
Spread into ungreased 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Place chicken, spaced, on top of rice.
Add the soup and water mixture.
Salt to taste. Cover dish tightly with foil.
Bake 30 minutes in a 425° oven, then remove foil and bake 30 minutes more.
Will be light brown and very tender.

title: marble angel cake
directions: Mix cake mix (minus 4 teaspoons), pudding, oleo, eggs, sour cream and salad oil.
Mix 5 minutes until well blended.
Melt sweet chocolate, sugar and the 4 teaspoons mix. Drip and swirl through batter in two layers in angel food pan or long pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
No icing required.

title: orange juice cake
directions: Mix with beater, adding eggs, one at a time, while beating. Bake in oven at 350° for 45 minutes.
As soon as cake is removed, punch small holes about 2-inches apart with toothpick.
Pour 1 cup orange juice mixed with 1 cup sugar over cake.
Let stand until mixture hardens.
Cake will have a pleasant glaze.
Do not heat orange juice and completed cake must not be placed back in oven.

title: olive chip dip
directions: Take cream cheese and put in bowl.
Soften by mixing half of olive juice and a little warm water.
Mix until smooth and creamy. Mix everything together.
Serve with choice of crackers or chips.

title: zucchini bread
directions: In large bowl, stir together flour, sugar, cinnamon, salt, baking powder, soda, zucchini, nuts and raisins.
In another bowl, beat eggs and oil; pour over flour mixture and stir until moistened.
Turn into greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.

title: brown sugar fudge
directions: Dissolve sugar and cream.
Cook until soft ball stage when tested in water (cold).
Take from fire.
Add butter, nuts and flavoring.
Let cool.
Beat until creamy.
Press in buttered pan. Cut into squares.

title: caramel layer chocolate squares
directions: Melt caramels and blend with 1/3 cup milk.
Beat together cake mix, margarine and 1/3 cup milk.
Press half of cake mixture into greased 9 x 13-inch pan and bake for 6 minutes at 350°.
Spread chocolate chips over baked crust.
Spread caramel mixture over chips, then rest of cake mixture.
Bake 15 to 18 minutes at 350°. Cool and refrigerate to set caramels, then cut into squares. Serves 8.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Cut thin slice from stem end of each bell pepper.
Remove seeds and membranes; rinse peppers.
Cook peppers in boiling water to cover, about 5 minutes; drain.

title: cajun rice
directions: Brown meat, onions and peppers in skillet until meat is brown and onions are soft. Mix with rice and seasonings and serve.

title: suzan's french bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add butter, salt, sugar and flour.
Mix, then let set for 10 minutes. Roll out into rectangle.
Then roll into a loaf.
Spray Pam in pan (flat cookie sheet).
Let rise for 1 1/2 hours.
(Will be easier if in 2 rolls.)
Bake about 30 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: white chocolate peanut clusters
directions: Melt chocolate and peanut butter together in double boiler. Pour mixture over marshmallows, peanuts and rice cereal.
Drop by teaspoons onto wax paper.
When firm, store airtight in cool place.

title: hors d'oeuvres
directions: Mix all the ingredients until thick.
Spread over bite size cubes of Italian bread.
Broil a few minutes until brown and melted.
Serve immediately.

title: green jello salad
directions: Let chill in refrigerator until mixture starts to jell. Remove and add drained, crushed pineapple, 1 small container of Cool Whip, 2 to 3 tablespoons of mayonnaise, 1 small bottle of maraschino cherries and 1/2 cup chopped pecans.
Mix thoroughly. Add marshmallows, if you wish.
Put back in refrigerator and jell until ready to serve.

title: parmesan chicken
directions: Mix together crushed stuffing mix, parmesan cheese, salt and pepper. Dip chicken breasts in melted butter and roll in stuffing mixture.
Place in casserole and bake at 350 degrees for 30-35 minutes uncovered.

title: peanut butter bars
directions: Mix Karo and sugar; bring to a boil.
Remove from heat.
Mix peanut butter and vanilla into sugar mixture.
Pour into Rice Krispies and mix well.
Put into buttered dish.
Melt white chocolate in microwave and pour on top.

title: tea cakes
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add one egg at a time.
Add buttermilk, flour, soda and salt.
Work dough until stiff.
Roll dough out until about 1/4-inch thick.
Cut with cookie cutter. Bake in 450° oven until brown.

title: almond cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream together sugar and shortening until fluffy.
Add egg and extract; beat for 1 minute.
Sift together flour, baking soda and salt.
Gradually add to the creamed mixture, constantly mixing.
Roll dough into 1-inch balls. Place on greased baking sheet 1-inch apart.
Press center of each ball down gently, filling center with 1 almond.
Bake for 20 minutes.
Cool on a wire rack.

title: easy swiss steak
directions: Mix flour, salt and pepper.
Cut meat into small pieces.
In a large skillet, brown meat in hot Crisco.
Remove excess grease from pan.
Top with onion, tomatoes and bell pepper.
Cover and cook over low heat for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
I use the stainless steel electric frypan.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Mix and pat first 3 ingredients into pizza pan.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes at 350°.
Cool.
Mix next 3 ingredients and spread on crust.
Layer fruit on top.
Next, use strawberries, kiwi, bananas, apples, etc.
Combine last 4 ingredients and pour on top of fruit.
Refrigerate and enjoy!

title: d j's casserole
directions: Brown hamburger meat and season with chili powder, salt, pepper and chopped onion.
Then layer ingredients in this way: tortillas, 1/2 meat mixture, 6 slices cheese, all the beans, tortillas, 1/2 meat mixture and 6 slices of cheese.
Mix chicken soup and Ro-Tel tomatoes; then pour on top.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: trash
directions: You also need 1 large brown grocery bag.

title: cookie sheet cake
directions: Put in saucepan and heat to a boil: 2 sticks margarine, 1 cup water and 3 tablespoons cocoa.
Mix 2 cups flour, 2 cups sugar and 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Add to boiling ingredients and mix.
Beat 2 eggs and add 1 teaspoon soda, 1/2 cup buttermilk and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Add to cocoa mixture and bake 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.

title: crunchy pea salad
directions: Combine Miracle Whip and salad dressing; mix well.
Add remaining ingredients; mix lightly.
Chill.
Add additional salad dressing just before serving, if desired.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix nuts in flour.
Mix all ingredients and cook in greased tube pan for 1 hour at 350°.

title: party franks
directions: Cut wieners in half. Wrap bacon around wieners.
Use a toothpick to hold bacon.
Put in pot and cover with brown sugar. Cook on low heat until all sugar is gone (crock-pot).

title: party mix
directions: Mix together.
Bake at 250° for 45 minutes. Stir every 15 minutes.

title: frosted pecans
directions: Toast pecans in a moderate oven about 350° for 8 minutes. Mix all other ingredients in a saucepan. Cover. Bring to a boil. Boil until you reach soft-ball stage. Remove from heat. Add nuts. Stir to coat the nuts. Turn out onto waxed paper and separate nuts. Allow to cool. Put in airtight containers.

title: italian creme cake
directions: Cream sugar and oleo until smooth.
Add egg yolks and oil. Combine flour, soda and salt, then add buttermilk, vanilla, nuts and coconut with flour mixture.
Fold in egg whites.
Pour in greased floured pans.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: strawberry jello salad
directions: Combine Jell-O with 1 cup of boiling water.
Stir to dissolve. Add strawberries, pineapple and pecans and stir well.
Put half of this mixture in a 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish.
Chill until set. When chilled, spread with sour cream.
Cover with remaining mixture.
Cover well with a plastic wrap.
Chill until set.
Cut into small squares and serve.

title: camp style eggs and corn
directions: Brown sausage in skillet; pour off fat.
Add corn.
Add beaten eggs to corn-sausage mixture and cook as scrambled eggs.
Makes 6 servings.
One-fourth cup of minced onions or scallions and 3 tablespoons finely chopped green peppers may be added to browning sausage for added flavor, if desired.

title: mexican tailgate hors d'oeuvres
directions: Combine soft cream cheese, sour cream and taco seasoning mix. Spread on dish and refrigerate overnight.
Spread over it 2 cans frozen avocado, shredded lettuce, chopped tomatoes and chopped onions.
Drizzle taco sauce on it and top with grated Cheddar cheese.

title: celebration punch
directions: Combine in saucepan and boil the water and sugar. Let cool. Stir until sugar is dissolved. Add the jello. Stir until dissolved. Add the pineapple juice and orange juice. Allow to cool. Place mixture in Ziploc Baggies. Chill in freezer until slush forms. When ready to use, place mixture in punch bowl. Then add ginger ale over mixture.

title: rice with vienna sausages
directions: Pour oil in Dutch oven.
Put in garlic and onions.
Saute until clear.
Cut up sausages (slice), put in pot and brown.
Add the following, after browned:
tomato sauce and Sofinto; season to taste.
Stir in rice and add water just until the rice is covered. Add salt.

title: rhubarb pie
directions: Mix eggs and milk; add sugar, flour, nutmeg and rhubarb.
Pour into shell; dot with butter.
Bake at 400° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: broccoli chicken bake
directions: Spread broccoli in well-greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Place chicken on broccoli; cover with 1/8-inch slices of cheese.
Mix soup and mayonnaise and spread evenly over cheese.
Sprinkle with water chestnuts.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven; cover with onion rings.
Bake ten more minutes or until onions are crisp.

title: green apple cake
directions: Slice apples and boil in the 2 cups of molasses.
Cook this away to 1/2 the quantity.
Cream the butter and sugar together and add eggs and milk.
Sift flour with spices and soda.
Add to this the raisins.
Add apples last.
Mix thoroughly.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes (time approximate, check often).
Use 2 loaf pans. This cake will keep for 1 month.

title: orange cake
directions: Mix the first
4 ingredients. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes in 3 round cake pans. Let cool and spread frosting.

title: rhubarb jam
directions: Put sugar over rhubarb; let stand overnight.
Cook until it boils well.
Add jello.
Pour in hot jars and seal.

title: sicilian meat roll
directions: Combine all ingredients except ham and cheese.
On foil or waxed paper, pat meat mixture to a 12 x 10-inch rectangle.
Top with ham slices and shredded cheese.
Start at short end and roll up meat.
Seal edges and ends.
Place seam side down in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 75 minutes.
Place cheese wedges over top and return to oven for 5 minutes or until cheese wedges melt.

title: chicken and pork adobo
directions: Cut pork into 1-inch cubes.
Heat oil in large skillet; add chicken and pork, a small amount at a time, browning on all sides. Repeat until all chicken and pork are browned.
Add garlic, soy sauce, coarse ground pepper, peppercorns, bay leaves, vinegar and broth.
Cover and cook over low heat 1 hour, stirring frequently, adding more broth if it becomes dry.
Add salt to taste.
If using coconut milk, add now and simmer 10 minutes longer.
Serve with boiled or fried rice.
Makes 12 servings.

title: savory broccoli casserole
directions: Cut broccoli, if fresh, into
1-inch
pieces.
Cook
in small amount of salt water and drain.
If frozen, cook.

title: sweet and sour stew
directions: Coat stew meat with flour.
Brown diced onion and meat in oil. Add all ingredients except carrots and mushrooms.
Simmer and cover for 45 minutes.
Add carrots and mushrooms.
Cover and simmer 45 minutes more.
Serve hot with rolls.

title: mother's red velvet pound cake(good!)
directions: Cream together Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time. Add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: easy crumb cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Add butter.
Mix and rub together to form crumbs.
Remove 3/4 cup of crumbs for topping. Add eggs, milk and vanilla to rest of crumbs.
Beat until smooth. Add crumbs.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: chili beans
directions: Cook pinto beans, then add remaining ingredients and mix. Brown ground beef before adding.
Cook slow at low temperature.

title: sugar-free egg custard
directions: Spray a 9-inch pie plate with Pam.
Mix eggs, flour and sweetener together; mix well.
Melt margarine; add to mixture. Add vanilla and milk.
Pour into pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle top with nutmeg, if desired.

title: chocolate delights(4 servings)
directions: In a double boiler, melt the chocolate and honey.
Peel the bananas and cut them into 4 sections each.

title: clam chowder
directions: Cook pork until crisp; add onions and cook 5 minutes.
Mix in potatoes, seasoning and water; cover pan and simmer 15 minutes. Add clams and liquid; then add milk, butter and cream.
Heat and serve.

title: best yet pound cake
directions: Take all ingredients out of refrigerator at least 2 hours before mixing.
Cream butter and cream cheese.
Add sugar and cream well.
Add eggs and flour alternately, mixing well after each one. Add flavoring and mix well.
Place in a cold oven.
Set temperature to 325° and bake for 1 hour and 25 minutes.

title: christmas pecans
directions: Beat egg white until stiff.
Stir in brown sugar and vanilla. Add pecans, coating well.
Using two forks, place pecans on cookie sheet, making sure they do not touch.
Bake in a 250° oven for 30 minutes.
Cool and store covered in a tin in the refrigerator.

title: chinese style vegetable medley
directions: Prepare 3 cups finely shredded cabbage.
Heat shortening in a medium skillet.
Add vegetables and stir.
Cover; steam 5 minutes or until crisp-tender, stirring several times.
Add salt and pepper.
If desired, stir in 1 tablespoon soy sauce.
Serves 4.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Fry bacon in drippings,
Saute onions, bell pepper and celery. Add chopped bacon and tomatoes with salt, pepper, garlic salt, Worcestershire sauce and bay leaves.
Cook about 45 minutes. Add raw shrimp.
Cook 10 minutes more.
Serve on rice.

title: sensational chicken
directions: Rub
chicken
with ginger.
Dip pieces in soy sauce; coat with basic barbecue sauce.
Let stand 1 hour or more.
Bake for 30 minutes at 400°.
Baste with more sauce; turn and baste again.
Bake 30 to 45 minutes more or until fork-tender, basting often with sauce and pan juices.

title: mommy's kugel *
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Butter two 8-inch square pans.
Boil and drain noodles.
Beat together remaining ingredients.
(Note that the batter will be loose.)
Fold noodles into batter and put into the pans.
Dot with butter and sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake in oven for one hour (but check after 45 minutes because ovens vary). Serve hot or cold.
Either way, it's delicious!

title: green bean hot dish
directions: Brown hamburger.
Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Beat eggs, milk, mustard and salt.
Add bread, sausage and cheese.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 35 minutes.

title: chocolate cheese pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In a large mixing bowl, combine cream cheese and sugar; beat well.
Blend in cocoa, scraping sides of bowl and beaters frequently.
Add eggs and vanilla; blend well. Blend in whipping cream.
Pour into crust.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes. (Center will be soft but will set upon cooling.)
Cool to room temperature.
Cover and chill several hours or overnight.
Garnish with pie filling.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: 7th day breakfast
directions: Put cereal in a cereal bowl, then add banana on top of that. Spread yoghurt on top of banana, then put Cool Whip on top of that, then eat!

title: coon a la delta
directions: After coon has been dressed properly, soak for 1 hour in mild vinegar solution.
Drain.
Cut up or cook whole, as desired.
Salt and pepper and cover with water.
Add cayenne pepper, chopped garlic, onion, celery and bell pepper and parboil until partially tender.
Remove from heat and drain.

title: new orleans style red beans and rice
directions: Wash red beans. Discard any bad beans. Cover beans with cold water (use medium Dutch oven or pot); put on simmer and let them get hot gradually. This will keep them from foaming. When hot, bring to a boil and add bay leaves. Add a ham bone, slab bacon or ham hocks to beans. Mince onion and garlic. Saute in bacon drippings along with the parsley flakes. Add sauteed ingredients to beans. Cook, covered, over low heat for 2 hours or until beans are tender. Add ham chunks, wieners or cooked smoked sausages to beans. Serve with rice and French bread. Best cooked a day ahead of time. Serve with hot Tabasco sauce, if desired.

title: sour cream apple pie
directions: Beat cream, sugar, 2 tablespoons flour, salt, vanilla and egg.
Add apples; pour into crust.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.

title: baked beans
directions: Chop bacon and onion and saute, drain some of the grease. Mix together all ingredients and bake in 350 degree oven for 1 hour.

title: peanut butter fingers
directions: Sift together flour, soda, baking powder and salt.
Combine shortening and peanut butter and cream together with a spoon. Beat in sugar, egg and raisins until fluffy.
Slowly blend in flour mixture.
Pinch off small pieces of dough and roll between palms into strips 2 inches long.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet. Press lengthwise with tines of fork.
Bake for 12 to 15 minutes at 350°.

title: cherry salad
directions: Mix in the order given and refrigerate.

title: fried burritos
directions: Brown hamburger and onion with taco seasoning until done. Put refried beans on flour tortilla.
Top with hamburger mixture and cheese.
Fold ends up and then roll.
Fry in hot oil for about 1 minute on each side or until brown.
Pat with paper towel. Top with more cheese, sour cream and salsa.

title: chicken monterey
directions: Cut chicken breasts in half.
Thaw frozen artichoke hearts and green beans.
Rub chicken breasts with 3/4 teaspoon salt.
In 12-inch skillet over medium-high heat, in hot salad oil, cook chicken until browned on all sides.
Arrange chicken in 3-quart casserole.
Spoon off all but 2 tablespoons drippings from skillet. In remaining hot drippings in skillet, over medium heat, cook green onion until tender, stirring occasionally.
Stir in flour until blended; gradually stir in milk and water until smooth; stir in ketchup, rosemary, bouillon and 3/4 teaspoon salt; cook, stirring constantly, until sauce thickens slightly.
Preheat oven to 350°. Pour sauce over chicken in casserole.
Cover casserole; bake 30 minutes.
Stir in artichoke hearts and green beans; bake 20 minutes longer or until chicken is fork-tender.
Skim fat from sauce in casserole.
Serves 6; 360 calories per serving.

title: paprika chicken
directions: Heat shortening in large skillet, saute onion until light yellow.
Stir in paprika over reduced heat.
Add meat and salt, browning meat while stirring.
When meat is well browned, add a small amount of water or stock.
Simmer, do not boil!
When meat is almost tender, add chopped green pepper and tomato.
Mix flour and sour cream together and thicken the gravy of the paprikas.
Serve with small dumpling or rice or boiled potatoes.

title: spaghetti florentine
directions: Cook noodles as directed.
Toss with spaghetti sauce.
Thaw and drain spinach.
Mix cottage cheese and Parmesan.
In a 9 x 9-inch pan layer ingredients as follows:
half the spaghetti noodles and sauce, then all spinach, all cottage cheese mixture, half the Mozzarella.
Repeat noodles and slice Mozzarella into thin strips, laying them in a lattice design.
Sprinkle with 2 tablespoons Parmesan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: potato casserole
directions: Peel and cube cooked potatoes.
Place in large casserole dish. Sprinkle cubes of cheese over potatoes, then onions, pimento, parsley, paprika and garlic salt.
Arrange cubes of bread over top.
Pour melted butter on top.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve immediately.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Sift flour with soda; set aside.
Cream margarine and slowly add sugar, beating well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Stir in sour cream.
Add flour mixture, 1/2 cup at a time, beating constantly.
Add extracts.
Pour batter into greased 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: red cinnamon rings
directions: Peel and core cucumbers, slice into 1/2 inch rings. Soak in lime water for 24 hours, drain, rinse with clean water until clear. Pour cold water over rings and cover with ice, soak for 3 hours, drain.

title: ham loaf
directions: Mix together and pack in loaf pan.
Bake at 375° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: peppered steak
directions: Rinse beef and with the flour, flour the beef thoroughly. Place in a
roast
pan
and
cover with the 1/2 gallon of water. Add the chopped onion, salt and pepper.
In a preheated oven cook for 2
hours at 325° or until the meat is tender. Add the soy sauce and the green peppers; cook another 15 to 20 minutes.
This recipe makes its own gravy.
Serve over rice or white mashed potatoes.
Serves 6 to 9 people.

title: old fashion ginger cake cookies
directions: Combine and blend sugar and butter.
Beat in egg, molasses and sour milk.
Sift together cinnamon, ginger, soda, salt, cloves and flour.
Add to liquid mix and blend.

title: quick chocolate buttermilk cake
directions: Sift first 3 ingredients together.
In a saucepan, bring butter/margarine, water, shortening, buttermilk and cocoa to a boil.
Remove from heat.
When mixture is cool, pour over sifted dry ingredients and mix well.
Add beaten eggs and soda.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes for layer cakes; 28 to 32 minutes for 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: southwestern cheeseburgers
directions: Mix ground beef, onion and chilies.
Shape into 8 thin patties.
Mound 1/4 mushrooms on center of 4 patties.
Top with 2 slices of cheese.
Place remaining patties on top; pinch edges to seal securely.
Cover and grill patties.
Serve with taco sauce or salsa.

title: frozen coconut caramel pie
directions: Melt butter; add coconut and pecans.
Cook until golden brown. Set aside until completely cool.
Beat cream cheese and condensed milk until creamy.
Fold in whipped topping.
Set aside one cup coconut mixture and combine remaining mixture with cream cheese/whipped topping.
Spread 1/4 of cream cheese mixture in each pie shell and drizzle caramel.
Repeat.
Top with remaining coconut mixture.
Keep frozen and set at room temperature 5 to 10 minutes before serving.
Vanilla or chocolate crumb crust may be used instead of graham cracker.

title: southern peanut brittle
directions: Cook peanuts, sugar, syrup and salt in a heavy iron skillet, stirring constantly until dark golden brown (hard crack stage). Remove from heat.
Working quickly, add butter, vanilla and baking soda.
The soda should be added last as it will foam up.
Stir completely.
Pour onto a greased cookie sheet.
Do not try to spread it out; let it move by itself.
It will be thick and airy. Cool completely before breaking into pieces.
The easiest way to break it is to hit the bottom of the cookie sheet on a firm surface.

title: southern skillet chicken
directions: In skillet, cook green pepper and onion with garlic in butter until tender.
Add remaining ingredients, except chicken and rice. Cook, stirring, until thickened.
Add chicken; heat.
Serve over rice.
Makes 6 cups.

title: quick batter rolls
directions: Scald milk. Add water, sugar, oil and salt. Mix. Add 2 cups flour and sprinkle on yeast.
Pour in remaining flour and mix well. Spoon in greased muffin pans. Bake about 15 minutes at 400°.

title: cheese strata
directions: Cut 12 donut shapes from bread slices.
Set aside.
Place all bread scraps into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Place cheese in layers over bread.
Add 1 layer broccoli and 1 layer ham.
Arrange donut shapes on top.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over top.
Cover and refrigerate 6 hours or overnight.
Bake uncovered at 325° for 55 minutes.
Sprinkle shredded cheese over top during last 5 minutes of baking.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Cut into 12 squares.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Mix together dry ingredients.
Then add vanilla, vinegar, salad oil and water.
Beat well with spoon and pour into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: shepherd's pie(student favorite)
directions: Brown ground beef; drain fat.
Add seasonings (you may vary seasoning amounts according to personal taste).
Add tomato soup and beans with liquid.
Simmer for 15 minutes.
This is delicious topped with mashed potatoes or served with rice.
It is a quick hot meal for those nights when time is short.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Dissolve strawberry Jell-O in boiling water.
Add frozen strawberries, partly thawed.
Stir in 1 1/2 cups applesauce and 1/2 cup water used to rinse out can.
Put in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put Cool Whip on top.

title: pistachio date nut bread
directions: Soak dates in hot water.
Cool.
Combine flour, pistachios, sugar, baking soda and salt.
Combine date mixture, eggs, butter, vanilla and orange peel.
Add to flour mixture.
Mix only until moistened.
Spoon into 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch greased loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until pick comes out clean. Yields 1 loaf.

title: stuffed squash
directions: Put squash in water to cover and boil until nearly tender. Split in half. Scoop out center.
Mix all the ingredients except butter.
You may have to use more bread crumbs. Put mixture in squash shells.
Put buttered crumbs on top. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: kentucky pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease and flour tube pan.
Combine all ingredients in order listed except nuts and egg whites; beat well. Add nuts.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Pour into prepared pan.
Bake 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: pink elephant
directions: Half-fill glass with pink lemonade.
Add strawberry ice cream. If glass not yet full, add more pink lemonade.
Enjoy.
Great way to cool off on hot summer day.

title: fluffy peanut butter pie
directions: Whip cream cheese until soft and fluffy.
Beat in sugar and peanut butter.
Slowly add milk, blending thoroughly into mixture. Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into crust.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Freeze until firm.

title: country breakfast pie
directions: Cook sausage until done.
Drain off fat and crumble.
Mix cheese and sausage together.
Sprinkle in pie shell.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Pour over sausage and cheese mixture. Bake at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Cool on rack 10 minutes. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: marinated vegetable salad
directions: Slice carrots and cook just until tender.
Combine all vegetables and toss in large mixing bowl.
In small bowl, mix remaining ingredients until well blended.
Pour over vegetables and toss to coat.
Cover and chill in refrigerator overnight.
Yields 10 to 12 servings.

title: wonderful pie
directions: Drain peaches and pineapple.
Mix together with lemon juice, condensed milk and Cool Whip.
Add pecans.
Chill.
Makes 2 pies.

title: curry glazed chicken
directions: Pound chicken breasts to 1/4-inch thick or just bake longer. Melt margarine in a baking dish at 375°.
Stir in mustard, honey and curry powder.
Add chicken and bake 10 minutes.
Turn chicken and bake another 10 to 15 minutes.
Good served with rice.

title: hamburg barbecue
directions: Fry ground chuck and onion together until cooked and pink disappears in meat. Drain if need be. Mix remaining ingredients together. Then place in pan with cooked meat and onions. Cook until the right consistency for barbecue.

title: yellow squash casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Melt 3 tablespoons of the butter in a 12-inch skillet over moderate heat.
Add the onion and cook, covered, for 5 minutes or until soft.
Meanwhile, cut the squash into 1/4-inch slices.
If they are large, quarter them.
Add the squash to the onion.
Cover and cook for 3 minutes or until crisp-tender.

title: coffee tarts
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Dip canned biscuits in melted butter. Put onto cookie sheet.
Sprinkle brown sugar on both sides of butter dipped biscuits.
Bake until golden brown, about 10 to 20 minutes.

title: carrot and garlic dip
directions: Cook the carrots in boiling salted water until just tender; drain thoroughly.
Refresh with cold water and drain again.
Put into a blender or food processor with the garlic, yogurt and coriander and puree until smooth.
Season generously with cayenne pepper and a little salt.
Turn into a serving dish and allow to stand about 1 hour to let the flavors develop.
Serve with the vegetables.

title: beans 'n wiener biscuit casserole
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
In a medium saucepan, combine wieners, pork and beans, catsup, onion and brown sugar.
Bring to a boil; simmer 5 minutes.
Spoon hot bean mixture into ungreased 8 or 9-inch square pan.
Separate biscuit dough into 10 biscuits; arrange over bean mixture.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes, or until biscuits are golden brown and no longer doughy.
Refrigerate any leftovers.
Makes 6 servings.

title: broccoli cauliflower casserole
directions: Saute sausage and onion in skillet. Add remaining ingredients and mix well. Pour into casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes or until bubbly and lightly brown on top.

title: master mix muffins
directions: Add sugar to mix.
Combine milk and beaten egg and add to mix until flour is just moistened.
Bake in greased muffin pans in 450° oven for 20 minutes.
Yields 6 muffins.

title: fudge pie
directions: Melt oleo and chocolate.
Add Karo and salt.
Remove from stove and add sugar to hot mixture.
Add beaten eggs and vanilla. Cook in unbaked crust at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.
Cover rim of pastry with foil to keep pastry from becoming too brown.
Serve with ice cream.

title: spinach quiche
directions: Mix eggs, flour and half and half.
Place Swiss cheese on bottom of unbaked pie shell.
Layer with spinach, ham and mushrooms.
Pour mixture into pie shell and top with shredded cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: breaded steaks parmesan
directions: Beat eggs; season to taste.
Dip steaks in egg batter, then in bread crumbs and fry in oil until brown, then place in pan and add tomato sauce, cheese, sliced eggs and peas.
Cover with foil; bake until done.

title: sauteed shad roe
directions: About 10 minutes before serving, in covered 10-inch skillet, over medium heat in hot butter, cook roe, turning once, for 8 minutes or until roe loses its pink color and is tender. Sprinkle roe with salt and pepper.
Serve with lemon wedges to squeeze over roe.

title: custard(serves 1)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients in blender on medium speed.
Pour into baking dish and bake for 12 minutes.

title: cinnamon pickles
directions: Mix vinegar, alum and food coloring.
Simmer 2 hours, then drain and discard water.

title: slaw
directions: Shred and chop all vegetables fine.
Put 1/2 cup sugar on it and let stand while you boil remaining ingredients.
Bring to boil and pour over slaw; let stand 2 hours before stirring. Refrigerate and will keep for several weeks.

title: five cup salad
directions: Combine ingredients; mix lightly.
Chill.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: sweet pickles
directions: Mix all together and stir every day for 3 days.
Store in refrigerator.

title: mother's salad dressing
directions: Stir flour and sugar together.
Add salt, pepper and mustard. Beat egg well and add.
Add vinegar and butter; cook until a little thick.

title: butterfinger cake
directions: Bake cake according to the directions on cake mix.
Using a 9 x 13 inch pan.
While cake is hot, take a wooden spoon handle and punch holes all over top of cake and pour condensed milk over cake.
Place in refrigerator and let set overnight.
Spread Cool Whip over cake.
Crush butterfinger candy bars and sprinkle over the top.
Place in refrigerator until ready to serve.
Tip for crushing candy: place candy bars in plastic bag and beat well with rolling pin.

title: fruit cake
directions: Pour cherry over fruit; let stand overnight.
Cream the butter and sugar.
Add sour cream; beat until fluffy.
Add flavorings. Sift flour, soda and salt.
Beat eggs.
Add flour and eggs to mixture, beginning and ending with flour.
Put 1/2 cup of the flour over fruit and nuts; blend until all fruit is coated.
Pour batter over all.
Mix until blended.
Put into 2 loaf pans lined with wax paper.
Bake in middle of stove at 250° for 2 hours and 20 minutes. Keep pan with water under cake.
Let cool in oven.

title: green pea salad
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Add enough mayonnaise to combine ingredients.
Chill overnight before serving.

title: poor man's steak
directions: Mix bread, hamburger, onion, salt and pepper.
Add hot water to moisten.
Flatten into cookie sheet.
Chill in refrigerator.

title: vegetable stir-fry
directions: Coat a wok or large nonstick skillet with cooking spray.
Heat at medium-high (375°) until hot.
Add onion.
Stir-fry 3 minutes. Add carrot.
Stir-fry 2 minutes.
Add peas and sweet red pepper. Stir-fry 4 to 5 minutes or until crisp-tender.

title: lemon pork chops(pressure cooker)
directions: Brown chops in shortening.
Top each with lemon slice, onion, salt and pepper.
Combine ketchup and water; pour over chops. Close cover, cook 15 minutes.
Cool at once.
Serve chops with sauce.

title: spicy baked shrimp
directions: Combine spice ingredients in a baking dish (9 x 13-inch).
Add shrimp; toss to coat.
Refrigerate for 1 hour.
Preheat oven to 450°.
Bake shrimp for about 7 minutes.
Cook 1 1/2 bags of bow tie pasta according to directions on package.
Drain pasta and mix with shrimp.
Great with a salad and French bread!

title: hash brown skillet cake
directions: You will also need nonstick cooking spray.

title: glazed sweet potatoes
directions: In skillet, mix gelatin, cinnamon, water and salt.
Add oleo. Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Add sweet potatoes.
Cook and cover for 15 minutes or until sweet potatoes are glazed.

title: easy lemon pie
directions: Mix lemonade and milk. Then add in Cool Whip. Pour into pie crust. Refrigerate before serving.

title: banana pudding
directions: Add Eagle Brand to prepared pudding, then add sour cream. Fold in Cool Whip.
Layer cookies, bananas and pudding in large bowl.

title: potato supreme
directions: Be sure the potatoes are shredded. You can also use boiled potatoes that have been shredded. Mix together all the ingredients, saving 1/2 of the Cheddar cheese.
Put in shallow baking dish. Top with remaining cheese. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix as for butter cake, adding baking powder to first cup of flour.
Drop by teaspoon.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: mom's pie crust
directions: Put in a large bowl the lard and boiling water; stir until dissolved.
Sift together the flour, salt and baking powder.
Add to lard and water mixture.
Stir together well.
Makes three 9-inch crusts.
Will keep for a month in refrigerator if wrapped in waxed paper.

title: lasagna
directions: Cook noodles as directed on package.
Break up and brown ground beef.
Add onions and celery and 1 or 2 cloves of garlic.
Add and keep on cooking tomato sauce and paste, water and seasonings. Heat.
In medium bowl, mix cheese, slightly beaten egg and parsley.

title: cranberry sweet and sour sauce
directions: In saucepan, mix brown sugar and cornstarch.
Stir in cranberry sauce, juice, vinegar and soy sauce.
Cook over medium heat until thickened.
Serve as sauce for chicken, pork, meatballs or cocktail weiners.

title: robust chili
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Drain and rinse.
In large pot combine all ingredients.
Simmer and serve.

title: green tomato pickles(like fish house serves)
directions: Put tomatoes, onion and pepper in large pan.
Mix remaining ingredients together and then pour over the tomatoes.
Bring to a boil.
Remove from heat immediately and put in sterile jars and seal.
If you don't like anything real hot, just use about half or less hot peppers and finish with sweet peppers.

title: marys mexican soup
directions: Saute hamburger meat and onions, add celery and the rest of the ingredients.
Add pepper and salt to taste.
Cook until done on low fire.
Serve with tortillas or corn bread.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Bake cake in oblong pan and cool well.
Cut cake in half and crumble in bottom of bowl and press down.
Layer with prepared pudding, pineapple and pie filling.
Crumble other half and put on top.
Then layer with Cool Whip.
Top with coconut and pecans and cherries.
Chill well.

title: squash casserole
directions: Saute onion and squash in butter.
Add salt and pepper.
Cook until tender.
Add chilies and corn.
Pour into greased or sprayed with Pam casserole dish.
Cover with cheese.
Bake at 350° until cheese melts.

title: mamaw's chocolate pudding
directions: Mix together flour, sugar and cocoa.
Add milk and stir.
Add eggs and stir.
Add butter.
Cook over medium-low heat and cook until boiling.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla and stir.

title: mexican sausage
directions: Simmer until macaroni is cooked and water absorbed.
I add garlic and 2 cups frozen corn and use sweet Italian sausage.

title: denise's meat loaf
directions: Mix ground beef, salt, pepper, onions and green pepper.
Mix, then add corn meal.
Mix.
Bake 1 hour and 45 minutes at 350°.

title: fluffy coconut frosting
directions: Beat cream cheese until smooth.
Blend in sugar, milk and extract.
Fold in whipped topping and coconut.
Makes about 4 cups or enough to frost tops and sides of two 8 or 9-inch cake layers or a 13 x 9-inch cake.

title: famous oatmeal cookies
directions: Beat together shortening, sugars, egg, water and vanilla until creamy.
Add combined remaining ingredients; mix well.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Yields 5 dozen.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix potatoes, 1/2 cup brown sugar, eggs, 1/2 stick oleo, milk and vanilla.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Mix flour, brown sugar, nuts and 1/2 stick oleo together.
Spread over sweet potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: cornmeal surprise
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake in a greased and floured pan at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: grouper chowder
directions: Partially fry bacon.
Add onion, pepper and garlic.
Saute until tender.
Add tomato sauce, tomatoes, water and seasons. Bring to a boil.
Add potatoes; simmer until potatoes are almost cooked.
Add grouper; simmer until done.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs until light; add sugar and oil.
Mix vanilla, butter and zucchini lightly, but thoroughly.
Combine flour, salt, soda and baking powder.
Add cinnamon and cloves to zucchini mixture. Mix both batters together.
Pour into 2 greased pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chocolate pudding cake
directions: Mix all ingredients in large bowl.
Add 1/2 cup milk and 2 tablespoons melted shortening.
Mix well and pour into a 9 x 9-inch baking pan.
Combine 1 cup brown sugar and 1/4 cup cocoa in small bowl.
Sprinkle over cake batter.
Pour 1 3/4 cups hot water over entire thing.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Serve with cream or whipped cream.

title: baked strawberry pie
directions: Mix the berries, sugar and cornstarch.
Bake in double pie crust at 425° for 40 minutes.
Put slits in top crust to let out the steam.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Serve with Wheat Thins.

title: crab dip
directions: Blend cream cheese and sour cream.
Add dry mustard, Worcestershire sauce, garlic salt, lemon, Old Bay seasoning and mayonnaise.
Blend well.
Stir in crab meat and Cheddar cheese. Bake for 30 minutes at 300°, uncovered.
Serve with crackers or bread.

title: samantha's sugar cookies
directions: Cut Twinkies in two.
Place in pan.
Drain 1 can of pineapple chunks and place on Twinkies.
Cut up bananas and place on top of that.
Pour on 1 package of prepared vanilla pudding, then top with Cool Whip.

title: easy brownies
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in a bowl.
Add butter, eggs and vanilla.
Stir well.
Stir in pecans.
Pour into an 8-inch square pan. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: hard candy
directions: Dissolve sugar in corn syrup and water in saucepan.
Cook to 300° without stirring.
Remove from heat and add flavoring and coloring.
Sprinkle powdered sugar on wax covered cookie sheet. Pour candy over.
Chill about 20 minutes.
Crack and eat.

title: mexican roll-ups
directions: Mix all the ingredients in food processor until creamy, then chill. Spread over flour tortillas. Roll up and cut in bite size pieces. Dip in picante sauce.

title: peach pickles
directions: Drain syrup from peaches into a small saucepan; add spices. Heat to boiling; simmer 10 minutes.
Pour over peaches in a medium bowl.
Let stand at room temperature until cool, then chill 1 to 2 days to season.
Drain before serving.

title: casa blanca stew(heart healthy)
directions: Heat oil and saut onion, garlic and leeks over moderate heat until soft. Add spices and cook another 2 minutes, stirring frequently. Add eggplant and squashes; cook another 5 minutes. Add remaining vegetables, currants, stock and seasonings. Cover and simmer until flavors are developed. Adjust seasonings. Serve with Cornmeal Dumplings. Yield: 6 portions.

title: banana punch
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients and freeze for 3 or 4 days.
Defrost and add club soda.

title: angel whip
directions: Drain pineapple.
Combine all ingredients and pat into paper cupcake cups.
May be frozen.

title: potato chips-in-chicken
directions: Dip chicken in butter. Mix garlic salt, pepper and potato chips.
Roll chicken in mixture and place on baking sheet. Bake for 1 hour at 375° without turning.

title: ham appetillos
directions: Combine cream cheese, mayonnaise, onion and olives.
Spread thin layer of mixture on tortillas.
Arrange 4 slices of ham over cheese mixture.
Tightly roll up tortillas and wrap individually in plastic wrap.
Place in refrigerator at least 3 hours.

title: chuck wagon stew
directions: Brown ground chuck and drain.
Add can of tomatoes, can of mushroom soup and bag of noodles.
Top with cheese.
Place in 350° oven and bake until cheese melts, 10 to 15 minutes.

title: chocolate marshmallow bars(servings: 16)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and 11 1/2 x 7-inch baking pan. Melt chocolate and butter in top of double boiler over hot water. Set aside.

title: fruit salad
directions: Cook sugar, cornstarch, juice, egg yolks and butter until thick.
When cool, add Cool Whip and fold in fruit.
Chill thoroughly before serving.

title: sweet potato filled orange shells
directions: Cut oranges in 1/2 crosswise.
With grapefruit knife, remove pulp from shell.
Arrange shells on glass serving tray and set aside.
Remove membrane from orange sections.
Mash sweet potatoes until smooth.
Beat in margarine, brown sugar and ginger.
Fold in orange sections.
Spoon mixture into shells, topping each with a little brown sugar and cinnamon.
Microwave on High for 4 to 5 minutes.
Yields 8 servings.

title: creamy baked chicken
directions: Wash and pat dry chicken and place in shallow baking dish. Mix together in a bowl the soup, sour cream and vermouth.
Pour mixture over chicken and bake uncovered for 1 hour at 350°. (Yummy gravy and easy!)

title: corn pudding
directions: Beat eggs.
Melt margarine; add to eggs.
Add flour, salt, pepper and sugar; mix well.
Stir in milk and corn.
Bake in quart size baking dish at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes, or until knife comes out clean.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine sugar, shortening and egg in a large bowl.
Cream well.
Combine dry ingredients to other mixture.
Add chocolate chips and blend thoroughly.
Drop rounded teaspoonfuls 3 inches apart onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Cook 8 to 10 minutes for chewy cookies or 11 to 13 minutes for crisp cookies.
Cool on baking sheet 2 minutes before removing.

title: hacienda dip
directions: Microwave 2 minutes on High; stir.
Microwave 2 minutes on High; stir.
Serve with large Fritos.

title: summer pasta:  linguine with tomatoes and basil
directions: Combine tomatoes, Brie, basil, garlic, 1 cup olive oil, 1/2 teaspoon salt and the pepper in a large serving bowl.
Prepare at least 2 hours before serving and set aside, covered, at room temperature.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Combine flour, sugar, soda, salt and cinnamon in a large mixing bowl.
Add eggs and oil.
Stir until dry ingredients are moistened.
Do not beat.
Add vanilla, pineapple, pecans and bananas.
Spoon batter into a Bundt pan that has been greased and floured.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour or until inserted toothpick comes out clean.
Cool in pan.
Put on cake plate and frost.

title: macaroni casserole
directions: Cook macaroni until tender; drain.
Mix with all the ingredients and bake 30 minutes at 400°.

title: pineapple strata
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs.
Beat thoroughly.
Add pineapple and bread cubes.
Bake in a buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole at 350° for 1 hour.

title: amish yum-a-setta
directions: Combine beef, onion and sugar.
In deep dish, layer meat mixture, soup, noodles and cheese.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: chocolate crinkles
directions: Mix oil, chocolate and granulated sugar. Blend in one egg at a time until well mixed.
Add vanilla.
Measure flour by dipping method, baking powder and salt into oil mixture.
Chill several hours or overnight.

title: fresh tomato wheels
directions: With bottom of tuna can, cut bread into circles and toast. Layer Mozzarella cheese, tomato, Parmesan cheese and oregano. Bake in oven for 4 minutes at 300° until cheese is melted slightly.

title: squash casserole
directions: Melt margarine and stir
in stuffing mix to coat.
Line baking dish with 1/2 of
the stuffing mix.
Mix other ingredients and spoon on top of
stuffing
mix.
Add rest of stuffing mix on top. Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: new orleans spaghetti
directions: Fry onions and meat in butter until brown.
Add both cans of soup and continue cooking, stirring frequently.
May be thinned with tomato juice, if desired.
Add mushrooms and cubed cheese and continue cooking and stirring.
Serve over previously cooked spaghetti.

title: vanilla shakes
directions: Mix all ingredients in mixer until thick.

title: funnel cake
directions: Measure flour, sugar, salt and baking powder; blend ingredients with a fork.
Add oil to pan 2-inches deep and heat to 375°.
Break egg into bowl and add 2/3 cup milk.
Beat lightly. Add dry ingredients to egg and milk; beat until smooth.
Take funnel and hold finger over spout.
Spoon batter into funnel. Drop batter into frying pan.
Each cake should be about 3-inches wide.
Fry cakes until golden brown.
Drain; dust with powdered sugar.

title: hamburger stroganoff
directions: In large skillet cook and stir beef and onion in butter until onion is tender.
Stir
in
flour, salt, garlic salt and pepper. Cook 5
minutes,
stirring
constantly.
Remove
from heat; stir in soup;
simmer,
uncovered,
10 minutes.
Stir in sour cream; heat.
Serve over noodles.

title: gazpacho salad
directions: Combine in bowl.
Add Italian dressing or Lawry's Caesar dressing and mix.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: caleb's favorite peanut butter cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream together the margarine and peanut butter.
Add white and brown sugar.
Stir in egg, vanilla, salt, baking soda and flour.
Place dough, a teaspoon at a time, onto a cookie sheet, pressing each dab flat with a floured fork.
Bake for 10 minutes.
Cool a minute or two before removing from cookie sheet.
Yield: 5 dozen.
Approximate calories per serving: 50.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, beaten after each egg. Add cream, then flour, baking powder and salt.
Add vanilla.
Mix well.
Chill 20 minutes.
Roll out on floured surface (very thin). Cut with cookie cutters.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 6 minutes or until brown.

title: broccoli bread
directions: Put 1/2 stick of butter in corn bread mix, then mix all ingredients.
Melt remaining 1/2 stick butter in dish.
Bake all in oven about 20 minutes.

title: pasta with cannellini beans
directions: Heat oil, salt and pepper.
Then add bay leaves and scallions. Heat, then add garlic, basil, oregano and beans.
Let it all heat up, then add the tomatoes, some water and a little sugar to cut the acid from tomatoes.
Serve alone with salad and rolls or as a side dish with meat.

title: batter bread
directions: Preheat well greased iron skillet in 425 degree oven.
Blend all ingredients together, stirring until moistened well.
Pour batter into the greased skillet.
Bake until golden brown and knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: corn bread
directions: Mix together.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes or until brown.

title: prehistoric pudding
directions: You will need 8 to 10 plastic cups and prehistoric decorations.

title: vegetable medley
directions: Boil vegetables for 10 minutes; drain.
Add whipping cream (you do not need to whip cream), mayonnaise and cheese; mix.
Then combine vegetables with cream mixture.
Bake in a covered casserole for 1 hour at 350°.

title: pineapple white fudge
directions: Combine sugar, sour cream, corn syrup, butter and salt.
Bring to a boil over medium heat, stirring constantly until sugar dissolves.
Boil, without stirring to 236° or until a little mixture dropped into cold water forms a soft ball.
Remove from heat and let stand 15 minutes, without stirring.
Add vanilla. Beat until mixture starts to lose its gloss, about 8 minutes.
Stir in pineapple and nuts.
Pour into buttered 8-inch square pan.
Cool and cut into squares.
Yield:
36 pieces or 1 1/2 pounds.

title: five flavor pound cake
directions: Cream butter and Crisco well.
Add sugar a little at a time, creaming well.
Now add eggs, creaming well.
Add baking powder and cream well.
Now, add flour, a little at a time, alternating with milk.
Now, add the flavorings.
Pour in well-greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 2 hours.
Cool in pan, upside down, for 15 to 20 minutes.
Glaze cake is you like.

title: apple-graham crunch
directions: For small dish, lightly butter small casserole dish.
Pour in 1 can pie filling.
Mix crushed crumbs (1 cup) with 1/2 cup brown sugar and oleo.
(If desired, other spices can be added.) Sprinkle over pie filling.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes. For larger dish, use double amounts.
Other pie fillings can be used:
peach, blueberry, strawberry, etc.

title: hidden valley chicken stir-fry
directions: Heat vegetable oil in a large skillet.
Add chicken strips. Stir in dressing mix to coat chicken.
Add vegetable mix and water.
Stir-fry about 2 minutes.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: In large bowl blend first 5 ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients slowly at low speed until moistened.
Beat 1 minute longer on medium.
Pour batter into loaf pan, greased and floured on bottom only.
Bake at 350° for 60 to 75 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes.
Remove from pan and cool completely.

title: easy strawberry pie
directions: Cook pie crust.
Slice strawberries in half and arrange in pie crust.
Spread glaze over strawberries and chill.
Serve with Cool Whip.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Combine and pour the first 6 ingredients into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch dish.
Mix the remaining ingredients.
Leave lumpy and pour over chicken mixture.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Serves 6. Contains 365 calories and 9.7 gr. fat.

title: simple pudding sauce
directions: Combine sugar, cornstarch, butter and water.
Stir and cook to the boiling point.
Cool slightly; add vanilla.
The sauce may be thinned with cream.

title: melt in your mouth dinner rolls(great for cinnamon or orange rolls)
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add 1 tablespoon sugar and baking powder.
Let stand for 20 minutes.
Scald milk; add margarine, 1/2 cup sugar and salt.
Cool.
Add eggs.
Combine all with flour.
Don't add too much flour or the dough will be dry. Let dough rise until double and roll out as cinnamon rolls or dinner rolls.
Shape as desired and let rise again (before baking).
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes or until light brown.

title: strawberry congealed salad
directions: Mix Jell-O, water, strawberries, pineapple and Knox gelatine. Pour 1/2 of mixture into container. Chill until thick.

title: chocolate clair dessert
directions: Combine pudding mix and 3 cups milk in large bowl. Prepare pudding using package directions. Add whipped topping, beating with electric mixer set at medium speed until blended. Arrange a layer of graham crackers in bottom of a 13 x 9-inch dish. Spread half of pudding mixture. Add a second layer of graham crackers. Spread remaining pudding mixture. Top with another layer of graham crackers. Combine butter and chocolate in small saucepan. Cook over low heat, stirring frequently, until chocolate melts. Stir in remaining milk. Place confectioners sugar in medium bowl. Add chocolate. Beat at medium speed until icing is a spreadable consistency. Spread over layers. Chill, covered, for 8 hours. Cut into squares and serve.

title: santa fe stew
directions: Brown hamburger and pour in the other ingredients.
Simmer for a bit and serve with warmed tortillas.

title: sausage bread
directions: Divide loaves and ingredients into 6 parts.
Butter loaves and place in pan or bowl to rise.
Roll out dough lengthwise.
Rub with butter.
In center of each loaf, layer sausage, cheeses, olives, peppers and onions.
Pull ends and sides over and fold long sides over.
Butter again and let sit for 30 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: cavatelli with chicken and broccoli
directions: Bring a large pot of lightly salted water to a boil. Add pasta and cook as package directs.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Get a shin-bone.
Put over with water.
Get ready carrot, cabbage, potatoes, corn and tomato; boil carrot 1 hour, cabbage 1 hour, potatoes half hour, corn 20 minutes and tomatoes last, a little onion if desired.
Season to taste and strain through the colander.

title: pork chops with rice
directions: Brown pork chops and set aside.
Place rice in 13 x 9 x 1 1/2 or 2-inch casserole dish.
Dissolve bouillon cube in 1 1/2 cups water.
Pour over rice.
Place pork chops on top of rice.
Pour mushroom soup that has been diluted with 1/2 cup water over chops and rice.
Sprinkle with 1/2 package onion soup mix.
Cover with foil and bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: john's barbecue sauce
directions: Cook onions in oil for about 5 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients and cook about 15 minutes.

title: new mexico apple crisp
directions: Peel and slice apples.
Arrange on bottom of a 9 x 13-inch glass baking dish.
Mix together the other ingredients and blend well with pastry cutter.
Spread over apples.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour or until brown and buttery.

title: fruit pork chops
directions: Brown pork chops in 1/2 teaspoon vegetable oil; turn chops. Stir in cranberry sauce, mustard and vinegar.
Cover; simmer for 5 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: hush puppies(makes 2 dozen)
directions: Mix cornmeal, flour, onion, salt and baking powder.
Add milk and mix.
Blend in beaten egg.
Drop by spoonfuls into hot, deep fat (375°).
Fry until brown.

title: smokies in a blanket
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Spray baking sheet with nonstick cooking spray.
Pull biscuits apart at layers; each has 4 layers. Wrap around a sausage.
Bake about 10 to 15 minutes or until brown.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Cook pudding mix according to directions.
Add coconut; mix well.
Set aside, but do not chill.

title: blue cheese burgers(top these whoppers with lettuce, tomato and onion)
directions: Divide beef into 8 equal portions.
Pat each portion into 4 1/2 to 5 1/2-inch patties on waxed paper.
Sprinkle cheese evenly on 4 patties, leaving 1/2-inch border.
Top each one with another plain patty.
Pinch edges together to seal.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/2 cup water.
Beat eggs in mixing bowl. Add sugar, salt and water.
Heat to scald milk.
Add butter to milk after it is hot, then add flour and beat until smooth.
Add 3 more cups flour; knead until it can be handled.
Let rise until double, then roll out.
Take 1/2 of dough; roll out and spread with butter, brown sugar and cinnamon.
Let rise again.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: turkey dressing
directions: Mix together ingredients.
Will stuff 1 (12 pound) turkey or bake in a pan.
I always just put it around the turkey so it will brown.

title: chunky apricot preserves
directions: Combine apricots and water in a medium saucepan; let stand about 1 hour to plump.
Place over medium heat and cook until apricots are tender, about 10 minutes.
Mash into coarse chunks. Add sugar and pineapple, blending well.
Continue cooking, over low heat, until thickened, stirring occasionally, about 15 minutes.
Pour into sterilized jars and seal.
Let cool.
Store in refrigerator.
Makes about 3 1/2 cups.

title: esperregado
directions: Wash and chop greens.
Bring water and a pinch of salt to boil.
Add greens and cook until tender.
Drain and squeeze all the water out.
In a frying pan melt butter.
Add flour, salt and pepper.
Stir; add greens and mix well for about 1 minute.
Serve hot with meat or fish dishes.

title: pimento cheese spread
directions: In food processor, add first 6 ingredients.
Process until smooth.
Add pimentos and mix in well with spoon.

title: mostaccioli
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Brown meat; add green pepper and onion. Cook until tender; drain.
Stir in tomatoes, paste, water and seasonings.
In a 2-quart dish, layer half of the noodles, meat sauce and sliced Velveeta cheese.
Repeat layers.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake for 30 minutes.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix sugars, margarine, shortening, egg and vanilla.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Drop dough by rounded teaspoonfuls about 2 inches apart onto ungreased cookie sheet. Bake until light brown, 8 to 10 minutes.
Remove immediately and cool on rack.

title: pecan pie
directions: Stir together first 5 ingredients until blended.
Add nuts. Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes or until knife inserted halfway between center and edge comes out clean. Cool before cutting.

title: italian wedding soup
directions: In a large bowl, combine ground beef, bread crumbs, egg, Worcestershire sauce and garlic powder.
Mix well. Shape meatballs using 1 rounded teaspoonful meat mixture for each meatball.

title: bunkhouse chicken
directions: Combine all ingredients and marinate chicken for 24 hours. Cook on grill on low heat until tender.

title: spinach quiche
directions: Over medium heat, cook onions and garlic in chicken broth until golden.
Add spinach and spoon into bottom of pie crust; set aside.
In a bowl, combine Egg Beaters, milk, flour, basil, dill and cheese.
Pour over spinach mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until inserted knife comes out clean.
Let stand for 10 minutes before serving.

title: baked pork chops
directions: Trim excess fat from meat.
Flour and pepper meat.
Brown in oil, turning once.
While meat is browning, combine milk and soup in saucepan at low heat.
Drain meat on paper towels.
Put meat in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan sprayed with Pam.
Pour soup and milk mixture over meat.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes, then turn oven down to 250° for 1 hour and 30 minutes.

title: oriental red snapper
directions: Combine first nine ingredients.
Stir well.
Place fillets in a shallow dish.
Spread green onion mixture evenly over fillets. Cover and marinate in refrigerator 30 minutes.

title: spice cake
directions: Mix well and bake at 325° for about 1 hour in tube pan.

title: cherry-o cream cheese pie
directions: Mix the sugar with cream cheese; beat Dream Whip and milk a as per package directions.
Mix with cream cheese and spread on crust.
Refrigerate at least 2 hours.
Garnish with chilled pie filling.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Melt butter in oblong (9 x 13-inch) pan.
Mix in bowl the flour, 1 cup sugar, baking powder and milk.
Pour over melted butter.
Pour the fruit over the batter.
Stir evenly.
Pour the 3/4 cup sugar over the mixture.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: lasagne
directions: Brown sausage; drain.
Add tomato paste, water, basil, garlic and 1 teaspoon salt (Mrs. Dash).
Simmer, covered, 15 minutes. Stir occasionally.
Cook noodles; drain.
Combine eggs, Ricotta, Romano, parsley, 1/2 teaspoon salt and 1/2 teaspoon pepper.

title: hawaiian haystacks
directions: This is great for a buffet!
Each person assembles their own. Start with the rice, then chicken, layer all ingredients in order given.
Top off with a spoonful of gravy.

title: strand bakery girl scout cookies
directions: Blend sugars, shortening, eggs, molasses and baking soda-water mixture. Sift dry ingredients and mix in. Chill and roll 1/8-inch thick. Cut out with round cookie cutter. Sprinkle with sugar and water to form cracks. Bake at 350° for 12 minutes or until done.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Wash cucumbers thoroughly using a vegetable brush.
Drain on rack.
Slice cucumbers and onions into 1/8 to 1/4-inch slices.
Add onions and garlic to cucumbers.
Add salt and mix thoroughly. Cover with crushed ice or ice cubes.
Let stand 3 hours.
Drain thoroughly; remove garlic cloves.
Combine sugar, spices and vinegar.
Heat just to boiling.
Add drained cucumber and onion slices and heat quickly to boiling.
Pack hot pickles loosely into clean hot pint jars.

title: graham cracker crumb cake
directions: Mix as for an ordinary cake.
Bake in 3 (9-inch) cake pans, greased and floured.
(I line mine with waxed paper first.)
Bake at 350° until done, 25 to 30 minutes.

title: turkey and roast beef pita
directions: Chop all ingredients and stuff any combination into sliced pitas.
Top with mayo, honey mustard or favorite condiment.
Kids favorite!

title: chunky onion dip
directions: Mix all ingredients with a fork until lumpy.
Cover and refrigerate for 2 hours.
Serve with raw vegetables: celery, carrots, zucchini, etc.

title: heath fluff
directions: Pound Heath bars with a hammer until they are crushed.
Mix these with Cool Whip in a Pyrex dish.
Place a layer of ladyfingers, then Cool
Whip mix, ladyfingers and top with Cool Whip mix.
Refrigerate until ready to use.

title: saltine cracker cake
directions: Beat egg whites until fluffy.
Add flavoring and cream of tartar.
Continue to beat while adding sugar.
Fold in saltines and pecans.
Bake in oblong dish (9 x 13-inch) pan for thirty minutes at 350°.
Cake should cool until cold.
Then add 12 ounces of Cool Whip on top of cooled cake.
Then sprinkle with coconut to your liking.
Keep refrigerated until ready to serve.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Layer ingredients in order given. Top with bread crumbs & several pats of butter. Bake at 350 degrees for about 30 minutes.

title: cinnamon pie
directions: Mix as written.
Gradually add 1 1/2 cups of Borden's condensed milk with half and half.
Stir well, then add 2 egg whites, not too stiff.
Fold in gently.
Pour mix into pie shell. Bake until pie sets at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: ham-pizza burgrs
directions: Total cooking time: 5 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil breasts in water about 20 minutes.
Skin and bone chicken.
Cut in pieces.
Spread dressing in a 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: manicotti
directions: Cook sausage.
Divide in half.
To first half, add tomato sauce and paste, water and brown sugar.
Simmer 15 minutes.
To second half, add Ricotta cheese, 2 cups Mozzarella cheese, egg and parsley.
Pour half of sauce in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Stuff noodles with cheese mixture and put on sauce.
Pour remaining sauce over manicotti.
Sprinkle with remaining cup of cheese.
Bake, uncovered, for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: carrot cake
directions: Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Preheat oven to 350°. Mix together the flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt and cinnamon.
Add oil, sugar and eggs; mix well.
Fold in carrots and raisins.
Bake for 30 to 45 minutes.
Allow to cool before frosting.

title: dinner rolls
directions: Place shortening, salt and honey in bowl.
Add water and stir well.
Add beaten eggs and stir into mixture with yeast.
Add flour all at once and stir to make a soft dough.
Knead into a ball.
Place in a greased bowl and cover.
Let rise for 1 1/2 hours.
Knead down.
Make into rolls.
Let rise approximately 45 minutes.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes at 400°.

title: aunt jackie's jello salad
directions: Drain fruit well.
Mix dry jello with fruit and cottage cheese.
Mix.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Chill for at least 1 hour or longer.

title: cornmeal pancakes(no eggs!)
directions: In a mixing bowl, stir together flour, cornmeal, baking powder and soda.
Add buttermilk.
Stir until blended.
For each pancake, pour about 1/4 cup batter onto a hot, greased skillet or griddle, spreading to a 4-inch circle.
Cook until golden.
Good served with applesauce or maple syrup.

title: zucchini bake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Mix all of above ingredients thoroughly.
Pour in pan and bake 45 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve hot.
Yields 9 large servings.

title: cream of potato soup
directions: Pare and dice potatoes.
Cover well with water and boil until soft.
Do not drain.
Add salt and celery.
Put a heaping tablespoon of butter in skillet and brown flour.
To this gradually add milk.
When milk begins to thicken, add it to the cooked potatoes and water.
Simmer and stir until mixed.
May add parsley.

title: party pinwheels
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients. Spread on tortillas. Drain vegetables and blot dry on paper towels. Sprinkle equal amounts of vegetables on top of cream cheese. Roll tortillas tightly. Chill at least 2 hours. Cut rolls into 1-inch pieces. Discard ends. Serve spirals facing up. (Can be prepared with diced veggies of choice!) Makes 3 dozen.

title: english cider cake(makes 8 servings.)
directions: Into medium mixing bowl, sift together flour, baking powder and seasonings; set aside.
Preheat oven to 375°.

In small mixing bowl, using mixer at medium speed, cream margarine with granulated sugar; add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition. Add egg mixture alternately with cider to flour mixture, stirring until batter is smooth.
Fold in fruits.
Line bottom of 7 3/8 x 3 5/8 x 2 1/2-inch loaf pan with paper.
Pour batter into pan; bake for 40 to 50 minutes (until cake tester inserted in center comes out dry).
Let cake cool in pan for 5 minutes, then remove to wire rack.
Let cool 10 minutes longer.
Using a sieve or tea strainer, sift confectioners sugar over loaf.
To serve, cut into 8 equal slices.

title: salad dressing chocolate cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar, soda and cocoa.
Add salad dressing, water and vanilla.
Stir until smooth.
Put into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 35 to 40 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: ambrosia salad
directions: Drain pineapple (save juice).
Add cold water to measure 1 cup.
Stir boiling water into jello.
