Add measured liquid. Refrigerate 1 1/4 hours or until slightly thickened.
Stir in Cool Whip.
Refrigerate 10 minutes or until mixture will mound.
Stir in pineapple, oranges, marshmallows and coconut.
Refrigerate three hours until firm.
Makes 10 servings.

title: chocolate rolls *
directions: Mix the last four ingredients together.
Spread over rolled biscuit dough.
Roll up and slice 3/4-inch thick.
Bake like biscuits.
The roll freezes well before baking.

title: homos bi tahini
directions: Rinse and drain chickpeas.
Place all in food processor and process until blended.
Serve with oil, parsley and ground red pepper sprinkled on top.

title: green eggs and ham
directions: Read story of Stone Soup to children.
Place stone in water (large stock pot is needed).
Add bouillon, tomatoes, onion and carrots.
Cook 10 minutes.
Add potatoes and celery and meat. After 10 minutes, add frozen vegetables, one box at a time.
Allow soup to boil gently between each additional box of frozen vegetables.
Cook on medium heat for 20 minutes, stirring often. Cut heat and simmer for 1 hour, stirring occasionally.
Makes large pot of soup to share.
Children love to help cook this.

title: beef and cabbage casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown ground beef.
Drain off excess fat.
Cut up cabbage, potato, carrots and onion.
Add rice and tomato soup.
Add 1 cup water and more if necessary.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Serves 6.

title: chicken-broccoli casserole
directions: Mix lemon juice, mayonnaise, milk, and soup together in saucepan; stir in chicken and onions.
Cut broccoli into small pieces; add to pan.
Cook for 1 or 2 minutes.
Pour into a buttered 9x13 inch pan.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake at 350 degrees for 45 minutes.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream
butter and sugar.
Add other ingredients and mix well. Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: cheese filled bread
directions: Soften cream cheese and Wispride.
Cream together.
Add ginger ale.
Mix
well
and chill.
Cut top off loaf of bread. Take out center of bread.
Break bread into small chunks.
Put chilled cheese
into
hollow bread.
Place bread chunks around cheese bread.

title: catfish chowder
directions: Cook fish until tender in 1 1/2 cups water.
Add bacon, broken into
small
pieces, add butter and let simmer.
Saute celery and
onions in 2 tablespoons butter.
Add cooked potatoes
and simmer all until serving time.
Serve on crisp toast points.
Good with tart apple salad.

title: chili beans
directions: Cook ground beef and onion together until brown. Simmer all ingredients together. Add pintos and kidney beans.

title: apple butter
directions: Boil cider for 15 minutes.
Add sliced apples and cook until soft.
Force through a sieve to remove skins and seeds.
Return to kettle.
Add spice, sugar and salt.
Cook slowly until thick and smooth, stirring to prevent scorching.
Pour into jars or crock. Makes about 4 pints.

title: party punch
directions: Combine
gelatin and boiling water.
Stir until gelatin dissolves.	Add juices and water.
Freeze.	To serve, partially thaw frozen mixture.
Put in punch bowl and add ginger ale. It should be slushy.
Yields 7 quarts.

title: buttermilk fried chicken
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients.
Pour buttermilk mixture over top of chicken.
Cover and refrigerate at least 30 minutes.
Remove chicken from liquid.

title: chicken with pineapple
directions: Cut chicken into serving pieces and coat with mixture of flour, salt and pepper.
Drain pineapple, reserving juice.
Heat butter in heavy skillet and brown pineapple lightly on both sides. Remove from skillet; add oil and cook onion rings until golden. Remove onion and brown chicken in same fat.
Place chicken and onion in casserole dish.
Measure pineapple juice and add enough chicken bouillon to make 2 cups; pour over chicken.
Season with salt and pepper.
Bake about 30 minutes at 350°; 20 minutes before serving, add defrosted peas and pineapple slices.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Mix the chicken, soup, veggies, poultry seasoning and garlic salt in ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.

title: old-time pineapple cheese cake
directions: The cream should be set in freezer at least 3 hours before making this cheese cake.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Beat together cream cheese and powdered sugar until fluffy. Add milk, peanut butter, vanilla and 1/3 of the Cool Whip.
Fold in remainder of Cool Whip and put into pie crust.
Chill at least 1 hour.

title: mini cheesecakes
directions: Crush and sift cookies, place 1 tsp. In each tassie cup. Mix cheese, sugar eggs and vanilla. Put 1 tbsp. filling in each cup. Bake at 350 Degrees for 15 minutes. When cool add cherries.

title: rhubarb pie
directions: Combine 1 1/2 cups sugar with flour, salt, butter and egg yolks.
Beat well.
Beat egg whites until stiff, adding 1/2 cup sugar.
Fold into egg yolk mixture; fold in rhubarb.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake in preheated oven at 400° for 10 minutes, reduce heat to 325° and bake 40 to 50 minutes.

title: charlotte carmean's party noodle casserole
directions: Saute onion in butter until golden.
Mix together all ingredients.
Place in 1 1/2-quart buttered casserole.
Top with bread crumbs, which have been mixed with butter.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: cheese krispies
directions: Mix all of the ingredients except the Rice Krispies with a pastry blender.
Then add Rice Krispies, mixing by hand, as the mixture will be very stiff.
Make ball about the size of a marble and flatten them gently with a fork.
Bake on lightly greased cookie sheet for 10 to 15 minutes in a 325° oven.

title: garlic dill pickles
directions: Use jar or jars from quart size to gallon size.
Wash cukes. Put pickling spice and cloves of garlic (gash a few of these but don't cut all the way through) in jar.
Pack cukes in jar (whole). Add a little fresh dill weed.
Add vinegar and enough hot water to dissolve salt.
Fill jar or jars.
Cover and leave on kitchen counter 2 days.
Refrigerate and enjoy.
(Must be kept in refrigerator.)

title: dill chicken
directions: Mix together wheat germ, almonds, salt, pepper and dill weed. Dip chicken pieces in yogurt and then wheat germ mixture; dredge to coat.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Brown and drain sausage.
Mix this with all other ingredients in a
9 x 12-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: sausage potato lasagna
directions: In a large skillet, cook sausage until no longer pink. Add onion, pepper, garlic and basil and cook 5 minutes longer over medium heat. In a 13 x 9 x 2-inch nonstick baking pan or dish prepared with cooking spray, use half of the potato slices, layering flat in the bottom of baking pan. Using half of sausage mixture, layer over potatoes. Using half of the cheeses, layer Mozzarella, then cheese cubes. Repeat layers in the same order with the remaining half of potatoes, sausage and cheese.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and cook noodles in salt water.
Mix all ingredients together and bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: baked rice
directions: Cook rice according to package directions and set aside.

title: tuna stuffed potatoes(english supper)
directions: Scrub potatoes and poke holes in them.
Bake in 375° oven for about 1 1/2 hours.
Cut slice from top and scoop out flesh.
Mash it along with butter, salt, pepper and parsley.
Add flaked tuna (drain first).
Add sour cream.
Mix thoroughly.
Fill shells with mixture.
Place one strip of crisp bacon on top of each potato. Return to oven.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: peanut butter fingers
directions: Combine together the margarine, 1/2 cup sugar and 1/2 cup brown sugar.
Blend in egg, 1/3 cup peanut butter, baking soda, salt, vanilla, flour and oats.
Spread in ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: rita's lasagna
directions: Brown your ground beef and season the meat to taste.
I sprinkle meat with seasoned salt, garlic powder, minced onion, salt and pepper.
Drain the meat and combine with sauce.
Heat until bubbling, then simmer while you cook lasagna noodles.
When noodles are done, drain and layer bottom of 11 x 14-inch baking pan, sprayed with cooking spray, then cover noodles with sauce and slice Mozzarella cheese and place on top of sauce.
Layer again with noodles and sauce.
I alternate this layer with the Jack and Cheddar cheese.
Put the last layer of noodles and sauce on.
Then grate the remainder of 3 cheeses and sprinkle the top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Let sit for 10 minutes.

title: coffee marinade
directions: Combine all; mix well.
Will marinate 4 pounds London broil, arm roast, etc.
Excellent for most red meats.

title: chicken pie
directions: Have ready your chicken, stewed to taste, and gravy (all piping hot) in a baking dish.
Drop the batter by spoonfuls over the chicken and bake in a moderate oven.

title: almond, chicken and rice casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients in baking dish and top with crushed potato chips.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: cobbler (fruit)
directions: Melt butter in casserole dish.
Mix sugar, flour and milk together.
Put in casserole dish.
Dump fruit in center and bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until brown.

title: chess pie
directions: Beat eggs, then add other ingredients.
Pour in pie shell and bake at 400° for 10 minutes, then at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: mama weaver's raisin roll
directions: Crumble wafers.
Add raisins, nuts and milk.
Work together with hands.
Make into 3 clumps.
Form each clump into a log and roll in powdered sugar.
Put in refrigerator.
Slice when ready to serve.

title: dq treat
directions: Crush cookies well; add melted butter and press on bottom of 9 x 13 pan. Spread slightly whipped ice cream over cookie mixture. Top with peanuts. Freeze 1 hour.

title: canned fruit dessert
directions: Mix well and chill thoroughly.
Serve alone or on cake or ice cream.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream together margarine, vegetable oil, both sugars and vanilla.
Add eggs.
Beat until fluffy.
Mix flour, salt, baking soda and cream of tartar and add to creamed mixture.
Mix until smooth.

title: 7-up cake
directions: Mix cake and bake at 350° in 3 layers.

title: addictive date roll
directions: **Make sure you have more nuts than fruit, ex: pistachios, almonds, cashews, pecans, etc.

title: split pea soup
directions: In Dutch oven or large kettle over medium heat, heat ham bone, split peas, carrots, onion and 7 cups of water to boiling. Meanwhile, tie allspice, peppercorns and bay leaf in a cheesecloth bag.
Add to ham bone mixture.
Reduce heat to low and simmer uncovered for 1 hour.
Discard spice bag.
Add salt to taste. Remove meat from bone and return meat to soup.
Discard bone. Makes about 7 cups or 6 servings.

title: rice casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Cut zucchini in half crosswise; cut each half lengthwise into quarters.
Toss with oil, salt and pepper in large bowl.
Arrange zucchini on a jelly roll pan in a single layer.
Roast 30 minutes, until tender.
Transfer to serving bowl. Serves 8.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Spread rice in greased casserole dish.
Arrange chicken breasts over rice.
Sprinkle onion soup over chicken breasts and rice.
Pour water over mixture.
Spoon mushroom soup over all. Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Remove foil and brown for 10 minutes.

title: snicker bar cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 350.
In a food processor, grind cookies into fine crumbs.
Add butter and process until well blended.
Press into bottom and about 1 inch up sides of 9 1/2 or 10 inch springform pan.
In a large bowl, beat together cream cheese and sugar with an electric mixer on medium speed until smooth, 1 to 2 minutes.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Beat in vanilla and 1 cup cream; beat 3 to 4 minutes.
Fold 1 1/2 cups cut-up Snickers pieces.
Turn into crumb-lined pan.
Bake 1 hour and 15 to 25 minutes, or until cheesecake is almost set but center still jiggles slightly.
Let cool to room temperature.
Sprinkle remaining candy pieces over top of cheesecake.
Refrigerate at least 4 to 5 hours before serving.
Run a knife around edge of pan to loosen cake and remove springform side of pan.
Just before serving, drizzle with chocolate syrup.
Whip remaining 1 cup cream until stiff and spoon dollop over each slice.

title: tomato delights(for tomi sue, debbie, shirley and ken)
directions: Cut a slice from each tomato top.
Scoop out pulp, leaving shells intact and reserve pulp.
Sprinkle insides lightly with salt; invert to drain.
Chop tomato pulp. Saute green pepper and onion in butter; add pulp and remaining ingredients. Spoon mixture into tomatoes and put in shallow baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Garnish.

title: pretzel surprise
directions: Mix well and press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 6 minutes.
Cool.

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: Skin chicken if desired.
Rinse and pat dry.
In a large skillet, cook chicken, onion and garlic in hot oil about 15 minutes or until chicken is lightly browned, turning to brown evenly.
Drain off fat.
Stir together mushrooms, tomato sauce, undrained tomatoes, wine, broth, basil, bay leaf, 1/4 teaspoon salt and 1/4 teaspoon pepper.
Pour over chicken in skillet. Bring to boiling.
Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer for 30 to 35 minutes or until chicken is tender and no longer pink.
Transfer chicken to a platter.
Cover and keep warm.
Discard bay leaf. Skim fat from tomato mixture.
Stir together cornstarch and 2 tablespoons cold water.
Stir into tomato sauce mixture.
Cook and stir until bubbly.
Cook and stir 2 minutes longer.
Serve over chicken and noodles.
Serves 6.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Coat beef with mixture of flour, salt and pepper.
Brown meat in shortening in large frypan or Dutch oven.
Stir in remaining ingredients, except sour cream, sherry and rice.
Heat to boiling. Reduce heat; cook for 20 to 30 minutes.
Stir in sour cream and sherry; heat through, but do not boil.
Serve over rice or noodles.
Makes 4 servings.

title: bull's eye barbecue burgers
directions: Combine meat and seasonings.
Mix lightly. Shape into 4 patties.

title: jello pudding dirt cups
directions: You will need 8 to 10 (7 ounce) cups.

title: salsa
directions: Mix all ingredients and refrigerate.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: corn casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix together in large bowl the corn, cream of celery soup and sour cream.
Pour this mixture into 13 x 9-inch baking dish, then sprinkle crunched Ritz crackers on top. Melt butter and pour over cracker crumbs, evenly.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: supreme skillet burgers
directions: Chop the celery, bell pepper and onion into fine pieces.
Add garlic salt, paprika, pepper and eggs. Combine all ingredients with ground meat.
Mix well.
Make patties to your liking. Dredge patties in flour and fry in shortening.
Cook until done over medium heat. Arrange in an attractive appearance. Garnish with pineapple.

title: sloppy joe pie
directions: In large bowl, combine biscuit mix and parsley.
Add water; stir until moistened.
Reserve 3/4 cup of the dough.
With lightly floured hands, pat dough onto bottom and sides of a greased 2-quart dish.
In saucepan, combine beans, tomato sauce, beef and seasoning mix; heat through.
Spoon mixture over dough. Drop reserved dough by spoonfuls around edge of dish.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes or until dumplings are golden.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: rice salad
directions: Blend all ingredients thoroughly.
Chill.
Serve on lettuce leaves, if desired.

title: zucchini-hamburger pie
directions: Brown hamburger with onion and dry seasonings.
Add bread crumbs, cheese and green pepper.
Line a large, deep pie pan with pastry crust.
Layer one-half of the zucchini in the pie shell. Top the zucchini layer with one-half of the meat mixture.
Repeat these layers using the rest of the zucchini and meat.
Top with tomato slices, adding a bit of tomato juice if the tomatoes are not juicy and ripe.
(You may also use canned tomatoes, whole or sliced.)
Cover with pastry, cut small hole in center of crust and dust with pepper.
Bake one hour at 350°.

title: gourmet potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes with skin on until slightly tender; cool. Remove skins and shred potatoes.
Add remaining ingredients. Sprinkle paprika on top.
Put in greased casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: three flavors fried rice
directions: Set ingredients (prepared and measured) by stove in order listed.
Set skillet over high heat for 30 seconds.
Swirl in half of the oil.
Add onions; brown lightly.
Add shrimp; stir-fry 3 minutes.
Salt.
Add eggs; scramble until cooked.
Remove from pan.
Swirl remaining oil in pan, then add chicken.
Stir-fry 2 minutes.
Add rice, soy sauce and pepper.
Stir and toss until all is heated.
Add eggs and stir.
Add lettuce last, just before serving and serve with soy sauce.

title: pizza pie
directions: Break sausage into pieces and brown. Drain and let stand for further use.

title: sugarless fruit cake(yields 2 loaf pans)
directions: Place first 5 ingredients in saucepan.
Bring to a boil and simmer 2 minutes.
Cool.
Add remaining ingredients and bake for 40 minutes at 350° in 2 loaf pans, coated with vegetable spray.

title: peas continental
directions: Heat butter in a skillet.
Saute mushrooms and onions about 5 minutes, or until tender.
Add salt, pepper, nutmeg, marjoram, sherry and then peas.
Makes 4 servings.

title: no-bake pumpkin pie
directions: In
medium
bowl
beat egg; beat in sweetened condensed milk and
spices.
In medium saucepan, sprinkle gelatine over water; let
stand
1 minute.
Over low heat, stir until gelatine dissolves.
Add
sweetened
milk mixture; over low heat, cook and stir constantly until mixture thickens slightly, 5 to 10 minutes. Remove from heat.
Add pumpkin.
Pour into crust. Chill 4
hours or until set.
Garnish as desired.
Refrigerate leftovers.
Makes 1 pie.

title: three bean salad
directions: Wash and drain beans.
Combine all beans, onion and celery in bowl.
In pan, put sugar, vinegar and oil.
Bring to boil.
Pour over bean mixture.
Chill.

title: layered banana pudding
directions: In medium saucepan, combine the flour and brown sugar.
Stir in milk.
Cook and stir over medium heat until thickened and bubbly.
Cook and stir 1 minute more.
Remove from the heat.

title: caramel cake
directions: Prepare the cake mix as directed; let cool.
Punch holes in cake with handle of wooden spoon.
Pour the sweetened condensed milk over cake; chill.
Pour over that the caramel butterscotch sauce.
Chill.
Top with Cool Whip, or serve on the side.

title: four pepper pasta
directions: Prepare mostaccioli as label directs, using 2 teaspoons salt. Cut peppers and onions into 1/2-inch wide strips.

title: curried fruit
directions: Bring to boil the last 5 ingredients.
Pour mixture over fruit.
Put in oven for 20 minutes at 350°.
Serve warm.

title: sweet raisin rolls
directions: Mix sugar, flour, butter, honey and raisins.
Cut a hole in center
of each roll and fill with mixture.
Place on baking sheet and bake at 375° for about 15 minutes.

title: spinach dip
directions: Thaw spinach and squeeze dry in paper towels.
Stir together spinach and remaining ingredients, blending well.
Cover and refrigerate at least 2 hours.

title: baked custard(makes six 4-ounce servings)
directions: Dissolve sugar and salt in milk.
Add vanilla.
Bring to a boil.
Add to eggs and mix lightly.
Place in custard cups. Place cups in pan of hot water (not boiling).
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Center should not be quite set.
Custard cooks after removal from oven.
A knife inserted between center and outer edge should come out clean.
Cool.

title: tamale pie
directions: Make cornmeal mush and line a casserole.
Brown onions and hamburger in oil.
After hamburger and onions are cooked, add the rest and put into a cornmeal lined casserole.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Add sliced cheese on top and melt.

title: homemade biscuits
directions: Mix together well.
Grease pan.
Roll out.
Cook at 425° until golden brown.

title: striped delight
directions: Combine graham cracker crumbs, 1/4 cup sugar and melted butter.
Press firmly into 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: chinese beef steak
directions: Cut steak into 1 1/2 to 1/8-inch thick (very thin) slices. Season with soy sauce, sugar, wine, M-retsin and cornstarch; mix well.
Heat skillet; brown chopped ginger and garlic in butter. Add meat strips; brown.
Then add sauce from No. 2 and heat.

title: health nuggets
directions: Cream the margarine, peanut butter, brown sugar, honey, egg and vanilla.
Combine the flour, salt, soda and powdered milk, wheat germ and oats; add to creamed mixture and mix well.
Add nuts, coconut and chips. Press into 1 inch balls, place on greased cookie sheet and flatten slightly.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: chocolate fudge sauce
directions: Melt margarine/butter in a saucepan.
Sift sugar and cocoa together, add to butter.
Add milk gradually.
Bring to a boil over medium heat.
Stir until thick.
Store in refrigerator.

title: filled cookies
directions: Mix and put in fridge to cool, about 1 hour.
Roll out thin and cut to size wanted.
Put 1 teaspoon filling on cookie, covering with second cookie.
Press edges together with fork.
Bake in 375° oven for 12 minutes.

title: baked plantains in orange sauce(uganda)
directions: Peel and slice 3 very ripe bananas.
Place in greased baking dish and dot with margarine.
Pour orange juice over bananas. Sprinkle with orange rind and ground cinnamon.
Bake, uncovered, 20 to 25 minutes, basting occasionally.
Serve warm with dab of whipped cream, ice cream or frozen yogurt (optional).

title: sour cream salmon loaf
directions: Drain half of the liquid off the salmon. Add all the ingredients together; mix well.
Place in a loaf pan.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes.

title: prize-winning chili
directions: Saute onion, bell pepper, celery and jalapeno in a small amount of oil.
Add the meat and braise.
Drain.
Mix in the remaining ingredients.
Add enough water to cover the top of the mixture. Cook the chili for three hours over a low heat.

title: lemon snow
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water; let set, but not too stiff.
Put into bowl and add lemon juice slowly while beating.
Beat in sugar a little at a time.
Beat until thick and foamy.
Beat chilled evaporated milk until stiff.
Fold in gelatin mixture.
Put 1 cup of crushed wafers on bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour lemon mix in center.
Top off with wafer crumbs.
Chill about 3 hours.

title: veggie bars
directions: All vegetables are raw.
Olives or other toppings are optional.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Pour 1 1/4 cup boiling water over oatmeal.
Let stand for 20 minutes.
Cream together oleo, brown and white sugar and eggs. Sift together flour, cinnamon, salt and soda. Add the creamed mixture and stir; add the oatmeal last and mix well.
Pour into loaf pan and bake 30 minutes or until done at 350°.
Frost with Caramel Frosting.

title: poppy seed yogurt cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time, beating after each addition.
Combine flour, soda and salt; add alternately with yogurt to creamed mixture, beginning and ending with flour.
Stir in vanilla, poppy seed and nuts. Pour into greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Cool before removing from pan.
(Try custard sauce on it.)

title: cheese cake cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add flour and walnuts.
Mix to make a crumb mixture.
Reserve 1 cup for topping.
Press in greased 8-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes until light brown (325° for glass pan).
Don't overbake.
Blend cheese and sugar; add egg, milk, lemon juice and vanilla.
Blend with mixer or food processor. Spread over baked crumb mixture.
Sprinkle with reserved cup of crumbs.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350° (325° for glass pan).
Cool and cut into 2-inch squares.

title: sweetened condensed milk
directions: Combine all ingredients in container of an electric blender. Process until smooth.
Store in refrigerator.
Yields 1 1/2 cups. Equals 1 commercial can.

title: cake mix cookies
directions: Mix and shape into cookies.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes. Don't overcook.

title: mixed bean salad
directions: Drain beans.
Mix together.
Let stand in refrigerator for 24 hours.
Pack into jars, if desired.
Will keep for up to 3 weeks.

title: bow tie pasta salad
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Refrigerate several hours (overnight best).
Serve on top fresh salad greens.

title: raspberry cream cheese coffee cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour bottom and sides of 9 or 10-inch springform pan.
Lightly spoon flour into measuring cup; level off.
In large bowl, combine flour and 3/4 cup sugar.
Using pastry blender or fork, cut in margarine until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Reserve 1 cup crumb mixture.
To remaining crumb mixture, add baking powder, baking soda, salt, sour cream, 1 egg and almond extract; blend well.
Spread batter over bottom and 2 inches up sides of prepared pan.
(Batter should be about 1/4 inch thick on sides.)

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: In a medium bowl mix flour, soda and salt.
Break egg into a small bowl and beat until foamy.
In a large bowl cream Crisco, brown and white sugars.
Beat well.
Add beaten egg and beat well. Stir in peanut butter and vanilla.
Gradually stir in flour mixture.
Blend well.
Shape into small balls.
Flatten with a fork, making crisscross marks.
Bake approximately 10 minutes at 375°.

title: chili soup
directions: Fry to brown and drain the ground beef, celery, onion, salt and pepper.
Add rest of the ingredients after sauce has cooked.

title: jane boones
directions: Cream together butter and peanut butter.
Add powdered sugar and vanilla and cream together.
Add graham cracker crumbs, coconut and chopped pecans and mix with hands.
Roll into small balls and place on wax paper.
Place in freezer to harden.

title: peanut butter apple bars
directions: Grease and flour a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Set aside. In a small mixing bowl, stir together the whole wheat flour and baking soda. Set aside.

In a large mixer bowl, beat the peanut butter and margarine or butter with an electric mixer on medium speed about 30 seconds or until softened. Add the sugar and vanilla, beating until well combined. Add the eggs, one at a time, beating for 1 minute after each addition.

Stir in the applesauce, then add the flour mixture to the peanut butter mixture, stirring until well blended. Stir in the rolled oats and wheat germ. Turn the batter into the prepared pan. Bake in a 350° oven about 25 minutes or until a toothpick inserted in center comes out clean. Cool completely in the pan on a wire rack. To serve, cut into bars.
Makes 32 bars.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt oleo in 8 x 10-inch Pyrex; while melting, combine 1 cup sugar with peaches on stove top.
Mix all other ingredients together, then pour over peaches.
Bake at 300° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Add all ingredients and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 300° for 40 minutes.

title: patti's yummy chocolate chip brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix eggs, melted butter and sugars together and blend well.
Add vanilla, baking soda, salt and flour and mix thoroughly.
Fold in chocolate chips.
Mixture should be fairly stiff.
Spoon into a 9 x 12-inch pre-greased cake pan. Bake 12 to 15 minutes; cut into small squares while still warm and serve with a cold glass of milk.
A great after school snack!

title: cry baby cookies
directions: Cream shortening.
Add sugar, molasses and eggs.
Sift flour, baking powder, salt and soda.
Combine coconut, nuts and raisins. Add dry ingredients alternately with milk to creamed mixture. Drop by spoonfuls onto greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Makes 9 1/2 dozen.

title: french silk pie
directions: Preheat
oven
Mix all ingredients and spread on bottom
of a buttered 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake for 15 minutes.
Remove from oven; stir, pat smooth and chill.

title: chicken salad
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in
a large bowl. In another bowl, combine mayonnaise, onion and salt. Add to chicken mixture, stirring gently. Spoon onto lettuce leaves. Makes 5 cups.

title: chocolate chip brownies
directions: Melt margarine in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Pour over brown sugar; stir and let cool a few minutes.
Add eggs and vanilla; stir well. Set aside.
Sift flour and add coconut and pecans to flour.
Stir dry ingredients into brown sugar mixture, a little at a time until all is well blended.
Pour into pan.
Spread chocolate chips on top of batter.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: red salad
directions: Heat undrained pineapple in a saucepan until bubbly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in gelatin until dissolved.
Cool to room temperature.
Fold in whipped topping.
Spoon into mold or dish. Chill until set.
Makes 6 servings.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix all ingredients except shrimp.
Whip until fluffy.
Mash shrimp and add to cheese mixture.
Chill.

title: glazed carrots and onions
directions: In a skillet, heat corn syrup and margarine over medium heat until melted.
Add salt and ginger.
Cook for 10 minutes, stirring occasionally or until thick.
Add cooked carrots and onions, stirring occasionally for about 8 minutes or until the vegetables are glazed.
Yield:
4 servings.

title: zucchini squash dressing
directions: Mix well and place in a 9 x 13-inch buttered Pyrex pan.
Cook at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: jeannette's caramels
directions: In a heavy pan, heat syrup to boil. Add oleo, bring to boil. Add sugar, bring to boil. Add milk, bring to boil. Lower heat and cook to soft ball stage ("firm"). Add vanilla and nuts. Pour into buttered pan. Cool and cut.

title: cliffie's punch
directions: Put juice into punch bowl.
Add just 1 can of cold water.
Add the ginger ale.
Add ice.

title: quail in a bag
directions: Grease pan.
Put 1 tablespoon flour in a large cooking bag and shake well, coating sides evenly.
Split dressed birds down the back.
Salt and red pepper them.
Rub seasonings well into the birds.
Put the birds in the bag.
Add all the other ingredients to the bag to tie.
Punch 12 holes in top of the bag with a 2-tined fork.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: rice pudding
directions: Boil 1 cup of rice.
Add evaporated milk, can of water, 1/2 cup sugar and vanilla.
Blend together.
Beat egg whites until stiff, adding sugar as needed (2 tablespoons sugar).
Fold into Rice Pudding.
Bake at 350° for 3/4 to 1 hour.

title: layered chocolate dessert
directions: Mix flour, margarine and nuts; press into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° approximately 10 minutes.
Cool.

title: pineapple salad
directions: Drain pineapple and use juice with 1/2 cup sugar and 2 tablespoons flour added.
Cook until thick.
Pour over other ingredients.
Cool in refrigerator.

title: broccoli cheese casserole
directions: Put broccoli in boiling water for 8 to 10 minutes.
While broccoli cooks, mix rice and chicken soup.
Put in warmed Cheez Whiz and broccoli; mix all together.
Put in dish and bake in warm oven for 20 minutes.
Can be doubled.

title: tomato beef skillet supper
directions: First, marinate the beef in basic gravy that glazes meat and vegetables.
The mixture is cornstarch, oil and soy sauce. Combine cornstarch, 1 tablespoon oil, soy sauce and pepper in bowl.
Add beef; toss and coat well.
Let stand several hours in refrigerator.
Drain and save marinade.

title: puffy french toast
directions: Beat all ingredients until smooth.
Dip bread in mixture, turning to coat on each side, about 30 seconds per side.
Fry in butter on each side until golden brown.
Serve with maple syrup.

title: ham hors d'oeuvres
directions: Cream first 4 ingredients together.
Spread mixture on cold ham slices, roll up.
Chill overnight and slice into serving size roll-ups.

title: roast new potatoes with garlic and rosemary
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Scrub new potatoes well.
If they're large, cut them into halves or quarters.
Combine olive oil, garlic and rosemary and salt and pepper to taste in bowl.
Add potatoes and toss until coated.
Transfer potatoes to shallow baking dish.
Roast, uncovered, until crisp on the outside and tender inside, about 20 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: hot rice dressing
directions: Cook rice in 2 cups chicken broth.
Brown sausage and drain grease.
Add celery, onions and bell peppers.
Cook until tender. Mix meat and rice together.
Pour into baking dish, then pour remaining chicken broth over it.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.
Do not use black pepper if you use hot sausage.

title: sour cream coffee cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream the butter and 2 cups of sugar until light and creamy.
Beat in eggs one at a time.
Fold in vanilla and sour cream.
Add flour, salt and baking powder gradually.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli until tender.
Beat eggs and add soup and mayonnaise.
Mix well.
Break up 3/4 of cheese and add to mixture and stir.
Drain broccoli and add to mixture and place in baking dish.
Sprinkle remaining cheese over the top.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: black and white enchiladas
directions: Mix chicken and hamburger together and set aside.
Mix soup, broth, sour cream, chilies and onion together.
Heat this mixture over low heat until smooth and very warm but not boiling.
Using hot oil, quickly heat tortillas 6 to 7 seconds on each side.
Put meat on tortilla.
Cover with some sauce.
Add small amount of cheese.
Roll and place seam side down in pan.
After all are done, pour remaining sauce over all and add a layer of cheese on top.
Bake at 350° until cheese has melted good, 15 to 20 minutes.

title: easy cherry cobbler
directions: Mix cherry pie filling with almond extract and pour into a buttered 9 x 9-inch pan. Sprinkle cake mix and nuts over pie filling.
Drizzle melted butter over all. Bake in a 350° oven for 55 minutes. Serve warm with ice cream.

title: refrigerator fruit cake
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients, then add Eagle Brand milk.
Use hands to knead entire mixture together well and pack into the graham cracker box, which you have lined with wax paper.
Tie well with string or close with freezer tape.
Store at least 1 week in refrigerator before slicing.

title: fluffy rice and chicken
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix mushroom soup and milk; reserve 1/2 cup of the mixture.
Mix remaining soup mixture, rice, mushrooms (with liquid) and half onion soup mix.
Pour into ungreased baking dish, 11 1/2 x 7 1/2-inch.
Place chicken breast on top.
Pour reserved soup mixture over chicken breast.
Sprinkle with remaining onion soup mix.
Cover with foil and bake for 1 hour.
Uncover and bake for 15 minutes longer (4 servings).
My family loves this and it's easy to prepare, too.

title: busy day casserole
directions: Place
ground chuck in baking dish.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Sprinkle
cup
finely chopped onion on top of meat. Place
layers
of
thinly
sliced potatoes on top of onions. Sprinkle
salt
over potatoes.
On top of this, place grated cheese, pork and beans and tomato soup, in order given. Cover tightly
with
foil.
Bake	at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
A meal in a dish.

title: chicken chalupa
directions: Grate Jack and Cheddar cheese together.
Combine soup, chilies, grated onion, 1/2 of green onion tops, sour cream, olives and 2/3 of grated cheese.
Set aside 1 1/2 cups of this mixture.
Add chicken to remaining mixture.
Place 3 heaping tablespoons of chicken mix on each tortilla.
Roll up and place in shallow pan. Spread remaining mixture (1 1/2 cups) on top.
Sprinkle the 1/3 cheese and onion tops and paprika over top.
Refrigerate overnight. Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
Makes 12 servings.

title: easy meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients well and bake in 400° oven until well done, 45 minutes to an hour.

title: chicken a la king
directions: Melt butter in saucepan and saute green peppers, mushrooms and pimentos.
Simmer 5 minutes and add flour and blend well.
Add 3/4 of the heavy cream and all of the chicken broth.
Cover and cook at a simmer until thickened, stirring constantly.
Add sherry, salt, cayenne and paprika.
Beat egg yolks and combine rest of the cream.
Stir slowly into sauce at low heat.
Add chicken and heat to a simmer.
Serve over toasts or puff pastry shells.

title: blackberry jam
directions: Crush blackberries thoroughly.
Add water and fruit pectin. Stir until pectin is dissolved.
Heat to boiling.
Boil 5-10 minutes.
Add sugar.
Stir until dissolved.
Boil 3-5 minutes, stirring frequently until thick.
Pour into sterile hot jars and seal.

title: vegetarian chili
directions: Cook onion and green pepper in hot oil.
Add tomatoes and seasonings.
Simmer, uncovered for 2 hours, adding water if necessary and stirring occasionally.
Remove bay leaf and cloves and discard.
Add beans and heat thoroughly.
Add water as needed.

title: chicken goo(no. 1)
directions: Wrap rinsed chicken with dried beef, then wrap again with bacon.
Mix sour cream and cream of mushroom soup together.
Add a dash of milk to mix well.
Pour over chicken.
Bake at 375° for 50 minutes, covered, then 10 more minutes uncovered.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: biscuit dumplings
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt together.
Cut in shortening.
Add milk, using more if necessary to make soft dough. Roll about 1/4-inch thick and cut into 1-inch squares, strips or diamonds.
Drop into hard boiling chicken stock.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes.
Cook chicken until tender.
Take meat off bone and add to dumplings while cooking.
Serves 6.

title: peanut butter bonbons
directions: In a large bowl, combine vanilla frosting, peanut butter and margarine with fork until well blended.
Stir in crumbs until well mixed.
Form into 1-inch balls; chill 1 hour.
In same saucepan, melt remaining frosting over low heat, stirring occasionally.
Dip chilled balls in melted frosting; allow excess to drip off.
Place on cooling rack over waxed paper; let stand at room temperature until dry, about 6 hours.
Makes 48 to 52 bonbons.

title: spiced tea
directions: Combine cloves, cinnamon and water.
Boil 10 minutes; remove from heat and add remaining ingredients.
May be served hot or cold.

title: mihshi waraq inab(grape leaves stuffed)
directions: Rinse rice in cold water and drain.
Add all ingredients but lemon juice and leaves.
Mix well.
Rinse leaves with hot water. Drain.
Place
a heaping teaspoonful on edge of the dull side of the leaf.
Begin rolling as with jellyroll.
After first roll, fold in ends and continue rolling.
Place a few leaves in bottom of 2 1/2-quart pan to prevent sticking.
Arrange rolls in compact rows and barely cover with water.
Sprinkle a tablespoonful of salt on top of the rolls and place a pottery plate over them so the rolls will remain firm and intact.
Cover pan and cook on a medium heat.
Add lemon juice; lower heat and simmer for an additional 30 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: mom's fruit salad
directions: Make dressing from last four ingredients; mix together and cook until thick.
Let cool.
Mix together with pineapple, bananas and marshmallows.

title: pastry wrapped frankies
directions: Combine flour and salt.
Cut shortening into flour mixture with a pastry blender until crumbs are about the size of small peas.
Add grated cheese.
Add water to mix, a small amount at a time, mixing quickly and evenly, until dough just holds in a ball. Roll pastry into a 6 x 12-inch rectangle.
Cut strips 1/2-inch wide and 6-inches long.
Wrap pastry spiral fashion around frankfurters, sealing ends.
Place on cookie sheet and bake in a hot oven at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes about 24 Frankies.

title: lime jello salad
directions: Soften cream cheese, mix with gelatin granules.
Add 1 cup boiling water and mix until smooth and creamy.
Add pineapple, ice cream and nuts.
Mix all together.
Set in fridge until firm.

title: lemon squares
directions: Combine melted oleo, flour and confectioners sugar.
Mix good and pat into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spray the pan with Pam before adding the mixture.
Bake about 20 minutes at 350°.

title: mrs. guy foster's chocolate icing
directions: Mix together in saucepan.
Let come to a boil for 4 to 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and cool in a pan of ice water and beat until right consistency to spread.
Put butter in in the beginning.

title: chocolate fudge candy
directions: Mix sugar, milk, butter and cocoa.
Heat until butter melts. Cook 3 minutes and take off stove.
Add peanut butter and vanilla. Pour in buttered dish.
If the mix is too thin, add more peanut butter to thicken.
Do not undercook.

title: pie crust
directions: Whip egg yolks, vinegar and ice water together before using.

title: dry baby lima beans
directions: Rinse
beans.
Cover beans with water by 1 inch and put in refrigerator.
Soak overnight.
Next day, bring to a boil; add water if needed.
Add salt, red pepper, onion and seasoning grease
or	ham hock.
Stir.
Return to boil; lower heat, cover and simmer for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: lobster thermidor
directions: Boil lobsters and remove meat.
Scald milk.
Melt butter in skillet and cook lobster meat 5 minutes.
Add flour, then milk and stir until blended.
Combine egg yolks with cream and bread crumbs. Add to lobster mixture and cook until thickened.
Add lemon juice, sherry and seasonings.
Fill lobster shells and place in baking pan.
If no shells, use shallow casserole.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese on top and cook under broiler until bubbly and hot.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: savannah pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs.
Beat in sugar, salt, corn syrup and butter.
Add pecans.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake in a 350° oven for 50 minutes or until knife inserted halfway between center and edge comes out clean.
Cool.
Makes 8 servings.

title: chewy chocolate cookies
directions: Mix in large bowl: sugar, margarine and cocoa.
Add 1 egg at a time, until well blended.
Add vanilla.
Mix dry ingredients in (not powdered sugar).
Cover and chill for 2 hours or overnight. Drop by teaspoonfuls into powdered sugar.
Shape into balls. Place on greased cookie sheet.
Flatten slightly.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 14 minutes.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: lemon angel food cake dessert
directions: Buy or bake an angel food cake.
Slice in half horizontally, about 1/3 from top. Pinch out tunnel in the bottom portion.
Mix sweetened condensed milk and lemon juice.
Let set for 30 minutes in refrigerator.
Whip cream until stiff.
Mix whipped cream (or topping) with lemon mixture.
Put some of this into tunnel in cake.
Replace top portion and frost with remaining mixture. Chill until ready to serve.

title: corn flake bars
directions: Combine sugar and syrup; bring to boil, stir in butter and peanut butter.
When melted, pour over corn flakes.
Press mixture in a buttered pan and cut into bars.

title: a non-toxic play dough
directions: In a medium saucepan, mix flour, salt and cream of tartar. In a small bowl, mix oil and water; add to dry ingredients and mix.
Over low heat, cook until dough isn't sticky and it forms a lump, stirring constantly.
Cool and color with your favorite food colors.

title: italian pound cake
directions: Mix and cream together the sugar, shortening and butter.
Add and mix in the eggs, one at a time.
Add and mix the flour and milk, 1/3 each at a time.
Flavor with the butternut flavoring. Add the nuts and cherries.
Put in a greased and floured tube pan. Put the cake in a cold oven (very important, do not preheat the oven).
Set the temperature at 300° (350° for gas).
Do not open door while baking.
Bake for 1 3/4 to 2 hours, then check with a toothpick.

title: jubilee jumbles cookies
directions: Roll nuts and dates in flour before adding.
Mix all ingredients together.
Drop by rounded teaspoon on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° to 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.	While warm, frost with butter glaze and top each cookie with a walnut half or a red maraschino cherry.

title: chicken soup
directions: Boil chicken breasts for 5 minutes.
Rinse and drain chicken breasts. Cover with water and cook for 1/2 hour.
Debone and chop chicken meat.
Add onion, carrots, seasoning, broth and celery. Cover and cook 1/2 hour.
Add macaroni. May need to add water. Cook 20 to 30 minutes.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Sift first 5 ingredients and set aside.
Cream oleo and sugars; add egg and vanilla; mix well.
Alternate flour mixture and pumpkin, mixing well.
Drop 1/4 cup dough on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Cool and frost with cream cheese frosting (in a can).

title: beet pickles
directions: Cook beets, whole, with about 1/2 inch of top on beet, until tender and peel.
Combine all ingredients except beets.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Pack beets into hot jars, leaving 1/2-inch head space. Pour boiling liquid over beets.
Seal and process about 10 minutes in boiling water bath.
You can use larger beets and slice. Canned beets, drained, can also be used.

title: 7 layers of splendor
directions: Layer all ingredients in the following order:
beans, sour cream, guacamole, diced black olives, diced green onions and chives, diced tomatoes and shredded Cheddar.
Serve with restaurant-style chips and salsa.

title: banana slush
directions: In saucepan mix sugar and water.
Bring to a boil.
In large non-metal container combine bananas, juices and sugar; mix well. Freeze 2 hours.
Before serving, remove from freezer and let stand at room temperature.
Just before serving, stir in Sprite.

title: hopping john
directions: Fry hamburger and onion together.
Add remaining ingredients. Cook until all ingredients are hot.

title: scalloped chicken
directions: Place chicken in kettle. Add celery and bay leaf. Salt and pepper.
Add water to cover.
Simmer until done.
Remove from bones and add rest of the ingredients.
Pour into baking dish. Cook 45 to 55 minutes at 350°.

title: squash dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake until bubbly at 350°. Delicious!

title: easy coconut pie
directions: Grease 9-inch pie plate.
Place first 6 ingredients in blender and cover.
Blend on low speed 3 minutes.
Pour into pie plate. Let stand 5 minutes.
Sprinkle with coconut.
Bake in 350° oven 35 to 40 minutes or until knife inserted between center and edge comes out clean.
Store in refrigerator.

title: zucchini relish
directions: Mix and cook 30 minutes.
Put in hot jars and seal.

title: monkey bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Shape bread dough into walnut sized balls.
Dip in margarine.
Coat with mixture of the sugar, brown sugar and cinnamon.
Arrange in greased tube pan.
(Do not use any pan with a seam, like 2 piece angel food cake pan, as the margarine will seep through and burn.) Drizzle with remaining margarine.
Sprinkle with remaining cinnamon-sugar mixture.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes.
Invert onto serving plate.
Best when warm; is easily reheated in microwave.

title: hello dollies
directions: Melt butter.
Put into a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Layer crushed vanilla wafer crumbs, semi-sweet chocolate chips, coconut, pecans and drizzle Eagle Brand milk on top.
(Don't stir anything.)
Bake at about 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Refrigerate overnight and cut into squares.

title: potato soup
directions: Put all into a crock-pot for 10 to 12 hours on low or 3 or 4 hours on high.
If you want to speed up the process, zap the potatoes, carrot and onion in the microwave and then cook for 2 hours.
During the last hour, stir in one 13 ounce can of evaporated milk.
If you want, mash the potatoes before serving. Top with chives.

title: kathy's mini pizzas
directions: Mix all ingredients
together
and
spread on slices of party rye or French bread.
Place
on cookie sheet and bake at 400° until cheese is melted.

title: chocolate fudge sheet cake
directions: Sift together first 3 ingredients.
Add next 3 ingredients. Melt over heat oleo, cocoa and water and bring to boil.
Then pour over other ingredients and mix well.
Pour into greased and floured cookie sheet pan with sides, 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 5/8-inch. Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: broccoli and butter bean casserole
directions: Cook lima beans and broccoli according to directions on packages.
Drain and mix with rest of ingredients.

title: easter duckling a l'orange
directions: Clean duckling.
Rub inside cavity and outside of duckling with mixture of salt and pepper.
Remove wing tips to first joint. Fasten neck skin and wings to back of duckling with skewers. Close the cavity opening with skewers and tie legs together on rack in roasting pan, breast side down.
Roast at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: crunchy pea salad
directions: Combine all ingredients except bacon.
Chill.
Just before serving, place lettuce leaves on serving platter and put salad over lettuce and sprinkle with crumbled bacon.
Serve chilled.

title: no bake cocoa-oatmeal cookies
directions: In heavy 3 quart saucepan put in first 5 ingredients. Cook and stir constantly until mixture comes to a boil. Continue to boil for 6 minutes, stirring constantly. Remove from stove, add oatmeal. Immediately drop by teaspoon on waxed paper.

title: * camping bread *
directions: Mix flour and salt.
Add butter, rubbing in lightly.
Add water and mix well.
Grease frying pan and pour in batter.
Bake very slowly over fire.
Turn on other side to brown.

title: crazy chocolate cake
directions: Make 3 holes in mixture.
Put in 1 teaspoon vanilla, vinegar, 5 tablespoons oil and 1 cup cold water.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Very moist and yummy.

title: shrimp gumbo
directions: Melt the butter in a heavy soup pot; whisk in flour and cook stirring frequently over medium low flame until medium brown.
Add the vegetables and stir.
Add the liquids and bring to a simmer. Add the shrimp and simmer until the vegetables are soft. (45 - 60 minutes)
Check seasonings.
Serve warm over rice.

title: meat and potato quiche
directions: Mix
the
potatoes and oil together in a large pie pan. Press evenly
into
pie
crust shape.
Bake for 15 minutes at 425°
or until beginning to brown.
Layer the meat, cheese and onion
onto the crust.
Beat together the milk, eggs, salt and pepper
in a bowl.
Pour over the other ingredients in the pie pan.
Sprinkle with
parsley
flakes.
Bake for 30 minutes at 425°.

title: green rice casserole
directions: Cook onion in margarine.
Combine all ingredients.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: brattens clam chowder
directions: Place onions, celery and potatoes in saucepan.
Drain juice from clams and pour over vegetables.
Add enough water to barely cover vegetables and simmer, covered, over medium heat, until barely tender.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix cream cheese,
Parmesan cheese and mayonnaise.
Add as much pepperoni as you wish.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Beat eggs with milk, salt and mustard.
Brown sausage and drain excess fat.
Place bread cubes in buttered 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Add sausage and sprinkle with cheese.
Pour egg mixture over bread, sausage and cheese.
Refrigerate ovenight.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: onion spread
directions: Combine salad dressing and cream cheese, mixing well until blended.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Chill.
Serve with crackers.

title: spinach torte
directions: Cook spinach as directed on package and drain.
To prepare the white sauce, melt the butter in a pan with the flour and half of the salt.
Add milk; stir and cook 1 minute.
Remove from heat and let the mixture slightly cool.
Break and add the eggs to the sauce.
Beat with a fork lightly, then add the cheese, onion, Season All, pepper, raisins, spinach and then the remaining salt. Mix thoroughly.

title: cherry cola, chocolate, mayonnaise, sauerkraut cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a 10-inch tube pan. In medium bowl, sift flour, cocoa, baking soda and baking powder. In large bowl, with mixer on high ,beat eggs, sugar and vanilla for 3 minutes.
Reduce speed to low and beat in mayonnaise.
Add flour and cola alternately.
Mix in sauerkraut.
Pour in pan and bake 50 to 55 minutes.
Cool.

title: twice baked potatoes
directions: Bake potatoes at 350° for 1 hour; let cool approximately 15 minutes.
Slice a thin lengthwise strip from top of each potato. Scoop out as much of inside potato without tearing.
In a medium bowl, mix scooped out potato, cheese, milk, egg, butter, salt and pepper.
Beat at medium speed with electric mixer until smooth. Spoon back into each potato shell.
Microwave on High for approximately 5 minutes or until potatoes have thoroughly heated again.

title: strawberry jello salad
directions: Drain pineapple juice in measuring cup.
Add enough water to juice to measure 2 cups.
Dissolve jello in water/juice mixture on stove top.
In serving bowl, add jello, strawberries and pineapple.

title: jello mochi
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Add unchilled soda, eggs and butter. Mix well.
Line pan with waxed paper and bake at 350° for 1 hour. Cool and cut.
Yield: 1 (9 x 13-inch) pan.

title: zucchini pineapple bread
directions: Beat eggs until fluffy.
Add sugar, vanilla, oil, zucchini, flour, baking powder, salt and soda.
Stir in pineapple, raisins and nuts.
Mix well.
Bake in 2 well-greased 9 x 5 x 4-inch loaf pans for 1 hour at 325°.

title: apricot cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into greased and floured stem pan.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.
Pour rest of apricot nectar over cake while hot.

title: soy sauce chicken
directions: Combine all ingredients except chicken and mix well.
Place chicken drummettes in baking pan and pour marinade over chicken. Cover and marinate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes, uncovered.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Combine pudding mixes and milk.
Fold in whipped topping. Layer bottom of pan with graham crackers.
Top with layer of crackers and rest of mixture.
Top with layer of chocolate icing (thin), being top.
Heat the icing in microwave 1/2 minute.
Works better refrigerated overnight.

title: wisconsin cheese soup
directions: Melt butter in 3 qt saucepan.
Add vegetables, saute until tender but not brown.
Add flour; stir.
Add stock; stir until thickened.
Add cheese stirring constantly.
Season with salt and pepper to taste.
Simmer 15 minutes, thin with small amount of milk, if desired.

title: san jose quiche
directions: Brown beef; add chopped onions, garlic and green pepper.
Cook 5 minutes.
Stir in salsa, oregano, cumin, chili powder and salt. Grease casserole dish and put a layer of tortilla chips in dish. Top with meat mixture.
Spread on chile Ortegas, and top with cheese.
Beat eggs with milk and 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Pour over top.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes or until set.
Garnish with olives.

title: pace con queso dip
directions: Combine ingredients in saucepan.
Cook over low heat, stirring frequently, just until sauce is smooth.
Serve with corn chips, tortilla chips or regular dippers.
Makes 2 1/2 cups.

title: baked caramel corn
directions: Mix all ingredients except baking soda and vanilla.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat to medium high.
Keep boiling, stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat and add baking soda and vanilla. Stir thoroughly.
Pour over popcorn.
Bake 1 hour at 250°, stirring every 15 minutes.
Cool and store in a tight container.

title: quick rolls
directions: Blend together butter, sugar and egg. Add 1 cup hot water and cold water. Blend yeast in 1/4 cup warm water and add to mixture. Add flour gradually and knead well or until mixed well.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Combine powdered sugar and peanut butter.
Mix with fork until mixture resembles coarse corn meal.
Spread half of mixture in baked pie shell.
Set remaining mixture aside.
Combine remaining ingredients, except egg whites, in a saucepan.
Cook over medium heat until thick, stirring constantly.
Spoon over peanut butter mixture in pastry shell.
Beat egg whites until stiff peaks form. Spread over cooked filling.
Sprinkle remaining peanut butter mixture over meringue.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes or until firm and brown.

title: creamy banana pudding(servings: 10)
directions: In large mixing bowl, combine milk and water (it sounds awful, but do it anyway). Add pudding mix; beat until well blended.
Chill 5 minutes.
Fold in whipped cream.

Spoon 1 cup pudding mixture into a 2 1/2-quart round glass serving bowl. Top with 1/3 each of the vanilla wafers, bananas and pudding. Repeat layering twice, ending with pudding mixture. Chill thoroughly. Garnish as desired.
(I use a few vanilla wafers and banana slices on top.) Refrigerate leftovers.

title: polish pierogi
directions: Mound flour on a bread board and make a well in the center. Drop eggs and salt into well.
Add water; working from the center to outside of flour mound, mix flour into liquid in center with one hand and keep flour mounded with other hand.
Knead until dough is firm and well mixed.
Cover dough with a warm bowl; let rest 10 minutes.
Divide dough into halves.
On floured surface, using half of dough at a time, roll dough as thin as possible.
Cut out 3-inch rounds with large biscuit cutter.
Place a small spoonful of filling a little to one side on each round of dough.
Moisten edge with water, fold over and press edges together firmly.
Be sure they are well sealed to prevent the filling from leaking out.
Drop pierogi into boiling salted water.
Cook gently 3 to 5 minutes, or until pierogi float.
Lift out of water with perforated spoon. Yields 1 1/2 to 2 dozen.

title: congealed cherry salad
directions: Drain liquid from cherries, add enough water to make 2 cups of liquid; heat and pour over gelatin.
Stir and add cream cheese to hot mixture.
Add mayonnaise and put in blender.
Cool.
Add pineapple and pineapple juice, pitted cherries, coke and nuts. Stir to mix.
Spray mold with Pam Cooking Spray.
Pour mixture into mold.
Refrigerate to gel.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, sour cream, vanilla, milk, flour, baking powder, baking soda, chips and nuts.
Mix well. Grease a Bundt or angel food cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Sprinkle top with 10x sugar when lukewarm.

title: grilled roast beef sandwiches
directions: Combine chilies, mayonnaise and mustard; spread about 1 tablespoon on one side of each slice of bread. Top half of the bread with 1 slice of cheese and 2 slices of beef. Cover with remaining bread. Butter the outside of bread. Grill sandwiches on a griddle or in a large skillet over medium heat until both sides are golden brown and the cheese is melted. Serve with salsa or picante sauce, if desired. Yield: 5 servings.

title: curried waldorf salad
directions: Combine turkey, apple and celery in a large bowl.
In a separate bowl, blend together mayonnaise, curry powder and Equal. Toss turkey mixture with dressing.
Chill and serve on lettuce leaves.

title: ham rolls
directions: Mix butter, mustard, poppy seed, Worcestershire sauce and onion. Split package of rolls horizontally through the center. Spread butter mixture on both sides of rolls.
Layer bottom half with ham. Sprinkle cheese on top of ham.
Replace tops.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes.
These freeze well. Cut into individual rolls before freezing so a few may be used at a time.

title: waldorf salad
directions: Combine mayonnaise or salad dressing and honey; set aside. Combine apple, celery, nuts and raisins.
Toss with mayonnaise or salad dressing and honey.
If desired, mound salad in lettuce cups and garnish with maraschino cherries.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: apple kuchen(12 servings)
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cut butter into dry cake mix until crumbly.
Mix in coconut.
Pat mixture lightly in ungreased baking pan (13 x 9 x 2-inch), building up edges slightly.
Bake for 10 minutes.
Arrange apple slices on warm crust.
Mix sugar and drizzle over apples.
(Topping will not completely cover apples.) Bake 25 minutes or until edges are light brown.
Do not overbake. Serve warm or cold.

title: beenie chili
directions: Brown hamburger meat and drain the grease off.
Then add the rest of the ingredients.
Simmer for 30 minutes.
(Kids love it.) Can be served with crackers or corn bread muffins.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs until fluffy; add sugar, vanilla, oil and zucchini that's grated.
Blend good.
Add all dry ingredients alternating with pineapple, nuts and coconut.
One or 1 1/2 cups of raisins may be added but if so, add an extra 1/2 teaspoon soda and extra 1/2 teaspoon baking powder.
Grease and flour pans.
Makes 4 loaves. Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours or until done.
Test with toothpick for being done.

title: broccoli cheese chicken
directions: In skillet over medium heat, in hot margarine, cook chicken 10 minutes or until brown on both sides, spoon off fat.
Stir in soup, water, and pepper.
Heat to boiling, add broccoli.
Reduce heat to low, cover, simmer 10 minutes or until chicken is fork tender and broccoli is done.

title: italian macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions.
Rinse and drain.
Combine with cheese, salami, pepperoni, onions, olives, celery and peppers in serving bowl.
Add Italian salad dressing to salad; mix well.
Chill for 24 hours.
Add tomatoes and parsley at serving time.
Yields 15 servings.

title: raw apple cake
directions: Pour sugar over apples and let stand in a bowl.
In larger bowl, mix flour, soda, cinnamon and salt.
Add the nuts and raisins.
Mix the eggs and oil together and pour into flour mixture (will be very stiff).
Pour in tube pan and bake in 350° oven for 1 1/2 hours.

title: holden's hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix together. Use 2 tablespoons to a mug with hot water.

title: all-purpose low salt seasoning mix
directions: Combine all ingredients in a small jar with a tight fitting lid.
Shake to mix well.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix in order and beat after each addition.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs and butter.
Press into bottom of pan.
Beat powdered sugar, eggs and margarine about 12 minutes and pour over crust.
Slice bananas.
Lay over mixture.
Spread Cool Whip and pineapple.
Sprinkle nuts over the pineapple.
Place cherry halves on top.
Chill and serve.

title: knockwurst in beer
directions: Simmer the knockwurst in beer very slowly, 15 minutes.
Remove the knockwurst to a heated shallow baking dish.
Reduce the beer to 1/3 cup by rapid boiling and stir in the vinegar and sugar. Pour over the knockwurst and broil briefly, turning to brown on all sides.
Makes 8 servings.

title: rice krispies bars
directions: Heat and blend sugar, peanut butter and Karo syrup.
Mix well with Rice Krispies.
Pour into large pan.

title: little pizzas
directions: Combine all ingredients. Spread over muffins. Broil until bubbly and slightly brown.
Cut in bite size pieces.
Place in center of oven when broiling.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix together pretzels and oleo.
Press in 9 x 13-inch cake dish.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 350°.
Cool.
Beat together cream cheese and sugar.
Fold in 2 cups whipped topping.
Spread on crust.
Chill.
Dissolve the gelatin in 2 cups boiling water. Stir in strawberries.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Pour over cheese filling.
Chill 2 hours.

title: gazpacho
directions: Finely chop all vegetables.
Combine all ingredients in a stainless steel or glass bowl.
Cover.
Chill at least 4 hours. Serve in chilled bowls.
Serves 6.

title: apple crisp
directions: Place apples in a baking dish.
Combine all other ingredients; mix well.
Sprinkle mixture over the top of the layer of apples. Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Can be served warm or cold.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Brown beef and add onions and bell pepper until limp, but not brown.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bring to a full boil.
Reduce heat and simmer for 2 to 3 hours, stirring occasionally.

title: kit kat bars
directions: Melt butter or margarine; add milk and mix together.
Add sugars and crushed graham crackers.
Boil for 5 minutes.
Line a 9 x 13-inch pan with Club crackers.
You will be using 2 packages. Fit tightly in pan.
Pour about 1/3 of the cooked mixture over the crackers.
Alternate crackers and cooked mixture, ending with crackers.
Melt chips with peanut butter.
Spread over crackers, refrigerate, then cut into strips or squares.

title: baked stuffed peppers
directions: Cut a slice off the tops of the peppers.
Remove the white pith and the seeds.
Parboil the peppers for 3 minutes in boiling water; remove and drain.
Heat the oil in a frying pan.
Add the onion, garlic and grated courgettes (zucchini) and fry for 5 minutes.
Add the mushrooms, then stir in the parsley, breadcrumbs, cheese, egg and salt and pepper to taste.
Combine the ingredients thoroughly.

title: cheesecake squares
directions: Cream butter with packed brown sugar; add flour and chopped walnuts.
Mix until crumbly.
Reserve 2 cups for topping.
Press remaining mixture into bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes, until lightly browned.
Blend 1/2 cup sugar and cream cheese until smooth.
Add eggs, milk, lemon juice and vanilla.
Beat well.
Spread on baked crust.
Sprinkle with reserved topping.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cool.
Cut into 2 inch squares.

title: helen sue sanderson's pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into 9-inch deep-dish pie shell.
Cook at 350° for 10 minutes.
Turn down to 325° and cook 40 to 45 minutes longer, until almost set.

title: pumpkin cranberry bread(makes 2 loaves)
directions: In large bowl combine flour, pumpkin pie spice, baking soda and salt.
In small mixer bowl, beat eggs.
Beat in sugar, oil and pumpkin.
Pour pumpkin mixture into dry ingredients.
Stir just until moistened.
Stir in cranberries.
Spoon batter into 2 greased and floured 8 x 4-inch loaf pans.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 60 minutes or until wooden pick comes out clean.
Cool for 5 to 10 minutes.
Remove from pan.

title: cheese ball 2
directions: Let all ingredients soften at room temperature.
Mix all except pecans together.
Shape into ball and roll in pecans. Serves 10 to 12.

title: zimbabwe greens
directions: Wash greens; remove stems and cut or tear into bite-sized pieces.
Put olive oil in a large hot skillet and add greens.
DO NOT ADD WATER.
Greens will turn bright green, get softer and create their own liquid as they cook.
Add seasoned salt and red pepper to taste and toss in the skillet.
Add chopped banana peppers (hot or mild to your taste) and toss.
Add the tomato last and toss only once.
The entire cooking process takes only about 10 minutes.
This recipe by Fannie Cox was adapted from a
recipe her aunt brought from Zimbabwe.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Cream together the sugar, shortening, raisins and applesauce. Sift flour, spices and baking soda together.
Add the dry ingredients to the creamed mixture.
Bake at 350° in a greased and floured tube pan for approximately 1 hour.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook noodles or rice in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Combine soups, sour cream, chicken broth, onion, mushrooms and seasoning. Arrange chicken on top.
Bake, uncovered, in a 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: boston cream candy
directions: Boil sugar, syrup and cream until it forms soft ball in cold water.
Beat mixture until stiff, then add the pecans.
Pour into plate.
When cool, cut in squares.

title: leaf lettuce dressing
directions: Boil all together about 2 minutes; cool.

title: apple dip
directions: Mix together.
Chill and serve with Granny Smith apples.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Beat all ingredients together and pour into 4 well greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake 1 hour at 350 F.

title: onion pie
directions: Melt 1 stick margarine in pie pan.
Add cracker crumbs; mix together.
Put in pie pan or casserole to form a base.
Put cooked onions on top of the crumbs (cracker).
Mix up the scalded milk, grated cheese, eggs, salt and pepper.
Pour this over the onions and cracker crumbs.
Bake at 325° for 40 minutes.
Good with barbecue chicken or steaks.

title: seafood stir-fry
directions: Heat oil in skillet.
Add Crab Delights and vegetables.
Stir over medium-high heat for 2 minutes.
Add seasoning.
Cook 1 minute.
Garnish with chow mein noodles.
Serve immediately.

title: salt pickles
directions: Mix water, vinegar and salt; bring to a boil.
Place 8 to 10 green grapes in the bottom of each quart jar.
Put cucumbers in and pour water, vinegar and salt mixture over them.
Seal.
Process in boiling water bath for 5 minutes.

title: coconut macaroons
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Mix coconut, sugar, flour and salt in large bowl.
Stir in egg whites and almond extract until well blended.
Drop from teaspoon onto lightly greased baking sheet. Bake for 20 to 25 minutes or until edges of cookies are golden brown.
Remove from baking sheet immediately.

title: bill shields' sauerkraut salad
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients in a suitable container for storage. Bring to boil the remaining ingredients.
Turn down and simmer for 2 to 3 minutes.
Pour over vegetables.
Mix and cool.
Will keep for several weeks.

title: rigatoni fra diavolo
directions: While rigatoni is cooking, fry pepperoni until the edges curl; add peppers and onion until tender.
Toss with cooked pasta.
Add remaining ingredients.
Add sauce to your liking.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Serves 2 to 3.

title: spaghetti with meaty mushroom sauce
directions: Place the TVP in small heatproof mixing bowl and pour the boiling water over it.
Mix well and set aside.
Fill a 4 1/2-quart saucepan 2/3 full of water.
Bring to a rolling boil.
Cook the pasta in it until it is al dent.
Drain the pasta well and return it to the saucepan.
Cover the saucepan with a lid and set it aside.

title: old fashion honey wheat bread
directions: Mix cottage cheese and butter or margarine with water and honey.
Heat in medium saucepan until very warm (130°).
Lightly spoon flour into measuring cup and level off.
Combine warm liquids, 2 cups flour and remaining ingredients in large bowl; beat 2 minutes at medium speed.
By hand, stir in remaining flour to make a stiff dough.
Knead dough on well floured surface for 2 minutes, or until smooth and elastic.
Place in greased bowl. Cover; let rise in warm place until light and double in size (approximately 1 hour).
Grease (not oil) two 9 x 5-inch loaf pans.

title: sour milk cake
directions: Mix all together with mixer for 2 minutes.
Grease one 8-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: buttermilk salad
directions: Remove from heat and blend in:

title: pecan crunch
directions: Line a cookie sheet with foil.
Place graham crackers on foil. Sprinkle pecans and Brickle bits over crackers.
Bring butter and sugar to boiling point in a heavy pan.
Boil 2 1/2 minutes.
Pour over crackers and pecan and Brickle bits.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes.
Let cool and break into pieces.
If the weather isn't too hot, sprinkle chocolate chips over hot cookies and spread.
Chill.

title: dishpan pound cake
directions: Beat mixture well.
Pour in a large round pan and bake 1 1/2 hours or until done.

title: hawaiian pie
directions: Mix pineapple, sugar and cornstarch.
Heat and bring to a boil until thickened.
Remove from heat; stir in Jell-O.
Add nuts, cherries and bananas.
Pour into large graham cracker crust.
Chill and serve with whipped topping.

title: smothered potatoes
directions: Slice potatoes and onion.
Put oil in frying pan.
Heat until hot.
Cook until crisp, turning occasionally.
Season with salt, seasoned salt and pepper.

title: devil's food cake
directions: Mix ingredients in order given.
Pour into a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes (test with toothpick).
Top with Chocolate Peanut Butter Sauce (recipe in this cookbook).

title: oyster stew
directions: In a heavy saucepan, heat butter until sizzling. Add oysters with liquid, Worcestershire sauce, celery salt, salt, pepper and paprika. Heat until edges of oysters curl slightly.
Add milk. Heat quickly, but do not boil. Serve in bowls, topped with paprika. Pass oysters crackers, if desired.
Yields 4 servings.

title: gingerbread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease an 8-inch square cake pan.
In a bowl, sift together flour, soda, black pepper, nutmeg, cloves, cinnamon and ginger.
Melt butter over low heat; stir in molasses, brown sugar, water and coffee.
Remove from heat and let cool. Slowly beat in eggs, flour and spices.
Pour batter into pan.
Bake 45 minutes.
Let cool, then cut into squares.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar, if you like.

title: meatball special
directions: Combine meat, bread crumbs, egg, 1/4 cup tomato sauce, salt, pepper and chopped onion.
Mix well.
Form meatballs.
Heat oil in large skillet.
Add meatballs and brown.
Add 3 cups water and remaining tomato sauce, onion soup mix, carrots, potatoes and peas.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 1 hour.

title: coffee cake dough
directions: Scald milk; add margarine, sugar and salt.
Cool it.
Put water in warm bowl with yeast; stir.
Put in milk; mix with egg and 1/2 flour.
Beat; add rest of flour and mix well with a spoon. Cover with aluminum foil and refrigerate at least 2 hours before forming into cakes.
Can stay in refrigerator for 3 days before forming into cake.
Put in cake pan and put melted margarine over it.
Then sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar, then put on sliced peaches.
Bake at 375° for 25 or 30 minutes.

title: barbecued short ribs
directions: Trim excess fat from ribs.
Place ribs and salt in 4 quart saucepan or Dutch oven.
Cover with water.
Bring to boil.
Cover. Simmer 1 1/2 to 2 hours until tender.
Meanwhile, saute onion in oil under tender.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer 15 minutes. Drain ribs.
Place on rack in broiler oven or over ash covered coals so meat is 6 to 7 inches from heat.
Broil 10 minutes, turning occasionally.
Baste ribs with sauce, continue broiling about 10 minutes, turning and basting frequently with sauce.
Serve with remaining sauce if desired.

title: canadian stew
directions: Fry meat.
When almost done, put in the onions and scallions until the meat is done.
Add the red pepper, potatoes, Everglade seasoning, salt, pepper and rutabaga.
Bring to a boil, then add the butter.
Cook until done and spice to suit yourself.

title: hamburger skillet dinner
directions: Put first 3 ingredients into skillet and fry until lightly browned.
Add soy sauce, pepper and water.
Add the veggies in layers (not stirred).
Cover and cook over high heat for 1 minute. Reduce heat and cook slowly for 15 minutes more.
Serves 6.

title: scallop casserole (bay)(serves 3)
directions: Melt stick of butter in a 3-quart casserole dish.
Add Ritz crackers, scallops and garlic powder to taste.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: sliced baked potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes.
Cut potatoes into thin slices but not all the way through.
(Use a handle of a spoon to prevent knife from cutting all the way.)
Put potatoes in a baking dish.
Sprinkle with salt and drizzle with butter; then sprinkle with herbs.
Bake potatoes at 425° for 50 minutes.
Remove from oven; sprinkle with cheese.
Bake potatoes for 10 more minutes until lightly browned. Check with a fork.
Makes 4 servings.

title: no cook banana pudding
directions: Put milk in large mixing bowl.
Add pudding mix and mix on low until starts to thicken.
Add sour cream.
Mix well.
Fold whipped topping into this mixture until well blended.
Place layer of vanilla wafers and bananas in 13 x 9-inch dish.
Cover with 1/2 of pudding mixture.
Repeat with another layer.
Refrigerate.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: magic crystal garden
directions: You will need a large bowl, spoon and glass container.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Crumble ground beef; brown until dry but not crisp.
Drain. Add chopped onion; cook until transparent.
Add egg, Worcestershire sauce, hot sauce and Lipton Secret Recipe; mix all together well.
Press meat mixture into 9-inch deep pie pan. Cover with mashed potatoes (like a meringue).
Sprinkle with paprika, then with Parmesan.
Bake until lightly browned and hot through.

title: strawberry jello salad(diabetic)
directions: Mix 2 cups boiling water with jello; stir until dissolved. Add 1 cup cold water.
Pour over pineapple, juice and strawberries.
Stir, then add walnuts.
Place in refrigerator. May serve with Cool Whip.

title: humdingers
directions: Mix first 5
ingredients and cook over low heat for 8 minutes.
Add vanilla and Rice Krispies.
Cool, then roll finger-size cookies and roll in powdered sugar.

title: blintz casserole
directions: First make the dough:
Melt 1 stick (1/4 pound) margarine in a 2-quart casserole.
Allow melted margarine to coat pan and pour balance into remaining dough ingredients in mixing bowl:
2 eggs, baking powder, milk, 1/2 cup sugar, flour, vanilla and salt; mix all together and set aside.

title: beefburgers deluxe
directions: Combine ingredients and shape into 6 patties.
Broil under moderate heat for about 7 minutes on each side (or fry).
Makes 6 servings.

title: lemon bread
directions: Mix butter,
sugar, lemon extract and lemon rind.
Beat in eggs and
milk.
Add
dry
ingredients
and
nuts.	Bake in 10-inch
Dutch oven that is greased with butter for 70 minutes at medium
heat.
Remove from pan immediately.
Combine juice of lemon and 1/2 cup powdered sugar.
Pour over loaf.

title: oriental coleslaw
directions: Crush the dry noodles and combine with coleslaw mix, sunflower seeds, and onions in large bowl.
Toss with Oriental dressing. Sprinkle with toasted almonds.
Cover and refrigerate overnight to blend flavors.

title: caramel corn
directions: Put popcorn in larger roaster pan (I spray with non-stick spray).
In saucepan, put brown sugar, margarine, Karo, salt and cream of tartar.
Cook over medium to medium high heat, stirring constantly until hard ball stage (260° to 264°).
Remove from stove; add soda and stir.
Pour over popcorn and stir until covered.
Put into 200° oven for 1 hour.
Stir twice during this time.
Dump on wax paper and separate to cool.
Makes about 2 gallons.

title: pecan fruit cake
directions: Mix all ingredients well with your hands.
Bake 3 hours at 250° in a tube cake pan.
Line bottom of pan with waxed paper to help keep from sticking.

title: icebox fruit cake
directions: Line bottom of tube pan with wax paper. Grind everything, except pineapple and cherries.
Cut pineapple into chunks and leave cherries whole.
Melt marshmallows in warm milk over low heat.
Fold in ground goodies and put in pineapple and cherries last.
Pack firm in cake pan and refrigerate overnight.
Remove from cake pan.
Remove wax paper from cake and rewrap in plastic wrap. Store in refrigerator until gone.

title: plantation supper
directions: Brown hamburger, onion, salt and pepper.
Cook until done. Add soup, milk, cream cheese and corn.
Cook noodles; drain.
Add to hamburger mixture.
Cook for about 45 minutes.

title: beer meatballs
directions: Mix all ingredients except beer, chili sauce and brown sugar. Make 50 medium-sized meatballs.
Place meatballs on cookie sheet and place in oven to brown for 30 minutes at 325°.
While meatballs are in oven, combine chili sauce, beer and brown sugar in large saucepan.
Bring to boil and then simmer for 15 minutes. Add meatballs and simmer an additional 30 minutes.
Serve with toothpicks.

title: raspberry custard brulee
directions: Divide raspberries evenly among 4 (6 ounce) ovenproof ramekins or custard cups.
Set aside.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Form into loaf.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until center is done.

title: red and green cabbage slaw
directions: In large bowl, combine vegetable oil, orange juice, soy sauce, sesame oil, vinegar, ginger, garlic and pepper.
Using fork, beat well to blend; set aside.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix ingredients, except cheese, together.
Put in greased casserole.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 45 minutes.
