title: cole slaw
directions: In a saucepan combine ingredients.
Bring to a rolling boil; keep stirring.
Pour over slaw.
Do not toss.
Cover and refrigerate for at least 4 hours.
Toss before serving and sprinkle with celery seed.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Sift flour; measure.
Add baking powder, salt and soda.
Cream shortening; add sugar gradually.
Beat until fluffy.
Add eggs and mix until smooth.
Add cinnamon and blend.
Add dry ingredients alternately with mashed bananas, stirring enough to combine thoroughly.
Add nuts.
Turn in greased loaf pan and bake 55 minutes at 350°.

title: cranberry souffle salad
directions: In
a saucepan, combine 1 1/4 cups of the orange juice, cranberry
sauce
and gelatin.
Cook and stir over medium heat until
gelatin
dissolves.	Stir
in
remaining
orange juice. Transfer
to
medium
mixing
bowl.
Apply a seal; chill until partially
set
(consistency
of an unbeaten egg white).
In a small
mixing
bowl,
beat	whipping cream to soft peaks; fold into
gelatin mixture.
Apply seal;
refrigerate until mixture mounds.
Pour
into the gel-ring mold.
Apply seal; chill 4 to 6 hours or until set.
To unmold salad, immerse mold into warm water for 20 to 30 seconds; do not melt gelatin.	Remove large seal; center
an inverted serving plate over mold.
Carefully lift
off inner
salad
with	orange	wedges and garnish with orange leaves,
if desired.
Garnish outer edge of salad with additional whipped cream and cranberries, if desired.	Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: texas 22 minute holiday fudge cake
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease and flour a 13 x 15-inch loaf. In a large mixing bowl, mix flour and sugar.
In a 3-quart saucepan, mix the next 4 ingredients.
Heat slowly, stirring constantly, until oleo and Crisco melt.
Pour over flour and sugar in bowl.
Mix on high speed.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Mix thoroughly and pour into greased pan.

title: pork chop potato bake
directions: Brown chops in skillet.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
In same skillet, combine soup, milk and sour cream.
Stir in potatoes, 1/2 cup cheese and 1/2 of onions.
Spoon mixture into 9 x 13-inch dish and arrange chops over top of potatoes.
Bake, covered, for 40 to 50 minutes at 350°.
Top with remaining cheese and onions and bake, uncovered, 10 minutes more.

title: pea salad
directions: Mix vegetables and sour cream together.
Mix dressing and mustard.
Pour over peas.
Cover with grated cheese.

title: sour cream cabbage slaw
directions: In a small bowl, gently blend sour cream, vinegar and seasonings.
Cover and chill.
When ready to serve, toss cabbage and green pepper lightly with dressing.

title: hot dog chili
directions: Brown ground beef and drain. Add chili powder, onion, tomato soup, hot sauce and ketchup. Bring to a boil. Simmer over low heat for 1 hour.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Drain macaroni and rinse starch off.
Toss with other ingredients.
Chill.

title: pickle roll-up
directions: Blend together and spread on bread.
Trim crust before spreading. Wrap around whole pickle.
Refrigerate overnight. Slice thin for serving.

title: cheese straws
directions: Cream together the margarine and cheese.
Mix in dry ingredients.
Roll the dough out flat on a cookie sheet and "stripe it" using a fork tip.
Cut into 2-inch long pieces.
Bake at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: apricot bread
directions: Soak apricots in warm water.
Cream sugar and shortening; add egg, 1/4 cup water and orange juice.
Mix dry ingredients together.
Add nuts and drained apricots.
Pour into greased loaf pan and bake at 350° for 55 minutes.

title: lo-fat and calorie slow-cooker sauerkraut and pork chops
directions: Broil chops until rare.
Combine first 7 ingredients together. Mix well.
Alternate mixture and chops, starting with cabbage-kraut mixture,
then a layer of chops; layer twice.
Bake at high heat 3 to 4 hours; low heat 6 to 8 hours.

title: oatmeal chocolate chip cake
directions: Pour boiling water over oatmeal.
Let stand at room temperature 10 minutes.
Add brown and white sugars and margarine.
Stir until margarine melts.
Add eggs.
Mix well.
Sift together flour, soda, salt and cocoa.
Add flour to sugar mixture.
Mix well.
Add about half of the package of chocolate bits.
Pour batter into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle walnuts and remaining chocolate bits on top.
Bake in preheated 350° oven about 40 minutes or until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.

title: zesty pretzel snack
directions: Mix vegetable oil, lemon pepper and powdered ranch dressing. Pour over pretzels and soak 24 hours, shaking often.

title: grandma's cheesy hash browns
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients and stir well.
Spoon into greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Top with crushed cornflakes, if desired.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: individual cheese cakes
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Line muffin tins.
Place wafers in bottom of tins.
Fill 3/4 full. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes (no longer.)
Cool.
Top with pie filling.
Makes 18 to 20.

title: fruit salad
directions: Combine juice from pineapple and 2 beaten eggs, 7 Tbsp. sugar, 2 Tbsp. flour and 1 Tbsp. butter.
Mix and cook until thick.
Cool and pour over fruit, then chill.

title: garden vegetable salad
directions: Mix together and store at least 1 to 2 hours before serving. Will keep in refrigerator at least 2 weeks.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Put water in large pot.
Add celery, carrots, onion and salt. Boil until vegetables are half done.
Add potatoes, tomatoes and parsley.
Continue boiling until vegetables are done.
In small pan, brown butter with flour; add paprika for color.
Add to soup and let it come to a boil.

title: savory rye snacks
directions: In bowl, combine the first 7 ingredients.
Spread on bread slices and place on ungreased baking sheets.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes or until bubbly.
Yield:
4 dozen.

title: super bowl party chili
directions: In a large kettle, heat the oil.
Saute the onions, garlic and green peppers until tender.
Add the brown beef and cook until browned, breaking up the chunks with a fork.
Add the remaining ingredients except the beans; stir well and cover.
Let simmer for one hour.
Add the beans and simmer for 30 minutes.
Remove the green pepper rings before serving.
Add beef stock if too thick. Serves about 20 people.

title: country fried venison
directions: Wash steak; drain.
Salt and pepper to taste and let stand for 15 minutes.
Dip in milk, then dredge with flour.
Heat cooking oil until hot.
Place steak in pan and fry until done and brown. Drain oil, leaving a small amount in pan.
Mix 1 cup water and 1 cup milk.
Pour over steak and cook until thickened.

title: barbecued chicken(president nixon's favorite)
directions: Sprinkle chickens with salt and pepper.
Place chickens in a shallow pan or Ziploc bag.
Pour marinade over the chickens and marinate 3 to 4 hours, turning occasionally.
Grill until tender, turning and brushing with marinade often.
Grill time:
3/4 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: easy fudge
directions: In heavy 2-quart saucepan, combine the first 4 ingredients. Bring to boiling over medium heat; cook to soft ball stage, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Immediately add chocolate bits and marshmallows.
Stir until chocolate and marshmallows are melted.
Stir in nuts and vanilla.
Spread into a buttered 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Cool; cut into squares.

title: shrimp creole
directions: In skillet cook onion, celery and garlic in shortening until tender but not brown.
Add tomatoes, tomato sauce, salt, sugar, Worcestershire sauce, chili powder and hot pepper sauce.
Simmer uncovered 45 minutes.

title: squash dressing
directions: Mix and bake in casserole dish for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: spareribs and sauerkraut
directions: Pack into kettle and barely cover with water.
Add salt and simmer until tender, about 1 hour.
Add sauerkraut, pushing kraut down into meat stock.
Cook 30 minutes more.

title: quick tuna casserole
directions: Mix tuna, soup and 3/4 cup crushed potato chips and place in greased casserole dish.
Place more crushed chips to cover dish. Bake in hot oven until heated.

title: dirt cake
directions: Mix pudding and milk until thick.
Mix softened butter and cream cheese together, then mix into pudding mixture.
Fold in Cool Whip and spread into your choice of containers.
Scrape filling from Oreo cookies and grind chocolate cookies in blender until fine.
Spread on top of pudding mixture.

title: sloppy turkey toms
directions: Crumble turkey into hard plastic colander or microwave ground meat cooker set in a microwave-safe pie plate.
Add garlic and onion.
Microwave, uncovered, on full power for 6 to 7 minutes or until meat is no longer pink, stirring once.
Drain.

title: california cobb salad
directions: Shred lettuce, watercress and romaine fine; place in a large salad bowl.
Arrange diced tomatoes, chicken, crumbled bacon, diced avocado, diced eggs and crumbled Blue cheese in strips across salad greens.
Just before serving, toss with enough vinagrette dressing to moisten salad and salt and pepper.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: potato casserole
directions: Combine potatoes, cheese, salt, sour cream, soup and onion together in large bowl and pour into buttered casserole dish.
Mix cornflakes and melted butter and sprinkle on potatoes. Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients; make a well.
Combine eggs and next 3 ingredients and add to well.
Fold in raisins and nuts.

title: chocolate strawberries
directions: Rinse strawberries, but leave stems intact.
Dry well on paper towels.
Melt the chocolate bits in double boiler over hot, but not boiling water.
Stir until smooth.
Reduce heat to low.
Dip berries in chocolate, one at a time, leaving an uncoated rim around the stem.
Shake off excess chocolate.
Place berries on wax paper.
Refrigerate for about 30 minutes.

title: kraut salad
directions: Drain all ingredients and mix well.
Place in refrigerator and let set for 2 days, stirring twice a day.
It is cool and crunchy; great with ham or dried beans.
Will keep in refrigerator for 1 or 2 weeks.

title: turkey hash
directions: Melt the butter in a skillet and saute the onion until slightly browned.
Add the diced potatoes and green pepper. Season with a little seasoned salt and pepper.
Mix in the diced turkey and cook slowly for about five minutes.
Add the gravy and cook a few minutes longer.

title: lasagna
directions: Mix; mash can of tomatoes with potato masher.
Mix tomato sauce, tomato paste with cup water, sauce mix and garlic.
Let simmer 30 minutes.

title: baked salmon fillets
directions: Dot top of 6 ounce salmon with a mixture of bread crumbs, dill, mayonnaise, mustard and pepper. Arrange in baking pan coated with cooking spray. Bake in 450° oven about 15 minutes or until fish is opaque throughout.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Blend first 5 ingredients.
Rub mixture on chicken.
Place chicken on baking dish.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: quick nut fudge
directions: Combine all ingredients, except nuts and vanilla, in top of a double boiler.
Place over hot water and stir until smooth.
Add nuts, vanilla and milk.
Spread mixture quickly into a buttered 9 x 5-inch pan.
Cool; cut into squares.

title: quick spanish hamburger soup
directions: In saucepan, cook ground beef until browned; drain off fat. Stir in salt and pepper.
Add tomato sauce, carrot, mushrooms, onions, olives and sugar.
Stir in water and wine.
Cover.
Simmer for 30 to 35 minutes or until carrot is tender, stirring occasionally.
Sprinkle individual servings with Parmesan cheese, if desired.
Makes 2 servings.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix the cream cheese, crushed pineapple, green pepper and 1 cup chopped nuts.
Chill, then form into a ball and roll in additional nuts.
Makes 2 small balls or 1 larger ball.
Serve with crackers.

title: hot chocolate mix(beverages)
directions: Stir ingredients together in a large bowl or pan until well blended.
Store in an airtight container.
When you are ready for hot chocolate, fill your mug 1/3 to 1/2 full of mix, depending on how strong you like it.
Add hot water until full and stir throughly.

title: simply delicious pork chops
directions: Arrange
chops	in a single layer in baking dish.
In a small bowl,
combine oil, catsup, lemon juice, Worcestershire sauce
and soy sauce.	Using a wire whisk or fork, spread half of the seasoning mixture over chops.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for
30 minutes.
Turn chops and spread with remaining seasoning mixture. Bake, uncovered, 30 minutes more.

title: pancakes
directions: Heat griddle to medium-high heat.
In large bowl, beat eggs. Stir in milk and oil.
Add remaining ingredients; beat or stir just until large lumps disappear.
Lightly grease heated griddle. Pour batter about 1/4 cup at a time onto hot griddle.
Cook until bubbles form and edges start to dry; turn and cook other side. Makes sixteen 4-inch pancakes.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Mix all ingredients well and pour into an unbaked pie shell. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: holiday cheese cake
directions: Combine crumbs, 3 tablespoons sugar and oleo for 9-inch crust. Bake
at
for 10 minutes.
Mix cream cheese, 3/4 cup sugar, lemon juice and rind.
Mix well.
Add eggs, one at a
time. Pour
mixture
in crust and bake at 300° for 55 minutes.
Combine sour
cream,
2 tablespoons sugar and vanilla; spread over cheese cake.
Bake 10 minutes more.

title: baked fish
directions: Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Boil sweet potatoes until tender.
Drain, peel and mash potatoes or beat in mixer.
Add sugar, butter, eggs, milk and vanilla.
Pour into 9-inch pie crust and bake 10 minutes at 425°, then 45 to 50 minutes at 325°.

title: oatmeal chip cookie(mix in a jar)
directions: To make mix:
Combine flour, baking soda, cinnamon and salt in a small bowl.
Place flour mixture in a 1-quart jar.
Layer remaining ingredients in the order listed, pressing down firmly after each layer.
Seal with a lid and decorate with fabric and ribbon.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Melt margarine; saute onion and green pepper for a few minutes.
Stir in flour and cook a minute or so.
Add tomatoes and liquid, sugar, salt, pepper, parsley flakes and chili sauce; simmer until thickened and seasonings are blended, approximately 15 minutes.
Remove bay leaf before serving.

title: microwave chicken a la king
directions: Melt 2 tablespoons of margarine in large casserole dish. Whisk in flour. Add onion. Microcook (100%) uncovered for 3 minutes.
Add 1/2 cup broth.
Whisk until smooth.
Whisk in remaining 1/2 cup broth and heavy cream.
Stir in peas.
Microcook (100%) uncovered for 8 minutes, whisking several times.
Add pepper sauce, remaining 2 tablespoons margarine and salt. Stir until margarine melts. Add chicken. Serve over mashed potatoes, rice or toast.
Serves 4.

title: 24 hour salad
directions: Mix well; cover tightly.
Refrigerate overnight.
Before starting your layers, take peas from freezer and thaw about 20 minutes.

title: no-crust pepperoni cheese pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Sprinkle cheese and pepperoni on bottom of 9-inch pie plate (sprayed with nonstick coating); set aside. In medium bowl, with wire whisk or fork, beat eggs, milk and basil until well blended.
Pour egg mixture into pie plate over cheese and pepperoni.
Bake for 25 minutes, or until knife inserted in center of pie comes out clean.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Bake cake in 9 x 13-inch pan or 2 (8-inch) round pans.
Slice to form 4 thin slices.
Prepare pudding and jello according to package directions.
Layer ingredients in punch bowl. Refrigerate.
If a hole in punch bowl, fill with fruit first.

title: date bars
directions: Blend first 3 ingredients well.
Add next 3 ingredients. Blend well.
Add dates.
Mix all well.
Place into well-greased and floured 13 x 9-inch roasting pan.
Bake in oven at 350° for 35 minutes.
Do not overbake.

title: vanilla refrigerator wafers
directions: Cream together the butter, margarine and powdered sugar.
Beat in egg and vanilla.
Combine flour, soda, cream of tartar and salt; add to creamed mixture.
Mix well.
Divide dough in half. Form each half into 2-inch round roll.
Wrap in waxed paper or aluminum foil.
Chill in refrigerator or freezer; slice 3/8-inch thick.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool on rack.
Makes about 7 dozen.

title: copper pennies
directions: Slice and boil the carrots; drain.
Toss onion and green pepper with carrots.
Mix the sugar, dry mustard, tomato soup, vinegar and salad oil; add salt and pepper to taste.
Pour over vegetables.
Marinate overnight in refrigerator.
Serve cold.

title: pineapple cheese ball
directions: Beat cream cheese until smooth.
Add onion, pineapple, seasoned salt and 1 cup pecans, mixing well.
Shape into a ball. Roll in remaining pecans.
Chill 2 hours.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix flour or cornstarch thoroughly with sugar.
Beat eggs slightly. Add butter to salt and sugar mixture.
Mix, then add syrup, vanilla and nuts.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake very slowly in preheated oven at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: southern raised biscuits
directions: Dissolve the yeast in warm milk.
Add the oil.
Combine the flour, soda, salt, and sugar.
Add this mixture to the milk mixture.
Knead 20 - 30 times.
Roll out to 1/2 inch thickness. Cut in rounds.
Butter one round and place another round on top. Cover and let rise.
Bake at 375 degrees for 12 - 15 minutes.

title: potato casserole
directions: Shred potatoes into greased 9 x 13-inch dish.
Melt butter in saucepan; add onion, sour cream, soup and cheese.
Spread evenly over potatoes and mix well.
Top with paprika and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 10.

title: aunt theresa's oatmeal crispies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Form a long loaf and cut slice and bake for 10 to 12 minutes at 375°.
Can also be refrigerated and then sliced. Great with raisins or chocolate chips in.

title: country chops(4 servings)
directions: Heat grill.
In small bowl, combine all sauce ingredients. Blend well and set aside.
When ready to barbecue, place pork chops on gas grill over medium heat or on charcoal grill 4 to 6 inches from medium-high coals.
Cook for 10 to 15 minutes, or until pork is tender and no longer pink, turning once and brushing chops generously with sauce during last 5 minutes of grilling.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Make juice from tomatoes (8 to 10 quarts juice).
Cook onions and green peppers until tender.
Put into blender and puree.
In a large pot put tomato juice, onions and green peppers; add oil, olive oil, black pepper, celery salt, garlic salt, salt, sugar, oregano and chili powder.
Cook for 45 minutes.
Add tomato paste and bay leaves.
Simmer for 1 hour.
Put in jars and seal.

title: baklava
directions: Grease a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
In a large bowl, with spoon, mix chopped walnuts, sugar and cinnamon until blended.
Cut phyllo into 13 x 9-inch rectangles.

title: beef stroganoff(club member: laine shoemake)
directions: Cut steak in thin strips; sprinkle meat tenderizer and let set for 10 minutes. Melt oleo in frying pan; cook steak strips until no longer pink. Remove from pan, leaving drippings. Put sliced onions in drippings; cook over low heat until soft. Spoon over steak. Mix flour and small amount flour; pour in pan with bouillon and mustard. Stir until thickens. Stir in sour cream. Do not boil after adding sour cream. Spoon over steak and onions. Serve over hot noodles.

title: finger jello
directions: Dissolve jello in 3 cups boiling water.
Dissolve 4 packages gelatin in 2 cups cold water.
Mix together.
Pour into a 13 x 9-inch cake pan.
Place in refrigerator.
Cut in cubes when set.

title: guacamole dip
directions: Fold in soy mayo as desired.

title: prize meat loaf
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients except ground beef; mix well.
Add ground beef; mix lightly but thoroughly. Press into 8 x 4-inch loaf pan.
Bake 1 hour, drain and let stand 5 minutes.
Makes 8 servings.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and pumpkin.
Add egg; mix well.
Add dry ingredients and raisins.
Drop from spoon onto cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: aunt barbara's frozen peanut butter pie
directions: Put into blender the cream cheese, peanut butter, sugar and milk; blend until smooth.
Pour into big bowl.
Fold Cool Whip into mixture.
Pour into pie shells.
Top with nuts to decorate. Freeze.
Remove from freezer about 20 minutes before serving. Serves 6.

title: paula's seafood dip
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Chill and serve with crackers or chips.

title: mountain muffins
directions: Combine flour, sugar, baking soda and salt in large bowl. Stir in egg, milk, banana and oil; mix well.
Add oats, raisins and coconut; stir to blend.
Line muffin tins with paper liners. Fill 2/3 full.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes 1 dozen muffins.

title: ham and mushroom crepes
directions: Prepare crepes.
Melt 3 tablespoons of butter over medium heat until bubbly.
Add mushrooms and saute until just lightly browned. Sprinkle with 1 tablespoon of flour and stir.

Add whipping cream and cook over medium heat until mixture is thickened and liquid is reduced to about 1/3 cup, approximately 8 minutes; set aside. Place a piece of ham on each crepe and spoon on about 1/4 cup of the mushroom filling.
Roll and arrange seam side down in a buttered 9 x 13-inch dish.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil and debone chicken.
Mix chicken, soups and sour cream in large casserole dish.
Top with crumbled Ritz crackers.
Pour melted butter over mixture.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix all ingredients to a texture that can be formed into balls.
Let set approximately 1 hour before frying in fish grease. Form round balls and drop into hot grease.

title: english toffee
directions: Melt butter in pan and add sugar, syrup and water.
Stir until hard crack stage (290 degrees), about 30 minutes.
Quickly pour onto cookie sheet (buttered or Teflon).
Smooth with spoon.
Melt chocolate chips and spread over top.
Sprinkle on chopped nuts. Cools quicker in refrigerator.
Break into pieces.

title: cranberry relish
directions: Combine all the ingredients in a heavy saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat to medium-low; simmer for 10 minutes or until berries pop open.
Skim foam from the surface for a clear result. Cool to room temperature.
This relish will set as it cools. Serves 8.

title: hot apple cider eggnog
directions: Heat water, chocolate, corn syrup and liqueur in medium saucepan over low heat until chocolate is melted.
Stir in milk. Immediately transfer to ice-cream maker and freezer according to manufacturer's directions.
Makes 2 cups.

title: grandma mahaffey's baked beans
directions: Brown hamburger with onion.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: old time starter
directions: Combine flour, sugar and salt.
Mix well.
Add water and beat well.
Set in warm place, covered, for at least 12 hours.
Use as needed and feed each time you use it.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Put pecans and coconut in bottom of a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Pour German chocolate cake mix on top of nuts and coconut.
Mix oleo, cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Pour on top of cake mix.
Bake at 350° for approximately 60 minutes.
Cake will crack on top. Excellent.

title: lemon herb broccoli
directions: Steam broccoli over boiling water in a large saucepan for 3 to 4 minutes or until tender-crisp.
Melt oleo in a small saucepan over medium heat.
Blend in lemon juice, mustard and marjoram. Spoon over broccoli.
Serve with grilled chicken breasts or broiled fish fillets.
Makes 2 to 3 servings.

title: orange slush
directions: Blend together ingredients.
Drink immediately.
May substitute other fruits for orange juice concentrate.
Suggestions:
2/3 cup strawberries or raspberries.

title: no-cook banana pudding
directions: Mix homogenized milk with the box of pudding mix; add condensed milk and whipped topping and mix well.
Using a large dish, layer the vanilla wafers, banana slices and pudding mixture until all is used.
Let chill in refrigerator before serving.

title: grandma gerry's apple dumplings
directions: Mix first 2 ingredients.
Put on floured surface and flatten with hands into a rectangle.
Peel and cut apples as you would for pie.
Place on dough and sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon.
Roll like a jelly roll.
Place the water and 1/2 cup sugar on the stove in an 8-inch square pan.
Heat until sugar is dissolved and it comes to a boil.
Cut the dumplings to desired shape and put in pan with water.
Place a dab of butter on each dumpling and bake at 350° until brown.
Serve warm or cold.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix cracker crumbs and melted butter and pat into a 9x13 pan. Beat eggs and 2 sticks butter with a mixer, add powdered sugar. Spread this
mixture over graham cracker crust and cover with sliced bananas.
Spread one large can drained pineapple over bananas.
Cover with cool whip.
Decorate with cherries and chopped nuts.
Chill overnight.

title: quick onion fries
directions: In large bowl, combine soup mix and oil.
Add potatoes; toss to coat.
Bake according to directions on package of potatoes, stirring occasionally.
Makes 6 servings.

title: potluck potatoes
directions: Slice potatoes; add all ingredients together.
Heat until cheese is melted.
Put in casserole and cover with 2 cups crushed corn flakes and crumbs, mixed with 1/2 cup butter, melted.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: aunt mazie's homemade coconut cake
directions: Combine baking powder and sugar; blend thoroughly.
Add to butter, eggs, milk and vanilla.
Stir in flour.
Bake in round greased and floured cake pans at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: aunt frances' spinach with sour cream
directions: Cook frozen spinach with onion.
Beat eggs and mix with other ingredients, then mix with spinach and onion.
Bake in casserole dish for 25 minutes at 350°.

title: creole omelette
directions: Slice bell pepper and onion, then saute in oil just until tender.
Add soup, water and vinegar.
Cook over low heat about 5 minutes.
Meanwhile cook four 2-egg omelettes or scramble 8 eggs. Serve Creole sauce over eggs.
Makes 4 servings.

title: raisin custard pie
directions: Mix together the ingredients, then pour into an unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake 30 minutes longer.

title: heavenly salad
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Add juice.
Fold in drained fruit. Top with chopped nuts and chill.

title: truffles
directions: Combine chocolate frosting and confectioners sugar in large bowl.
Stir with wooden spoon until thoroughly blended.
Cover each of 36 pecan halves with 1 tablespoon candy mixture.
Roll into 1-inch balls; set aside.
Chop remaining pecans; set aside. Place chocolate chips and shortening in 2-cup glass measuring cup. Microwave at Medium for 2 minutes; stir.
Microwave for 1 minute longer at Medium; stir until smooth.
Dip one candy ball into chocolate mixture until completely covered.
Remove with fork to cooling rack.
Sprinkle top with chopped pecans.
Repeat with remaining candy balls.
Allow to stand until chocolate mixture is set.
Makes 3 dozen candies.

title: carrot muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease muffin tins or line with baking cups and set aside.
Combine flour, sugar and cinnamon in a mixing bowl.
Mix applesauce, oil and eggs together.
Add to dry ingredients and stir just until moistened, batter will be lumpy. Do not overmix.
Fold in carrots and nuts.
Fill tins and bake for 20 minutes.

title: broccoli and chicken casserole
directions: In a 13 x 9-inch baking dish, layer rice, spices, chicken, and broccoli.
Spoon soup over broccoli.
Pour water over all, top with cheese cubes, cover and cook at 350 for 45 minutes.
Remove from oven and stir cook 5 - 10 more minutes.

title: peanut butter swirl bars
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients.
Beat eggs and vanilla until creamy. Combine the rest of the ingredients.
Spread into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Sprinkle 1 (12 ounce) package chocolate chips over surface.
Place in a 350° oven for 5 minutes.
Remove from oven. Run knife through to marbleize. Return to oven for 30 minutes or until done.
Makes 4 dozen 2 x 1-inch bars.

title: annette's meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together well, bake at 350 degrees for 1 - 1
1/2 hours.

title: peach pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Rinse, peel and pit peaches; slice into small pieces.
Combine peaches, sugar (or jam) and tapioca and spread filling evenly in pie shell.
Make lid of lattice, spiral or medallion shapes with unbaked pie dough.
Brush with egg glaze. Put assembled pie on baking sheet and bake until internal temperature reaches 180° or until filling bubbles up like cooking jam, about 1 hour.
Makes 8 servings.

title: lemon supreme cake
directions: Combine all ingredients, except eggs, confectioners sugar and lemon juice.
Mix well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beat well after each addition.
Bake in greased and floured tube pan at 325° for 1 hour.

title: chinese pork chops
directions: Add soy sauce to the brown sugar until it makes a fairly thick paste (like glue).
Add the garlic, then coat both sides of each chop with the marinade.
Let stand in refrigerator for at least 2 hours.
Barbecue on grill (about 5 minutes a side or until done) or bake in oven at 350° for approximately 40 minutes.
Serves 4 to 8.

title: easy chicken pie
directions: Cook chicken, skin and remove bones.
Put melted oleo in bottom of 9 x 9-inch baking dish.
Lay chicken on top.
Mix broth with soup and vegetables.
Top with Bisquick mixed with milk. Bake at 350° until brown.

title: sheath cake
directions: Boil butter, Crisco, water and cocoa 1 minute.
Pour over flour, sugar and baking powder.
Then add eggs, buttermilk (add tablespoon of lemon juice in regular milk) and vanilla.
Mix well and pour into greased and floured pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: scripture cake
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, salt, cinnamon, nutmeg, cloves and allspice.
Set aside. Cream butter and sugar; add honey and eggs and beat until light and fluffy.
Combine fruit and nuts in a small bowl.
Sprinkle 1/4 cup of the flour mixture over the fruits and nuts. Add remaining flour mixture to creamed sugar and butter alternately with milk.
Stir in fruit and nuts and spoon into a greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.

title: venison (or beef) steak and gravy
directions: Trim fat.
Sprinkle meat with salt and pepper.
Dredge in flour.
Fry at medium heat until brown.
Remove steak and leave about 5 tablespoons fat in pan.
Add 3 tablespoons remaining flour and brown.
Add water and bring to a boil.
Cut heat down and put steak back into gravy; cover and simmer until tender.
Serve with rice or mashed potatoes.

title: apple delight
directions: Combine sugar, flour, salt and baking powder in bowl.
Add walnuts and apples to dry mixture.
Combine eggs and vanilla and add.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes in an 8 x 8-inch square pan.

title: carrot-pineapple bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix ingredients in order given.
Line 2 ungreased loaf pans with wax paper; pour batter into pans.
Bake 1 hour.
Wrap in aluminum foil.
Store in refrigerator.

title: amish sugar cookies
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients.
Add eggs; beat well.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Chill in refrigerator overnight. Roll into balls; press down and sprinkle with sugar or cookies can be iced after baking.
Put on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream butter, Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Add salt, cocoa and baking powder to flour.
Add flour and milk alternately to butter mixture and add vanilla.
Pour into greased tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: crabmeat ball
directions: Soften cheese, add a little mayonnaise, salt and milk to desired consistency. Blend until cheese is spreadable. Stir in crabmeat, and mold into a flattened ball in round dish.

title: fried frog legs
directions: Wash frog legs under cold water.
Soak frog legs in mixture of milk, salt and 3 tablespoons of paprika for 5 minutes.
Heat vegetable oil to 375°.
Season flour with 3 tablespoons paprika and dip frog legs in seasoned mix.
Shake off excess flour and fry legs for 3 to 5 minutes, depending on size of legs.
Turn legs frequently to keep from burning.
Paprika does not have to be used as it does not affect the flavor.
However, the meat takes on a prettier golden brown color as it fries.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch and water together and cook until thickened.
Add jello and mix well.
Cool to room temperature. Slice berries in baked shell.
Pour cooked mixture over them. Chill 30 to 60 minutes.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: cheese soup
directions: Blend first 4 ingredients really fine in blender or processor. Saute in butter.
Add broth and milk.
Boil for one hour.
Add cheese, flour and cornstarch.

title: jello cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Put through cookie press.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes at 400°.

title: granny's thanksgiving dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Be sure to brown onion and celery first. Put in a greased pan.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: ham quiche
directions: In a large bowl, beat eggs.
Add soup and cream.
Mix well. Sprinkle cheese, meat and broccoli into pie crust.
Pour soup mixture over.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until center is set.

title: rosemary potatoes
directions: Wash potatoes and cut into quarters, almost bite size.
Spray glass casserole with Pam; put potatoes in pan.
Crush rosemary over potatoes; add olive oil and stir.
Cook in oven about 1 hour or until brown.
Stir every 20 minutes.
Bake at 325°.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Drain artichoke hearts.
Combine all ingredients except crackers in food processor.
Bake in a small casserole for 20 minutes.
Serve with Melba rounds or crackers.

title: nuts and bolts
directions: Melt margarine and mix all ingredients together. Put in slow oven at 150°; stir often.

title: banana bread
directions: Mash bananas in bowl with fork.
Beat until well blended.
Add nuts.
Bake at 350° until done (about an hour or hour and a half).

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Saute celery, onions and bell pepper in margarine.
Drain canned vegetables.
Mix all ingredients together in casserole dish.
Top with Cheese Nips and slivered almonds.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: beef ball
directions: Soften cream cheese. Chop packs of beef.
Chop onions.
Whip cream cheese and add beef, onions and Worcestershire sauce.
Form into ball shape and then lay the remaining beef slices on top, pressing down into a flat, round shape as you go.
Serve with a variety of snack crackers.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook macaroni.
Drain and run cool water over.
Let drain. Cut up Spam and green pepper into small cubes.
Mix all together with cheese.
Add Miracle Whip to taste.

title: ham and cheese strata
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Place bread on bottom. Layer ham, cheese and mushrooms.
Mix eggs, milk, salt and pepper in blender and pour over top.
Cover and refrigerate at least 12 hours.
Preheat oven to 350° and bake uncovered about 40 minutes or until center is set.
Serves 8.
(May substitute any kind of meat.)

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix melted margarine, stuffing mix and broth.
Put 1/2 of this in dish.
Add chopped chicken, onions, celery and mayonnaise.
Mix well.
Add remaining half of stuffing mix.
Add eggs and milk. Let stand overnight
in refrigerator.
Remove next morning and let stand 1 hour.
Spread chicken soup on top.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes.
Take out of oven, sprinkle top with grated cheese.
Bake 10 more minutes.
Serve.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Mix mayonnaise, cheese and artichokes.
Spread in greased pan.
Bake 350° until brown on top and bubbly.
Serve with crackers.

title: v-8 beef stew
directions: Brown onion and meat.
Add all remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Cook in crock-pot for 4 hours.

title: snowballs
directions: Soften butter; thaw orange juice.
Mix everything except coconut.
Wet hands with water; make balls the size of large marbles.
Roll each ball in coconut.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown meat.
Drain.
Add Ro-Tel, soup and beans.
Layer in casserole Doritos, meat mixture and top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° until cheese is
melted.

title: goro
directions: Beat cream until stiff; beat yolks until stiff.
Add sugar and beat more.
Add the beaten cream and cardamon.
Mix in enough flour to make soft dough.
Pound the butter in with rolling pin.
Do not use too much flour.
Use 8 cups when mixing and 2 1/2 cups to roll out.
Bake on large burner on medium.
Do not cool this dough.

title: breakfast pecan rolls
directions: Thaw bread dough just enough to cut.
Cut lengthwise and halves into 6 pieces or 12 pieces in all.
Grease 1-piece tube or Bundt pan.
Place pieces in circle.
Sprinkle pudding mix over sections. Sprinkle cinnamon and nuts in desired amounts.
In saucepan, mix butter and sugars; cook until dissolved slightly.
Pour over rolls and cover.
Let rise in refrigerator overnight.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.
Immediately invert on plate.

title: jello delight
directions: Put fruit into bowl with juice.
Sprinkle jello over top and mix.
Add cottage cheese.
Fold in Cool Whip; refrigerate until thick.

title: broccoli salad
directions: In a large bowl, stir together mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar. Add broccoli, bacon, raisins and onions. Toss well. Yield 8 to 10 servings.

title: stromboli
directions: Cook spinach; drain.
Saute garlic in oil.
Pour oil and garlic over drained spinach.
You may add a little grated Parmesan or Romano cheese.
Make each package of crescent rolls into a rectangle.
Flatten slightly with rolling pin.
Put spinach and Mozzarella cheese onto flattened dough and roll.
Bake according to crescent roll directions, or just a little longer.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and place in casserole dish. Bake at 350 for 50-60 minutes.

title: fudge brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Line a 9-inch square pan with foil. Grease foil.
Melt chocolate and butter in top of double boiler. Cool 15 minutes.
Stir sugar, eggs, vanilla and flour into chocolate.
Pour into prepared pan, spreading evenly.
Top with walnuts.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool completely in pan on a wire rack.
Refrigerate 30 minutes.
Invert.
Remove pan and peel off foil.
Turn over and cut into squares.

title: heart-healthy apple coffee cake(only 5 grams of fat)
directions: Spray a 9-inch round baking pan with nonstick spray coating; set aside.
In medium bowl, combine the 2/3 cup all-purpose flour, 1/2 cup whole wheat flour, baking soda, 1 teaspoon cinnamon and salt. Set aside.
In a large mixing bowl, toss together the chopped apples and egg product.
Stir in the 3/4 cup sugar, the first 1/4 cup nuts and applesauce. Add flour mixture and stir just until combined.
Pour batter into prepared pan.

title: cheesy chicken enchiladas
directions: Microwave onion, garlic and oil in a 2-quart casserole on High 2 to 3 minutes.
Stir in chicken, chilies, broth and seasonings. Microwave on High 4 minutes.
Add cream cheese; stir until melted. Spoon 1/3 cup chicken mixture onto each tortilla; roll up.
Place seam side down in microwave-safe baking dish.
Microwave Velveeta cheese, milk and 1/4 cup tomato in bowl on High for 2 to 3 minutes until cheese is melted.
Pour sauce over tortillas.
Top with remaining tomatoes.
Microwave on High 6 to 8 minutes until thoroughly heated.

title: broccoli cheese bake
directions: Cook broccoli as directed; drain.
Melt margarine over low heat
Stir in flour and salt; simmer 2 to 3 minutes.
Gradually add milk, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Blend in cream cheese until smooth.
Add onions.
Pour over broccoli; add cheese and crumbs on top.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.
Serve.

title: stanley kelly's kettle beef
directions: Brown meat in skillet; remove.
Move to crock-pot.
Cook slowly several hours.
Add tomatoes, celery, carrots, onions, okra, mushrooms, water chestnuts and mushroom soup.
Season to taste with salt, pepper and Worcestershire sauce.
Serves a large group and is really good.

title: sweet pickles
directions: Pour juice off pickles.
Drain well.
Slice pickles thin and garlic buttons.
Put in large bowl.
Add sugar and spices.
Stir often for 3 days.
Put in jar and refrigerate.
Keep refrigerated until all is eaten.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Saute
onion,
pepper
and celery in oil; add flour and stir until
smooth like gravy.
Add tomatoes (cut), sauce and seasoning.	Simmer	20 minutes.
Add juice and shrimp.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: sour cream cake
directions: Sift together flour, salt and soda; set aside.
Cream together butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add egg yolks one at a time.
Add vanilla and dry ingredients alternately with sour cream.
Beat whites and fold into mixture.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Soften margarine and combine ingredients in order given. Batter will be short.
Refrigerate 15 minutes for easier handling. Roll into balls; place on cookie sheet and flatten crossways with a fork, dipped in water, prior to baking.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes 4 to 6 dozen cookies.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Layer chicken, crackers, sour cream and soup.
Repeat until all used up.
Bake at 350° until browned.

title: easy chili
directions: Brown meat and onions in hot oil in skillet; add remaining ingredients.
Cook over low heat, stirring occasionally, 20 to 30 minutes.

title: spoon rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Melt margarine; cream with sugar.
Add egg.
Stir in yeast.
Add flour and mix well.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Cream butter, sugar and vanilla.
Add flour, chips and pecans.
Form batter about 1-inch in diameter.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet; press down with a lightly floured bottom of a small glass.
Bake in 350° oven for 12 to 14 minutes or until edges are golden.
Makes about 2 1/2 dozen.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Boil chicken breasts and drain.
Cube and put into 9 x 13-inch dish.
Mix soup and sour cream together.
Pour over chicken.
Crush Club crackers and mix with melted margarine.
Spread over top of chicken mixture with 2 tablespoons of poppy seed.
Bake for 25 minutes at 350°.

title: corn flake pudding
directions: Heat milk, do not boil.
Beat egg and add other ingredients. Add milk and mix together.
Add corn flakes and stir.
Bake in 350° oven until silver knife comes out clean.
Bake approximately 30 to 45 minutes.
This recipe can easily be doubled or tripled.

title: mom's homemade bread
directions: Mix lard, hot water, sugar and salt.
When water is lukewarm, add 1 1/2 yeast cakes.
Let dissolve.
Pour 4 cups flour and mix, then add 2 cups flour, one at a time.
Knead until not real wet. Shape into balloon.
Let raise in warm place.
Then push down and shape.
Place in pans.
Let raise and bake at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: grandma's molasses drop cookies
directions: Sift salt, flour, soda and spices together.
Add remaining ingredients.

title: sloppy joes(for a crowd)
directions: Cook at 300° for 2 to 3 hours.

title: apple mallow salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 1 cup hot water or juice drained from pineapple.	Chill
until
jello has partially thickened.
Whip jello until fluffy.
Fold
in
cream
and rest of ingredients. Chill.

title: macaroni salad(serves 12)
directions: Cook bacon.
Drain.
Coarsely chop.
Cook pasta in salted water.
Drain, rinse in cold water and drain.
Whisk mayonnaise, buttermilk, lemon juice, mustard and sugar.
Add pasta, bacon, mushrooms and peas.
Toss.
Season with salt and pepper.

title: pork chop marinade
directions: Mix ingredients together. Add pork chops and marinate 1 to 2 nights in refrigerator.
Set out 2 hours before grilling so chops will be at room temperature. Grill chops.
Chops will be very tender, if not overcooked.

title: granny's seven-up pound cake
directions: Mix together sugar, margarine, Crisco and lemon extract until real creamy.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat well after each egg. Add flour alternately with 7-Up.
Mix well and bake in a Bundt pan at 350°.
Bake for 1 hour.
(Grease and flour pan.)

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs. Add sugar gradually, then syrup, salt, vanilla, butter and pecans.
Pour into pie shell and cook at 360° for about 60 minutes or until crust is light brown.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown meat, drain. Cook rice according to package directions. Add tomatoes and cheese. Bake in casserole dish until cheese melts. Serves 4.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Combine ingredients and beat 2 minutes on medium speed.
Pour in casserole dish.

title: marinated vegetables
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Refrigerate for 24 hours.
Drain. Serve cold.

title: baked brie with tuscany toast
directions: Spread pesto sauce on one side of bread slices.
Top with some of chopped tomato.
Place on a cookie sheet and bake in 400° oven until toasted.
Spread Brie on both sides with pesto sauce.
Bake in 400° oven until soft.
Serve with toast.

title: crispy baked fish
directions: Wash and dry fillets and cut into serving size pieces.
Pour lemon juice in a shallow bowl.
Add fish and let sit in juice 10 to 15 minutes.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream the shortening, sugars and eggs.
Slowly add flour, soda, salt and vanilla.
Stir in chips and nuts.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheets at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: lemon delight
directions: Combine butter, flour and nuts.
Spread into 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool. Cream together next 3 ingredients and spread on top of cooled crust.
Mix until thick the pudding and milk.
Pour on top of the first layer.
Top with remaining Cool Whip and a few chopped nuts.

title: sauce for yellow or white cake
directions: Melt margarine in large skillet.
Add flour and sugar that have been mixed together.
Cook until brown and hard (do not let mixture burn).
Add milk and cook, stirring constantly until all sugar mixture is dissolved.
Let cool.
Add vanilla.
Use as sauce on cake.

title: frozen cups
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour in small paper cups.
Place in freezer and freeze until firm.

title: meatballs and gravy
directions: Mix well ground meat, eggs, bread, tomato sauce, onion, 1 teaspoon of salt and 1/4 teaspoon of black pepper.
Roll the mixture into balls and fry until slightly brown and then place in large bowl and fry gravy in skillet with the grease from the meatballs.

title: no knead rolls
directions: Melt margarine. Add milk. Turn heat off.
Beat the eggs well. Add sugar and salt.
Add the milk and margarine.
Dissolve the yeast in warm water and add to mixture.
Gradually stir in the flour.
Mix well and put in a large greased bowl.
Cover and put in refrigerator.
Leave overnight or at least 8 hours. Divide dough in 3 sections.
Roll and make in desired rolls.

title: impossible cheeseburger pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease 10-inch deep pie plate.
Brown and stir beef and onion until brown.
Drain, stir in salt and pepper. Spread in plate.
Beat milk, eggs and Bisquick until smooth.
Pour over meat.
Bake 25 minutes.
Top
with tomatoes and cheese.
Bake until knife inserted in center comes out clean, about 5 to 8 minutes more.
Then serve.

title: soup(quick and easy)
directions: Brown meat and onion; drain.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer.
Serve with cornbread.

title: ruth ann's gourmet potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes in skins.
Cool, peel and slice.
Fold all ingredients with potatoes and turn into a greased 2-quart casserole.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: reese's cup candy
directions: Melt together and put on cookie sheet.
Melt 1 large chocolate bar.
Put on top of peanut butter base.
Cool in refrigerator. Cut into squares and chill.
Very good!

title: orange coconut pound cake
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in warm water; add oil to mixture.
Add cake mix and flavorings.
Add eggs, mixing after each egg.
Add coconut.
Pour in tube or Bundt pan and bake at 300° for 45 to 60 minutes.
Test for doneness with toothpick.

title: spinach dip
directions: In a medium bowl, combine spinach, sour cream, mayonnaise, soup mix, water chestnuts and green onions.
Cover; chill.
Serve with fresh vegetables, crackers, pumpernickel bread or chips.
Makes 3 cups.

title: shells with meat sauce casserole
directions: Melt margarine in skillet.
Add ground beef and brown.
Add onion, celery and garlic.
Cover until celery is tender.
Remove from heat.
Add Parmesan cheese, salt and bread crumbs.
Stuff each shell with cooled meat mixture.
Pour 1 jar of spaghetti sauce in casserole.
Place in shell.
Pour second jar over shells.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Can top with Mozzarella cheese.

title: cheese meat loaf
directions: Mix the first 9 ingredients and 1/2 can of cheese soup.
Add hot water; continue mixing.
Place in greased meat loaf pan. Hollow out center of meat loaf; fill with the rest of the cheese soup.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: tea cake
directions: Mix together the first three ingredients and soak overnight. Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into two greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 325° for about 1 1/2 hours.
Yields two loaves.

title: ripe tomatoes sauce
directions: Peel
tomatoes
and cut in small pieces.
Place in iron skillet. Add
onion
and
pepper. Add sugar and 1/2 cup water. Cook about 30 minutes.
Good with vegetables.

title: apple walnut cake
directions: Chop apples and put into a bowl.
Add sugar and set aside. In another bowl, put eggs, oil, vanilla, salt and cinnamon.
Beat well; then add flour and soda.
Beat again.
Add this mixture gradually to apples; add walnuts.
Bake in a greased tube pan or loaf pan at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool for 10 minutes and remove from pan.

title: pumpkin bars
directions: Beat together eggs, sugar, oil and pumpkin until light and fluffy.
Stir dry ingredients together in separate bowl.
Add all together and mix thoroughly.
Spread in 15 x 10 pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool completely.

title: heath bar dessert
directions: Mix both cracker crumbs and butter.
Spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cook 5 minutes at 350°.
Cool.

title: crab filled buns
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Spread on hamburger buns, about 6 regular size.
Wrap individually in foil.
Can be frozen after wrapping.
Bake at 350 degrees for 25 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes before opening.
Bake a little longer if necessary.

title: rice pudding
directions: Break eggs in bowl; beat slightly.
Add sugar, salt and vanilla.
Beat with spoon until well blended.
Add milk and stir in raisins and rice.
Set baking dish in a shallow pan filled about 1/4 full of water and bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until inserted knife comes out clean.

title: lime cheesecake
directions: Mix together graham crackers, butter and powdered sugar.
Put 1/2 of mix in bottom of 9 x 13-inch Tupperware pan.
Mix hot water and lime jello; chill.
Mix cream cheese, sugar and vanilla.
Add to this 1 large can of Milnot, that has been whipped.
Add chilled jello.
Pour on top of crust.
Crumble remaining crumbs on top. Chill and keep in fridge.

title: sunday yeast rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water and mix thoroughly in large bowl with remaining ingredients.
Cover and let stand 8 hours or overnight on kitchen counter.
Next morning, turn out on floured board and knead lightly.
Roll 1/2-inch thick and cut into rolls. Place rolls on greased cookie sheets.
Let rise 4 to 6 hours.
Bake in preheated 400° oven 10 to 12 minutes.

title: mrs. elkins' sheath cake
directions: Sift sugar and flour into a large bowl.
In saucepan, bring next 4 ingredients to rapid boil. Stir into sugar and flour.
Mix in other ingredients.
Pour into greased 11 x 16-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Five minutes before done, make icing.

title: ranch ham roll-ups
directions: In a small mixing bowl, beat cream cheese and dressing mix until smooth; add onions and mix well. Spread about 3 tablespoons of mixture over each tortilla. Top each with 2 slices of ham. Roll up tightly and wrap in plastic wrap. Refrigerate until firm. Unwrap and cut into 3/4 inch slices.

title: chicken-italian dressing bake
directions: Combine bread crumbs, cheese and salt in plastic bag.
Shake to mix.
Dip chicken in salad dressing.
Place chicken, one piece at a time, in bag and shake to coat.
Place on lightly greased pan.
Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes or until done.

title: hamburger cookies
directions: Frost flat side of one wafer with yellow.
Place unwrapped mint on top of frosting.
Put a small amount of red frosting on mint.
Sprinkle with green coconut to cover.
Take another wafer, frost flat side with red and place on top of coconut.
You now have a hamburger cookie.
Wrap in piece of foil.

title: ginger cookies
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients in order.
Add next 6 ingredients. Form into a ball (marble size) and roll in granulated sugar.
Bake in a greased pan at 350° for 13 to 15 minutes.
Makes approximately 6 dozen.

title: hidden valley ranch buffalo wings
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Dip chicken into mixture of melted butter, pepper sauce and vinegar; put in baking pan.
Sprinkle with 1 package of dry dressing mix.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes or until browned.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Serve with prepared Hidden Valley Ranch salad dressing as dip.

title: marinated pork chops
directions: Place pork chops in shallow dish. Combine remaining ingredients and pour over chops.
Cover and marinate in refrigerator 1 1/2 to 2 hours, turning once.

title: blueberry cake
directions: Mix all together (not topping). Pour into a 8 x 8 pan, sprinkle topping over batter. Bake at 350 degrees for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion together in butter until tender (no water).
Add remaining ingredients and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cheese dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes, until bubbly.
Good served on Shredded Wheat squares.

title: shrimp pilau
directions: Prepare rice, fry
shrimp
and bacon.
Drain well.
Add to rice and other seasonings.	Simmer for 30 minutes.

title: pan peaches
directions: Put sugar and vinegar on peaches and cook until thick.	Seal in jars or freeze.	This makes great fried pies.

title: maudie's giblet gravy
directions: Cook, bone and chop chicken.
Save broth.
Cook and chop eggs, then add eggs, butter and soup to broth; mix well.
Add chicken.
I also cook gizzards and livers and add to this.

title: macaroni salad veronique
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions; drain.
Rinse with cold water; drain again.
Combine macaroni, ham, grapes and onions.
Add dressing; toss lightly until well coated.
Chill 6 hours or overnight.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix ingredients together as listed.

title: mr. nik's hamburger stuff
directions: Brown hamburger; drain.
Drain lima beans and corn.
Place hamburger in bottom of casserole dish; cover with tomato soup. Next cover with corn and limas.
Cover with other can of tomato soup.
Heat at 350° for 25 minutes.
Sprinkle onion rings on top. Heat 5 minutes longer.
Remove and serve.

title: rum balls
directions: Combine all ingredients, except powdered sugar, blending well. Shape into small balls.
Roll into powdered sugar.
Store in a tightly sealed container.

title: cake with pineapple topping
directions: Mix and bake cake mix according to instructions on a cookie sheet with sides.
Mix cream cheese, pudding mix (do not use mixing instructions on box) and milk.
Spread on cooled cake. Chill for short time.
Spread over mixture the pineapple.
Spread Cool Whip over pineapple.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Combine mashed	potatoes,
hot	milk
and
butter, beat until fluffy.
Add
nutmeg,
cinnamon,
sugar
and
pineapple. Blend well, fold in egg whites.
Put into a greased casserole. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until puffy and brown.

title: ukrainian babka
directions: Warm milk in large pot (not hot because yeast will not rise). Dissolve yeast in warm milk.
Add 4 cups flour; mix well.
Put in warm place.
Cover with towel; let rise for 2 hours.
Add sugar, eggs, sour cream and salt; mix again.
Add rest of flour, a little at a time, until flour is used.
Add melted butter and raisins. Keep kneading until the dough comes clean from your hands.
Cover again; put in warm place until it doubles in size.

title: mushroom salad(france)
directions: Clean mushrooms; wash in cold water to which vinegar has been added.
Dry in a cloth; slice.
To keep mushrooms from turning black, sprinkle with lemon juice.
Toss lightly but thoroughly with mixture of mayonnaise, garlic, salt and pepper. Place in refrigerator for 1 or 2 hours; mixture will become moist from juice of mushrooms.
Stir lightly several times during chilling. Serve on a bed of bibb lettuce and parsley.
Yields 10 to 12 servings.

title: baked corn
directions: Pour in casserole dish and bake, uncovered, about an hour at 325° to 350°.
You may put grated cheese on top.

title: corn pudding
directions: Drain corns.
Place in a square casserole dish.
In another dish, beat eggs. Combine sugar and milk.
In casserole dish, combine all ingredients. Bake at 375° for approximately 45 minutes or until center doesn't shake.

title: french coconut pie
directions: Combine ingredients.
Beat well.
Pour in crust.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cook spaghetti as directed on package. Set aside.
In Dutch oven, melt margarine.
Stir in flour.
Add chicken broth; cook, stirring constantly, until sauce is thickened.
Remove from heat; stir in half and half, sherry, parsley, salt, nutmeg and pepper.
Toss chicken, mushrooms and cooked spaghetti into sauce.
Turn mixture into 13 x 9-inch pan. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until thoroughly heated.
Garnish with parsley before serving, if desired.
Makes 8 servings.

title: pineapple cheese loaf
directions: In medium size bowl, cream the cheese until smooth.
Stir in drained pineapple, half of pecans, green pepper, onion, sugar, salt and Worcestershire sauce.
Shape into loaf on plate.
Cover with plastic wrap.
Let season in refrigerator.
Freezes well.

title: chocolate almond marble pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt over hot (not boiling) water, 1/2 cup morsels.
Stir until smooth; set aside.
In medium bowl, combine flour, baking powder and salt; set aside.
In large bowl, combine sugar, vegetable oil and almond extract; beat well.
Add eggs, 1 at a time, beating well after each addition.
Gradually beat in flour mixture alternately with milk.
Divide batter in half.
Stir melted morsels and remaining 3/4 cup morsels into 1/2 of batter; mix well.
Pour 1/2 plain batter into greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Top with 1/2 of chocolate batter. Repeat layers with remaining batters.
Bake for 65 to 70 minutes. Cool 15 minutes; remove from pan.
Cool completely on wire rack. Sprinkle with confectioners sugar.

title: eggplant relish
directions: Peel eggplant and cut into narrow strips.
Combine water and vinegar.
Bring to boil.
Boil cauliflower 1 minute.
Take out with spoon to drain.
Boil eggplant 1 minute and drain.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Combine chili sauce, Miracle Whip, cream cheese and horseradish; mix well.
Add shrimp.
Chill and serve.

title: quick and easy jello salad
directions: Mix cottage cheese, pineapple and Cool Whip thoroughly. Sprinkle and fold in dry Jell-O.
(Do not add water.) Fold in any other fruits desired and sprinkle
with nuts.
Ready to eat in 5 minutes.
Delicious!

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Combine sugar, water, salt and cornstarch. Cook until clear. Remove from heat. Add Jello and stir well. Let cool. Cut up fresh berries into bottom of pie shells until covered well. Fill shells with sauce and chill until set. Serve with Cool Whip.

title: viennese rounds-christmas cookie(about 4 dozen cookies.)
directions: Mix sugar, margarine and egg. Stir in flour and pecans. Shape into roll 12 inches long, wrap and refrigerate at least 4 hours or until firm.
Heat oven to 350 degrees. Cut roll into 1/4 inch slices.
Place about 1 inch apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake about 15 min. or until light golden brown; cool.
Spread 1/2 teaspoon jam over each cookie.
Heat chocolate chips and shortening over low heat until melted.
Drizzle chocolate over cookies. 80 calories per cookie.

title: italian sausage egg bake
directions: Brown sausage; drain off fat and set aside.
Saute onion and mushrooms in butter.
Place meat in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover with mushrooms and onions.
In a bowl, beat eggs and half and half. Pour over sausage and onion mixture.

title: fresh coconut cake
directions: Mix together and beat for 2 minutes.
Bake at 350° until done. Makes three layers.

title: corn-chili-cheese casserole
directions: Mix ingredients together and put in 9 x 13-inch buttered pan. Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix pineapple and its juice with pudding, then add other fruit. Chill well.

title: clam chowder
directions: Saute onion.
Add juice from clams.
Add salt, pepper and parsley.
Add enough diced potatoes to come to the top of liquid. Add half and half and flour.
Add clams.

title: baked tomatoes
directions: Wash and dry tomatoes, remove top portion from each.
Melt margarine and add remaining ingredients.
Place tomatoes in baking dish and cover with topping.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes or until barely tender.
These can be prepared well in advance and stored in refrigerator before baking.
Serves 6.

title: coconut cream torte
directions: Prepare cake batter according to package directions.
Pour into three greased and floured 9 inch baking pans.
Bake at 350 degrees for 20-25 minutes or until a toothpick inserted near center comes out clean.
Cool for 10 minutes before removing from pan.
Cool completely.

title: date and coconut balls
directions: Cut dates into small pieces.
Mix together with sugar and beaten egg in saucepan.
Cook for 5 minutes over low heat.
Add vanilla, Rice Krispies and pecans.
Dampen hands and form into balls.
Roll in coconut or powdered sugar.

title: peanut delight
directions: Cook butter, milk, sugar and cocoa for 2 minutes.
Quickly add vanilla, milk, oatmeal, peanut butter and nuts.
Drop on wax paper.

title: mom's divinity(works best to make this on a clear, dry day.)
directions: Combine chocolate chips, marshmallows and nuts in large bowl. Blend sugar with milk and butter.
Cook at rolling boil for six minutes.
Remove from heat and add vanilla.
Pour into bowl with chocolate chip mixture.
Stir until well blended.
Pour into buttered pans; let stand 24 hours.

title: cheese krispies
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Roll into small balls and flatten balls in palm of hand about the size of half-dollar.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into greased loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: 10-minute peanut brittle(microwave)
directions: Pour a No. 2 can of crushed pineapple (with juice) into bowl. Pour a box of angel food cake mix on top. Mix. Pour into 9 x 13 baking dish and bake at 350° until top is brown. Cut into 12 pieces.

title: sweet and tangy almond chicken
directions: Combine molasses, mustard, garlic, parsley and lemon rind and brush mixture lightly over both sides of chicken breasts.
Spread ground almonds on a dinner plate and carefully dip breasts into almonds.
Place chicken on a waxed-paper-covered plate and refrigerate for at least an hour.
Heat oil in large skillet. Saute breasts for 10 to 15 minutes, until lightly browned and cooked through.
Garnish with parsley and lemon.
Excellent accompanied by buttered parsley noodles or rice pilaf.
Makes 4 servings.

title: crab ball
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Shape into ball.
Roll in chopped nuts, if desired, or serve plain.
Serve with cocktail sauce.

title: portuguese chocolate cake
directions: Beat eggs with sugar and Portowine.
Melt the chocolate gently with butter.
Add to the previous mixture.
Break the buttered cookies into pieces and mix.
Cover the bottom of pan with plastic bag. Pour the mixture and freeze for about 8 to 10 hours.

title: holiday cheese tree
directions: Combine cheeses; mix until well blended.
Add 1 tablespoon pimento, onion, pepper, Worcestershire sauce and salt.
Mix well. Chill.
Divide into 7 parts and shape into tree with base; smooth to form tree.
Cover with parsley.
Put nuts on base.
Dot tree with pimento.
Serve with assorted crackers.

title: banana pudding(quick and easy)
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients well. In another bowl, mix Cool Whip, sour cream and milk. Mix well and add to pudding mixture. Alternate layers of bananas, vanilla wafers and pudding mixture. Chill.

title: hungarian chicken paprikas
directions: In Dutch oven, put oil and heat.
Add onion and saute.
Add paprika, stirring, into onion.
Add chicken, turning to coat chicken with paprika.
Cook on low heat so liquid does not evaporate.
Cook 1 hour.
Do not add water.
Take chicken out. Add sour cream; stir until diluted (do not boil).
Put chicken back and turn very low.
Serve with rice, noodles or dumplings.

title: oatmeal pie
directions: Combine all ingredients and place in unbaked pie shell.
Bake for 30 minutes at 375°.

title: taco treat
directions: Layer
lettuce,
mixed cottage cheese and cream cheese, tomato, onion and Cheddar cheese (enough to cover last layer). Add sauce about 1 hour before serving with tortilla chips.

title: blueberry coffee cake
directions: Mix cake mix (reserve 1 1/2 c.), yeast, flour, eggs and water.
Beat 2 minutes.
Spread in greased 13 x 9 cake pan. Spread 1 can filling on top
Sprinkle with 2 Tbsp. sugar.
Mix remaining 1 1/2 c. cake mix with melted margarine with a fork. Crumble on top of pie filling.
Bake and glaze.

title: delicious 10 cup cookies
directions: Cream together first five ingredients.
Add last 8 ingredients.
Mix well.
Drop by spoons onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Let cool on rack 5 minutes before removing from cookie sheet.
Makes 4 to 6 dozen.

title: kim's potato casserole
directions: Mix 1 stick melted margarine, potatoes, sour cream, undiluted chicken soup, onions, Cheddar cheese, salt and pepper together. Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover with topping made with cornflakes and 1 stick melted margarine.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: fried apple ring
directions: Wash and core apples. Cut crosswise slices. Melt Crisco in a heavy frying pan. When hot, put apples in and cook until tender and lightly brown on both sides.

title: tomato pudding
directions: Cook tomatoes and bread slowly (over low or medium heat) for a half to three-quarters hour, stirring frequently.
Add brown sugar and spices and continue cooking (and stirring) until mixture attains a thick consistency.
Can be served alone, as a vegetable, or over beans or black-eyed peas.
Especially appropriate for New Year's Day.

title: come on over cake
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Crush crackers.
Mix nuts and baking powder.
Beat egg whites and sugar with vanilla.
Fold cracker mixture into egg whites.
Bake at 300° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool completely.
Mix Dream Whip according to directions.
Add softened cream cheese, powdered sugar and drained pineapple.
Spread on cake.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: leftover turkey casserole
directions: Saute onion and pepper until tender in margarine.
Mix all ingredients together and bake until bubbly.

title: divinity
directions: Cook to 242° on candy thermometer.

title: barbecued shrimp(from my brother's restaurant)
directions: Clean
shrimp,
leaving
tails
intact.
Place
a small piece of
cheese
between shrimp.
Wrap a small piece of bacon around shrimp
and secure with toothpick.
Place under broiler and cook for
about
2 or 3 minutes, turning once.
Baste with barbecue sauce and cook an additional minute.
Serve at once.

title: chocolate chip cookies*
directions: Beat together with electric mixer sugars and oil.
Add eggs (beaten) and beat again.
Add vanilla, salt, soda and flour.
Stir well.
Add chips and nuts.
Drop by teaspoons.
Bake at 350° for 9 minutes.

title: hot fudge pie
directions: Combine all ingredients together.
Pour in pie shells.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Serve hot with ice cream.

title: easy pie crust
directions: Mix all dry ingredients well and then add liquid.
Roll out on floured board.
Makes 2 pie crusts.
Bake at 450° for 8 to 10 minutes or until light golden.

title: cioccolato paradiso(orange-scented, chocolate-nut biscotti)
directions: Place nuts in a shallow pan and bake in a preheated 325° oven for 8 to 10 minutes or until golden brown.
Let cool.

title: 2 chocolate pies
directions: Mix dry ingredients first, then add egg yolks in with it. Just heat milk, stirring occasionally.
Add dry ingredients in with hot milk.
Stir until thick.
Take off and add 6 tablespoons of butter and 2 tablespoons vanilla.
Pour in cooked pie shell and let cool.

title: country deep-dish berry pie
directions: Prepare mixture of butter, flour, sugar and milk and set aside. Heat fruit almost to boiling. Pour warm berries or cherries into mixture, stirring. Pour in an ovenproof bowl or casserole and bake 25 to 30 minutes in a 375° oven or until crusty on top.

title: strawberry rhubarb pie
directions: Prepare pastry.
Mix the sugar, flour and orange peel.
Mix strawberries and rhubarb together; put half of the mixture into pastry lined pie plate.
Sprinkle with half of the sugar mixture. Repeat with remaining strawberry-rhubarb and sugar mixtures.
Dot with margarine.
Cover with top crust.
Cut slits into the top crust; seal and flute.
Sprinkle with sugar if desired.
Bake at 425° until crust is brown and juice begins to bubble through the slits in crust, 40 to 50 minutes.

title: roast opossum
directions: Roast opposum is good when baked with sassafras twigs when that spicy bush is close by.
Rub the meat with salt and pepper inside and out and stick lots of sassafras twigs into the outside. Roast, uncovered, at 300°, half hour for every pound of meat.

title: blueberry pie
directions: Bake 2
pie
shells
with 1/2 cup pecans in each shell. Cream the cream cheese with powdered sugar and almond flavoring.
Whip Dream Whip and fold into cheese mixture.
Pour into pie shell. Spread a can of blueberries on top.

title: mississippi mud
directions: Melt butter and cocoa; pour into bowl.
Add eggs, sugar, flour and salt.
Mix thoroughly; add nuts.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Spread over top of cake mixture marshmallows and melt in oven. Cool.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Melt butter in skillet.
Saute onion and mushrooms; remove. Brown steak which has been dredged in flour.
Add seasonings to browned meat, onion and mushrooms.
Add bouillon.
Simmer until tender, about an hour.
Add more liquid if needed.
Serve over noodles; top with sour cream.

title: cornbread cake
directions: Beat eggs.
Add other ingredients.
Put in greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Stir well together as given.
Put in bread pan, greased (9 x 5-inch loaf pan).
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: pecan pie
directions: Blend first 5 ingredients.
Stir in pecans.
Pour into 9-inch pie crust.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes or until firm.

title: bojangles biscuits
directions: Mix flour, baking powder and sugar.
Add Crisco and mix until crumbly. Add buttermilk and stir quickly until mix does not stick to side of bowl. Turn out on floured board and knead well.
Roll to 1/2-inch thickness. Cut with 3 1/2-inch cutter. Dip in melted butter or margarine.
Place on greased pan and bake for 10 to 15 minutes at 450°.

title: joe's spaghetti sauce
directions: In a large pot, on medium heat, heat oil and add onions, pepper, celery and garlic for a few minutes.
Add oregano, basil, parsley flakes, black pepper and salt.
Saute for 1 minute.
Add ground beef, crumbling to break up the meat.
Cook, stirring occasionally, until beef looses its pink color.
Add tomato paste and mix well.
Add tomato juice and mix.
Add water and mix until desired thickness is reached.
Add sugar and mix.
Salt to taste. When sauce starts bubbling, reduce heat and simmer for 1 to 2 hours.
Stir occasionally.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix the cream cheese and as much of the taco seasoning as you like and spread on a platter. (You may need to add a little milk to make it spreadable.)
Spread taco sauce over cheese mixture. Layer lettuce, tomatoes, cheese, olives, onions and anything else you like on tacos.
Use Doritos for dipping.

title: 3 bean hot dish
directions: Brown beef in large skillet; pour off drippings.
Add remaining ingredients and pour into baking dish.
Bake in 350° oven for 35 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: oven browned chicken
directions: Melt butter in a Pyrex baking dish in a preheated 400° oven. Meanwhile, shake chicken pieces in flour, salt, pepper and paprika mixture in a plastic bag.
Place chicken, skin side down, in melted butter.
Bake 30 minutes, then turn chicken and bake 15 more minutes.
Heat chicken soup (do not dilute) and mushrooms (add liquid, too) together on top of stove.
After chicken browns the additional 15 minutes, pour soup mixture over chicken.
Reduce oven heat to 350° and continue cooking 15 to 30 minutes more.

title: sheet carrot cake
directions: Combine sugar, oil, spices, eggs, vanilla, salt, carrots and flour and beat until mixed.
Stir in nuts.
Pour mixture into greased and floured pan, 12 x 7 1/2-inch (approximately).
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Test with toothpick to check whether cooked. (Moisture content varies according to carrots.)

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs; stir in sugar, oil, vanilla and grated zucchini. Combine dry ingredients.
Stir into zucchini mixture until well mixed.
Add nuts.
Pour into 2 well-greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch pans. Bake 55 minutes at 350°.
Cool thoroughly before slicing.

title: party snacks
directions: Preheat oven to 250°.
Heat oleo; stir in salt and sauce.
Add Chex and nuts.
Heat for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes. Spread on crumpled paper to cool.

title: banana cake
directions: Cream together the sugar, shortening and vanilla.
Blend together the eggs, buttermilk and mashed bananas.
Add to first mixture.
Mix together the flour, salt, soda, baking powder and chopped walnuts; add to first mixture.
(Save 1/3 of nuts to be included in icing of your choice.)
Pour mixture into two greased cake pans.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes.
Test with a toothpick.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Line 12 medium muffin cups with paper baking cups or grease bottoms of muffin cups.
Beat egg slightly in medium bowl; stir in remaining ingredients except blueberries just until moistened.
Fold blueberries into batter.
Divide batter evenly among muffin cups.
Bake 13 to 18 minutes or until golden brown.
Immediately remove from pan.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: poulet d'artichoke
directions: Drain artichoke hearts and arrange in 9 x 13-inch casserole. Spread chicken on top.
Combine soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry powder and pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Top bread cubes with butter and place on top and sprinkle with almonds. Bake at 350° until bubbling and slightly brown.
Can be prepared in advance.
Good served with a simple rice pilaf.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: In a shallow 2-quart baking dish, press ground beef evenly. Then spread peas over ground beef and next spread with cream of chicken soup.
Line top of casserole evenly with rows of Tater Tots.
Bake at 350° for approximately 30 to 45 minutes.

title: cauliflower and broccoli salad
directions: Mix mayonnaise, sour cream and vinegar.
Pour over mixture of vegetables.
Chill and serve.

title: orange charlotte
directions: Soak gelatin in 1/2 cup of cold water.
Dissolve in 1/3 cup of boiling water.
Add sugar, lemon juice and orange juice.
Chill. When quite thick, beat until frothy.
Fold in egg whites, beaten thick, and beaten whipped cream.
Refrigerate.

title: zucchini casserole pie
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large bowl; pour into 9-inch buttered pan (cake).
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: sour cream biscuits
directions: Mix ingredients in order. Spray muffin tins with Pam. Fill 3/4 full. Bake at 450° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: old state ham and noodle casserole
directions: Add salt and noodles to boiling water; boil rapidly, stirring constantly for 2 minutes.
Cover; remove from heat and let stand for 5 minutes.
Melt butter in a saucepan and add onion and green pepper.
Cook for 5 minutes.
Add ham and cook a few minutes longer.
Rinse noodles.
Heat soup and milk together until smooth. Combine ham mixture, soup, pimiento and pepper with noodles.
Pour into a greased 1-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with grated cheese. Bake in a moderate oven (375°) for 20 minutes.

title: chocolate pies
directions: Layer 1/2 cup nuts on each cooled pie crust.
Mix cream cheese, powdered sugar and 1-1/4 cups cool whip.
Layer over nuts.
Mix pudding and milk until thick, pour over cool whip mixture.
Top with remaining cool whip and nuts if desired.

title: easy cheesy lasagna
directions: Heat
oven to 375°.
In a 10-inch skillet, brown ground beef, onion
and garlic; drain.
Return beef mixture to skillet;	stir in	spaghetti
sauce
and water.
In a 9 x 13-inch baking pan, layer 1/3 of sauce mixture, 1/2 of slightly boiled lasagna noodles,
of
combined
Ricotta
cheese, 1/4 cup Parmesan cheese
and
parsley
and
1/2 of Mozzarella cheese. Repeat layers, ending with sauce mixture.	Cover tightly with foil;
bake for
hour.
Uncover;
sprinkle	with remaining Parmesan cheese.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: pineapple side dish
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Beat eggs into mixture, one at a time.
Stir in pineapple.
Fold in bread cubes.
Turn into a greased 1 1/2-quart glass dish.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour.

title: sausage balls
directions: Bring ingredients to room temperature.
Mix all together with hands.
Shape into balls the size of a marble.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.
Use deepish pan to hold melted fat.
Yields about 200.

title: zucchini pie(mock apple)
directions: Cook all ingredients until tender.
Thicken with 2 tablespoons cornstarch and water.
Cool and pour into an unbaked pie shell.

title: sauerkraut casserole
directions: Boil and drain noodles al dente.
Set aside.
Brown meat and drain.
Add celery, soup mix and sauerkraut and simmer for 1 hour. Mix soup and water and heat.
Add to meat mixture and add noodles.
Pour into greased casserole and bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: fun guy pasta
directions: In the time it takes to boil the water for the pasta, your dinner will be ready.
In 1 pan, bring enough water to boil to cook a 1 pound box of pasta.
While the temperature is coming to a boil, prepare the sauce.

title: pepper relish
directions: Put all peppers and onions through grinder/processor after seeding and cleaning.
Cover with boiling water for 10 minutes. Drain, then return to pan.
Add sugar, vinegar and salt.
Boil for 10 minutes.
Seal in jars while hot (pint jars).
Great on hamburgers and hot dogs.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken breasts.
Mix all other ingredients together, then add chicken.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until bubbly, then add chow mein noodles last 10 minutes.

title: cheese biscuits
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Cut in shortening.
Add cheese.
