Add milk and stir to form a soft dough.
Roll thin and cut into small biscuits.
Bake at 400° approximately 8 to 10 minutes.

title: reese's peanut butter cups
directions: Mix preceding ingredients well.
Make into balls.
Stick toothpick into each ball.

title: broiled shrimp in beer
directions: Thoroughly combine beer with all other items on the list in a large bowl.
Marinate shrimp in mixture overnight in refrigerator. Stir occasionally so shrimp are evenly seasoned.
Drain shrimp and broil 3 inches from flame for about 2 minutes on each side. Serve immediately.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: pecan chewies
directions: Mix margarine and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add flour, then nuts and vanilla.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Double for a big batch.

title: molded salad
directions: Make Jell-O and let cool.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix. Put in mold and refrigerate until set.

title: broad leaf weed killer
directions: Mix together and spray on browning broad leaf weeds in lawn. Biodegradable.

title: glazed sweet potato casserole
directions: Cook sweet potatoes in boiling water to cover for 20 to 25 minutes or until fork-tender.
Let cool to touch.
Peel and cut into 1/2-inch slices.
Arrange slices in a lightly greased 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Set aside.
Combine all ingredients, except potatoes and walnuts, in a saucepan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture begins to boil.
Boil for 1 minute, stirring constantly, until mixture begins to thicken and becomes bubbly.
Pour over sweet potatoes and sprinkle with walnuts.
Cover and refrigerate for 8 hours.
Remove dish from refrigerator.
Let stand for 30 minutes.
Uncover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook spaghetti according to package directions.
Drain and rinse with cold water and drain well again.
Transfer to large bowl.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Cut eggs in half.
Take out the yolks and mash with fork until fine.
Add all other ingredients except paprika and make a smooth mixture.
The yolks may need a little more moisture.
You can add a little more salad dressing.
Place the mixture back in egg whites and sprinkle with paprika.

title: chicken divan
directions: Cook broccoli and drain.
Place spears in a 9 x 13-inch pan with flowerets to outside.
Place cooked chicken in middle over spears.
Sprinkle cheese over chicken.
Combine remaining ingredients and mix well.
Pour over chicken and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: champagne punch
directions: Peel, slice, crush and place in large bowl pineapples.
Cover pineapples and juice with powdered sugar.
Let mixture stand, covered, for 1 hour.
Add lemon juice, curacao, maraschino, brandy and light rum.
Stir and let stand for 4 hours.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: While hen is cooking make sauce by frying onions, green pepper, celery and seasonings (to taste) in small amount of fat or oil until tender.
Add the tomatoes and mushrooms; cook down. Prepare spaghetti according to package instructions; drain.
Cool chicken, uncovered, in broth, then drain and cut up.

title: calico corn custard
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease a 10 x 6-inch baking dish (1 1/2-quart).
Dice peppers; place in a large bowl.
Place strainer over a 2 cup glass measuring cup.
Pour corn into strainer and drain well.
Add corn to red and green peppers in large bowl.
Add milk to corn liquid to measure 1 cup.
Beat eggs thoroughly; beat in sugar, nutmeg, salt, pepper, light cream and milk mixture.
Stir into corn-pepper mix.
Gently transfer corn custard into prepared baking dish.
Now, place this dish into a pan approximately 13 x 9 x 2-inch.
Pour boiling water around custard dish (about 1-inch depth).
Bake 40 minutes or until set. Will bake to perfection if water bath is used.

title: tomatoes, mac and cheese
directions: In a bowl, combine macaroni, tomatoes, onion, salt, pepper and 1 1/2 cups Cheddar cheese.
Pour into a greased 2-quart baking dish.
Dot with butter.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes. Sprinkle with remaining cheese; bake 15 minutes longer.
Yield:
4 servings.

title: pineapple filling
directions: Cook in top of double boiler until thick.

title: pudding delight
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix margarine and flour together to form a ball (for a thicker crust, use 2 cups flour and 2 sticks margarine).
Press into bottom of 13 x 9 inch pan.
Bake for 20 minutes and cool.
Using a mixer, blend together powdered sugar, cream cheese and one container of Cool Whip.
Pour into cooled crust.
Chill for 1 hour.
Mix instant pudding with milk and pour over cream cheese mixture.
Chill for 1 hour.
Top with one container of Cool Whip and sprinkle with crushed nuts.

title: corn pudding 1
directions: Mix all ingredients together, adding milk last.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: no-bake cookies
directions: In a large saucepan, combine sugar, milk, butter and cocoa. Bring to a boil. Boil for 1 minute MAX. Turn off heat. Pour remaining ingredients into saucepan and mix together. Spoon drop size cookies onto cookie sheet and refrigerate. Serve cold.

title: rice pudding
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients.
Add scalded milk and butter.
Add a dash each of cinnamon and nutmeg.
Pour into a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour or until mixture is firm.
Makes 6 servings.

title: vidalia onion pie
directions: Prepare crust by combining cracker crumbs with melted butter; press into bottom of pie pan.
Saute onion in butter until tender. Pour into crumb crust.
Beat eggs; add milk and salt.
Pour mixture over onion.
Sprinkle with cheese over the top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: winter bread chowder
directions: Prepare the loaves of bread by slicing off the top and scooping out the insides of the loaves.
Chop the onion and pepper; saute in the butter until tender.
Stir in the corn, chopped potato, cream and chicken broth; heat to a simmer.
Season with salt and pepper to taste.
Add the hot pepper to taste. Simmer for 15 minutes.
Place the hollowed loaves on large serving platters.
Pour the soup into the "bread bowls."
Garnish with parsley sprigs.
Save the bread tops for dipping.

title: hamburger medley
directions: Chop onions and cook until transparent.
Add hamburger and cook until browned, but not dry.
Place in a baking dish.
Add mixed vegetables and mushroom soup.
Top with Tater Tots and cheese.
Bake at 250° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: easy baked chicken(microwave)
directions: Remove giblets; wash chicken and pat dry.
Sprinkle inside of body cavity with salt and pepper.
Place onion and celery inside chicken.
Tie legs together and tie wings to body.
Place chicken, breast up, on a microwave roasting rack in a 12 x 7 x 2-inch microproof dish.
Spread with softened margarine; sprinkle with thyme.
Cook on High for 15 to 17 minutes, or until done (juices will run clear).
Cover with aluminum foil; let stand 5 minutes before serving.
Makes 4 servings.

title: chocolate drop cookies
directions: Bring first 4 ingredients to a boil and boil 1 minute.
Add oats, peanut butter and vanilla.
Drop on wax paper.

title: broccoli dip
directions: Saute onions and broccoli in butter until melted.
Add soups, cheese and seasonings.
Cook over low heat until cheese melts. Add mushrooms and nuts.
Remove from heat.
Serve hot.

title: hot fruit casserole
directions: Going to Bakersfield once a month to stock up on groceries. We would have 3 packed carts and the total bill would be $100.00.

title: popeye's sweet pea and olive oyl soup
directions: In a large pot, boil water.
Add split peas, onion, yams, celery and olive oil.
Reduce heat and simmer, covered, about 30 minutes.
Add spinach, garlic and basil; bring to a boil again. Reduce heat and simmer, covered, about 25 to 35 minutes or until split peas have dissolved to form a thick broth.
Stir occasionally.
Add frozen peas and soy sauce.
Add molasses and Spike or salt to taste.
Simmer 5 minutes until peas are tender and flavors are well blended.
Serves 8 to 10 bowls.

title: sausage balls
directions: Thoroughly mix ingredients and shape into 1-inch balls.
Bake on cookie sheet 10 to 12 minutes at 400°.
Good hot or cold.
May be frozen.

title: cloud biscuits
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Cut in shortening until crumbly. Combine egg and milk, then stir into flour mixture.
Stir just long enough to have dough follow fork around bowl.
Pour out onto floured board.
Knead a little to make it easy to work with.
Roll out to 3/4 inch.
Cut and place in ungreased pan.
Bake in a 450° oven for 10 to 14 minutes.

title: lemon meringue pie
directions: Mix egg yolks and lemon juice well. Pour in milk and stir until thick.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix bean dip, green chiles and taco seasoning.
Spread in bottom of dish.
Layer with remaining ingredients and top with grated cheese.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: fudge cake(doris' campout cake)
directions: Put sugar and flour into a large mixing bowl.
Then put water, shortening, cocoa and margarine into a saucepan and bring to a boil.
Pour over dry ingredients and mix.
Then add eggs, buttermilk, soda and vanilla.
Mix well.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Brown hamburger with onion; drain off fat; season with salt & pepper.
Cook macaroni with salted boiling water 10-12 minutes and drain.
Mix sauce with macaroni and hamburger.
Place in casserole, alternating layers with pepperoni and cheese, ending with cheese.
Bake uncovered at 350 degrees for 30 minutes.
Can be baked frozen if covered with foil and baked for 1 hour at 325 degrees.

title: cheddar squash bake
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Layer half the squash egg mixture and cheese.
Crumble bacon on top.
Mix butter and bread crumbs and bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: magic cookie bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In 13 x 9-inch pan, melt margarine in oven.
Sprinkle crumbs over margarine.
Mix and press.
Pour milk over crumbs.
Top evenly with chocolate morsels, nuts and coconut. Press firmly.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes or until lightly brown. Cool before cutting.
Store loosely covered at room temperature.

title: icy pineapple - fruit salad
directions: Drain apricots and pineapple, reserving 1 cup juice in a small saucepan; boil 2 minutes.
Set aside to cool.

title: cherry delight
directions: Cream together Cool Whip, sugar and cream cheese.
Spread into crust.
Spread pie filling over mixture.
Ready to serve. You may use any flavor pie filling.
Example: blueberry, pineapple, strawberry.

title: crab cakes
directions: Saute first 6 ingredients until tender in the butter.
Combine rest of ingredients and add to sauteed mixture.
Shape into cakes. Roll in flour.
Brown quickly and cook 5 minutes.

title: irish soda bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour an 8 x 9-inch round pan (traditionally a black cast-iron frying pan).
Mix 4 cups flour with next 5 ingredients.
Stir in raisins.
Add 2 cups buttermilk all at once and stir with a fork to form a soft dough.
Sprinkle 1/4 cup of remaining flour on board; add dough and knead for about 5 minutes.
Use as much of remaining flour as needed to keep dough from sticking.
Put dough into pan as round ball, cut 1/2-inch cross on top.
Cook until golden, about 45 to 60 minutes.
Cool on wire rack.
Best when not sliced for 8 hours.

title: cherry applesauce
directions: Dissolve jello in 1 cup boiling water.
Add applesauce, nutmeg and lemon juice, then refrigerate.

title: mostaccioli mosta
directions: In large skillet, cook ground beef and onion; drain excess fat.
Add tomatoes, tomato sauce, olives, Parmesan cheese, seasoned salt, oregano and crushed pepper.
Simmer 15 minutes. Prepare mostaccioli according to package.
Toss with melted butter.
Arrange in a 3-quart shallow baking dish.
Pour on meat sauce.
Top with Mozzarella cheese.
Place under broiler for 2 to 3 minutes until cheese melts.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: mexican salsa
directions: Simmer as thick as you like, then can put in pint jars.

title: chocolate zucchini coffeecake
directions: Beat together eggs, oil and vanilla.
Mix in zucchini and sugar.
Combine dry ingredients and stir into wet ingredients.
If desired, add nuts or raisins.
Pour into greased and floured Bundt or tube pan.
Bake in 350° oven until fork comes out clean, 45 to 60 minutes.
Cool on rack 20 minutes, then remove from pan. Frost, if desired.

title: brownies
directions: Melt oleo and cocoa together.
Cream eggs and sugar; add chocolate mixture.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: crispy potato wedges
directions: Combine olive oil and seasonings in a bowl.
Scrub unpeeled potatoes well.
Cut each potato in half lengthwise, then in thirds.
Coat each slice in the seasoned oil.
Spread in a single layer on a greased baking sheet.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes. Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake 15 minutes longer.

title: green bean salad
directions: Mix vinegar and salad oil.
Mix other ingredients.
Marinate with the oil mixture and let stand overnight.

title: apple and orange slaw(low-fat)
directions: Place first three ingredients in a bowl, tossing to combine. Combine Miracle Whip and brown sugar.
Add this mixture to cabbage mixture and coat well.
Cover and chill one hour.
Serves 4.
Per serving:
fat 0.25 g., calories 87, protein 1 g., cholesterol 1 mg., carbohydrate 22 g., sodium 225 mg.

title: taco casserole
directions: In a large skillet, brown beef; drain.
Add onions, garlic, tomato sauce, mushrooms and taco seasoning.
Simmer 15 minutes. Mash beans with their liquid and add to meat mixture.
Layer tortilla chips, meat mixture and cheese, ending with cheese in a 2-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.
Serve with taco sauce and sour cream.
Serves 6 to 8 people.

title: guacamole salad bowl
directions: Top with dressing and 1/2 cup shredded cheese.

title: chocolate covered spiders
directions: Melt chips in a saucepan over low heat.
Carefully stir in noodles and nuts.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto waxed paper.
Let cool.
Makes about 3 dozen.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Roll into balls and press with fork.
Bake in 300° oven for 10 minutes or until golden brown.

title: oven baked potatoes
directions: Put in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Melt butter in bottom of pan.
Mix sour cream, cream of chicken soup, shredded cheese and onion.
Put potatoes in dish and pour the mixture over potatoes.
Sprinkle with another cup cheese.
Add 1 cup crushed corn flakes on top. Sprinkle with melted oleo.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Boil cauliflower in salted water until slightly tender (should not be soft).
Peel eggs.
Cut cauliflower into small pieces. Mash eggs with fork.
Mix mayonnaise, mustard and Worcestershire sauce with eggs.
Mix all ingredients.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Refrigerate immediately.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: cheese rounds
directions: Cut bread into circles with a cookie cutter.
Dip circles into butter-oleo mixture, then flip into grated Parmesan cheese.
Put on cookie sheet; bake for 20 minutes at 300°.

title: pizzas
directions: Toast English muffins and let the children spoon on tomato sauce and grated cheese before adding round pepperoni and olive slices to make pizzas.
Bake at 350° until cheese is melted.

title: chocolate angel food cake
directions: Sift flour once, measure, add cocoa and sift flour again. Beat egg whites and salt on large platter with flat wire whisk. (We use electric mixer.)
When foamy, add cream of tartar and continue beating until eggs are stiff enough to hold up in peaks, but not dry.
Fold in sugar carefully, 2 tablespoons at a time, until all is used.
Fold in vanilla.
Then sift small amount of flour over mixture and fold in carefully; continue until all is used.
Pour batter into ungreased angel food cake pan and bake in a slow oven at least one hour.
Begin at 275°, increasing heat slightly to 325° after 30 minutes.

title: raisin nut cake(from 1975 edition)
directions: Mix water and raisins and boil a few minutes.
Take off stove; add baking soda.
Set aside to cool.
Mix eggs, sugar, vanilla and flour well.
Add raisin mixture to this and beat well.
Add oil and mix well.
Add walnuts.
Grease tube pan and bake for 1 hour at 375°.

title: mock mincemeat pie
directions: Combine all ingredients and boil for 5 minutes.
Pour into pie shell.
Cover with top crust.
Bake 30 minutes at 400°.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Add eggs, oil and milk to cake mix, then add berries and jello.
Save 1/2 cup berry juice.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
While hot, poke holes in cake with fork.
Add the powdered sugar to 1/2 cup berry juice and pour over cake.
Good with whipped cream.

title: l.k.p. potatoes
directions: Peel and quarter potatoes.
Roll in melted butter, then in crumbs.
Place in a baking dish.
Bake 1 hour at 400°.

title: party pumpkin dip
directions: Beat cream cheese in a mixing bowl until smooth.
Add pumpkin pie mix; beat well.
Add sugar, cinnamon and ginger, beating until smooth.
Serve with cookies.
Store in refrigerator.

title: apple pie
directions: Place flour, salt and sugar in food processor, pulse 3-4 times to combine.
Add butter pieces, tossing to coat with flour. Pulse 5 more times to cut butter into flour.
Repeat with crisco. Turn mixture out into large bowl.
Sprinkle with 5 tablespoons ice cold water.
Use a spatula to fold and press dough together to form a ball, add up to 1 tablespoon more water if necessary. Divide into 2 dough balls and roll out into circles.
Place one circle into glass pie plate.

title: raw vegetable dip
directions: Place the cream cheese in a bowl and allow it to stand for about 20 minutes at room temperature to soften.
Add the milk, sour cream, grated Parmesan cheese and salt to the softened cream cheese.
Mix with a spoon or an electric mixer on low speed. Place the cheese mixture in a small dish and serve it with raw vegetables.

title: cream cheese icing
directions: Cream Cool Whip and cream cheese in bowl; add small amounts of powdered sugar and mix well after each addition until all powdered sugar is mixed in.
Spread on cake and top with fruit of your choice (pineapple, blueberry, strawberries).

title: great potatoes
directions: Layer potatoes, onions and peppers in baking dish.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Add garlic salt and lots of butter.
Add just enough water to cover bottom of baking dish.
Cover with aluminum foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Enjoy.

title: upside-down apple pecan pie
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
In 9-inch pie pan, combine pecans, brown sugar and margarine; spread evenly over bottom of pan.
Place bottom crust over pecan mixture in pan.
In large bowl, combine apples, sugar, flour, cinnamon and nutmeg; mix lightly.
Spoon into pie crust-lined pan.
Top with second crust and flute; cut slits in pie crust.
Bake at 375°
for 40 to 50 minutes, or until crust is golden brown and apples are tender.
Cool pie upright in pan for 5 minutes.
Place serving plate over pie.
Carefully remove pan.
Some nuts may remain in pan; replace on pie with knife.
Cool at least 1 hour before serving.
Place pan on foil or cookie sheet during baking.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: pot roast
directions: Place roast in large roasting pan.
Clean and quarter potatoes, onions, carrots and celery.
Place around roast. Sprinkle with garlic powder and pepper.
Add bay leaf.
Mix bouillon cubes in two cups of water.
Pour over meat and vegetables.
Cover and bake at 300° for 2 hours.
Remove bay leaf before serving.
Serves 6.

title: meat loaf
directions: In a large bowl, pour milk over bread crumbs.
Mix in rest of ingredients and shape into loaf.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours. Serves 8.

title: poppy chicken
directions: Mix soup and sour cream.
Boil chicken breasts in water or bouillon.
After chicken is cooked, cut into pieces and mix with soup and sour cream.
Place in baking dish.
Crush Hi-Ho crackers and place on top.
Cut up butter and place on top.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: sweet potato casserole 3
directions: Cream oleo, eggs, sugar and vanilla.
Mash and stir potatoes. Pour in casserole.
Mix the last 5 ingredients and spread over potatoes.
Bake 45 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: carrot and ginger soup
directions: Melt butter in large pot over medium heat.
Add onion, ginger and garlic.
Saute for 15 to 20 minutes.
Add chicken stock, wine and carrots.
Heat until it boils.
Reduce the heat and cook, uncovered, until carrots are tender, about 45 minutes.
Place in a food processor or blender with a steel blade.
Puree and add lemon juice, curry, salt and pepper to taste.
Sprinkle with parsley and serve hot or chilled.

title: orange drop cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar. Add eggs, orange juice, peel, vanilla and milk; mix well. Add dry ingredients. Drop on greased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes. Frost, if desired.

title: oreo freakout
directions: Cover bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan with crushed Oreos (save a little to decorate top with).
Mix ice cream, milk and vanilla pudding together until creamy.
Spread over top of Oreos.

title: peanut butter bars
directions: Mix together first 11 ingredients.
Pour batter in a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° until done.
Put chocolate chips and marshmallows on top as it's taken out of the oven, then put it back in for a couple minutes to soften.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Mix flour, sugar and milk together.
Melt butter in baking dish.
Add peaches.
Pour flour, sugar and milk mixture over peaches.
Bake at 350° until golden brown, about 45 minutes.

title: party potato skins
directions: Scrub potatoes; rub skins with oil.
Prick each potato several times with a fork.
Bake at 400° for 30 to 40 minutes or until potatoes are done.
Allow potatoes to cool; cut top third off of each potato.
Discard tops.
Carefully scoop out pulp, leaving about 1/8-inch thick shell.
(Reserve potato pulp for other use.) Fry potato skins in hot 375° oil for 3 to 4 minutes or until brown.

title: supper nachos
directions: Brown beef and onion with salt and pepper; drain.
Spread refried beans in a shallow 11 x 17-inch pan.
Top evenly with meat, then green chilies with shredded cheese over chilies. Drizzle taco sauce over cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Remove from oven and cover with onions (tops too) and chopped ripe olives.
Heat 10 minutes more.
Mound center with avocados; surround with sour cream and sprinkle with parsley.
Quickly tuck nachos around edges.
Serves 8 to 12.

title: arroz con pollo(rice with chicken)
directions: Separate breasts, wings, upper joints, drumsticks and liver. Place remaining parts of chicken in saucepan with 3 cups water, a peeled onion, saffron and 1 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Boil 30 minutes, strain and measure to make 2 1/2 cups.
Meanwhile dust tender parts of chicken with flour and 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Cook in hot oil until well browned and tender.
Add a few slices of onion to oil to prevent spattering.
When tender, remove chicken to large casserole, keeping in oven or warm place.
Add ham, scallions, pimiento and parsley to the skillet.
Cook until scallions are tender.
Add bay leaf, rice, chicken broth (boiling hot) and salt to taste.
Bring again to the boil.
Cook over moderately high heat, uncovered, 10 minutes.
Stir well; transfer to casserole with chicken, arranging chicken over the top.
Cover; let stand 15 to 20 minutes, until all liquid is absorbed or place uncovered in 325° oven for 20 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings, enough for 4 persons.

title: chocolate chip cookies with cool whip
directions: Mix together cake mix, egg and Cool Whip topping.
Add mini chocolate morsels and mix.
Drop by teaspoon into powdered sugar to coat.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Remove from pan while hot.
It's delicious!

title: baked bean casserole
directions: Brown ground beef, onions and celery.
Drain well.
Pour into a large casserole dish and stir in remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: homemade pizza
directions: Place flour in bowl; make a well in flour.
Put yeast in 1/4 cup lukewarm water and dissolve; add to flour with 1 cup lukewarm water and salt.
Mix with fork; form into ball and knead.
Place dough into oiled bowl and cover with heavy towel.
Let rise for 1 hour; punch down and let rise another hour.
Oil pans and hands; spread dough onto pans.
Use Chef Boyardee pizza sauce or your favorite pizza sauce, cheese, pepperoni, sausage, etc.
Put in 400° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.
Yields 2 pizzas.

title: peanut butter fingers
directions: Remove crust from bread.
Slice bread into 4 slices (per piece of bread).
Bake in a 350° oven until lightly browned.
Meanwhile, melt 1/2 cup peanut butter and 1/8 cup oil in saucepan.
Dip toast in melted mix, then dip in cornflake crumbs to coat.
(Double the recipe for twice the treat!)

title: corned beef salad
directions: Mix jello, bouillon and hot water.
Add Miracle Whip and cream cheese.
Mix well and cool.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well and let set.
This also makes a good dip for vegetables or crackers.

title: caramel frosting
directions: Melt butter in 2-quart saucepan; stir in brown sugar and salt. Bring to rolling boil and boil rapidly for 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in milk, then return to rolling boil.
Cool 20 minutes or until lukewarm.
Add powdered sugar and beat until smooth and cool enough to spread.
If frosting stiffens too quickly while spreading, beat in several drops of milk.
Frosts 2 (8 or 9-inch) layers.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease and flour a tube pan or Bundt cake pan.
Sift dry ingredients all together.
Blend eggs, sugar, vanilla and oil.
Add sifted dry ingredients.
Batter will be very stiff.
Stir in apples and pecans.
Pour into cake pan.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours.
Let cool on rack before removing from pan.
Keep cake in tightly covered container and it will stay very moist. This cake freezes well.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients.
Pour in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt 1/2 stick margarine.
Mix in crushed corn flakes or crushed crackers. Put on top of potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: wiener wrap
directions: Cut wieners in thirds.
Wrap each piece with 1/2 slice of bacon, securing with toothpick.
Place wrapped wieners in a slow cooker or crock-pot.
Pour brown sugar over top of wieners.
Do not stir.
Cook on low heat at least 4 hours.
Can be cooked all day. Stir and serve warm.

title: roll out cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In a large bowl, cream the butter and sugar with an electric mixer. Beat in egg and vanilla.
Add baking powder and flour, one cup at a time, mixing after each addition. The dough will be very stiff. Blend last flour in by hand. Do not put into refrigerator. Divide dough into 2 balls.
On a floured surface, roll each ball in a circle approximately 12-inches in diameter and 1/8-inch thick. Use a cutter as a guide. Dough should be only slightly thinner than cutter.
Dip cutter in flour before each use.
Bake on ungreased sheet on top rack until lightly browned, 6 to 7 minutes.

title: frozen strawberry salad
directions: Cream together the cream cheese, sugar and whipped topping. Fold in remaining ingredients.
Place in a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan and freeze.
Cut into squares and serve.

title: french oven beef stew
directions: Combine all ingredients except potatoes.
Place in a 2 1/2-quart casserole.
Cover and cook for 2 1/2 hours at 275°.
Add the potatoes.
Cook, covered, for 1 hour more.
Stir occasionally. Serve.

title: quick, easy quiche
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix everything in one bowl; stir.
Pour into buttered glass pie dish.
Bake for 40 to 45 minutes, or until edges are golden brown.

title: regal carrot cake
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine sugar, flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt, nutmeg and cinnamon; make a well in center. Combine eggs, oil and vanilla and pour into well.
Beat with a large wooden spoon until batter is smooth.
Fold in grated carrots and chopped pecans.
Turn into well greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake in a 325° oven for 1 hour and 20 minutes or until top springs back when lightly pressed with fingertip.
Cool cake in baking pan on wire rack for 1 hour.
Remove cake from the pan and frost with Orange Cream Cheese Frosting.
Yields 12 generous servings or 24 small servings.

title: chicken-pepper salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a bowl and cover with dressing.

title: mashed potato bake
directions: Combine mashed potatoes and sour cream. Place 1/2 in casserole dish; layer 1 cup cheese on potatoes and 1/2 of French fried onions on cheese. Spread rest of potatoes on top of onions, then spread rest of cheese on potatoes, then onions. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: italian meatballs
directions: Soak bread crumbs with milk.
Beat in egg.
Add ground beef and mix together.
Add seasonings.
Roll into 2-inch or larger meat balls.

title: piggy's in a blanket
directions: Cook hot dogs and cut in half.
Flatten dough, add half a hot dog with 1/2 piece of cheese.
Roll up and put in 350° till brown.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onions together and drain.
Melt 1 stick butter and pour in 1/2 box Stove Top dressing mix.
Mix well. Line casserole dish with this mixture.

title: green tomato pickles
directions: Core tomatoes and slice 1/4-inch thick.
Measure 16 cups. Combine tomatoes, onions and green peppers.
Set aside.

title: christa's tomato chutney
directions: Put tomatoes in bowl and sprinkle them with salt.
Cover bowl for 24 hours, put in fridge.
Mix the curry, flour and mustard in a bowl, add enough vinegar to make a paste.
Drain tomatoes, rinse off excess salt and place them in a preserving pan.
Simmer gently until just boiling, then cook for 5 minutes.
Dissolve the sugar with the remaining vinegar and add to the pan.
Simmer about 30 minutes.
Add the flour paste and cook for 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Pour in hot sterilized jars and seal with vinegar proof tops.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Butter 9 x 13-inch glass baking dish.
Cover bottom of dish with layer of graham crackers.
Mix pudding with milk until almost set and then add the Cool Whip.
Pour 1/2 pudding mixture over bottom layer of graham crackers.
Add a 2nd layer of crackers over pudding mixture.
Then pour remaining pudding mixture over 2nd layer of crackers.
Add a 3rd layer of crackers.
Then put Fudge Frosting over crackers and refrigerate overnight.

title: southern pecan pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Beat eggs and gradually mix in sugar, butter and salt. Whip the cream gently 1 minute and stir into egg mixture with corn syrup.
Add vanilla and 1 1/4 cups pecans. Spoon into pie shell and bake 40 to 50 minutes.

title: hawaiian cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and the fruit.
Add the flour, baking powder, soda, salt and vanilla.
Drop on a cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.
Can be frozen and will not harden or freeze solid.
Can be eaten right from the freezer.

title: microwave divinity
directions: In small bowl combine frosting mix, corn syrup, vanilla and boiling water.
Beat on high until stiff peaks form, about 5 minutes.
Transfer to large bowl.
On low speed blend confectioners sugar gradually.
Stir in chopped nuts.
Drop mixture by teaspoon onto waxed paper.
When outside of candy feels firm, turn over and allow to dry 12 hours or overnight.
Store in airtight container.

title: cauliflower squash soup
directions: Saute onions, celery and carrots for 3 to 8 minutes in oil. Cover.
Add rolled oats after 5 minutes, adding water (small amount).
Add cauliflower, then squash, Herbamore, bay leaf and water to cover.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; simmer for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Add water to 1 cup level.
When done, remove bay leaves and process in a food processor.
Makes a thick, tasty soup perfect for cold weather cooking.

title: taco dip
directions: Spread beans into bottom of a dish, (13x9 if you use 2 cans of beans).
Mix together sour cream and HVR Fiesta Dip mix, spread on top of beans already in pan. Grate cheese and layer on top of sour cream mixture.
Top with tomatoes, scallion onions, red pepper, and black olives.
TA DA DONE!!!
Enjoy!!!

title: brunswick stew
directions: Combine all ingredients in a saucepan.
Cook over low heat for 1 hour.
Stir occasionally to prevent scorching.
Yield:
4 to 6 servings.

title: catch of the day
directions: Heat oven or grill to 350°.
Place piece of fish on foil (make into "boat").
Sprinkle with dill, salt and pepper and olive oil.
Place selection of
fresh or frozen veggies on top of fish. Close up foil and place on cookie sheet (if using oven) and cook 20-30 minutes depending on thickness of fish.
Serve with rice.

title: banana pudding(1930)
directions: Mix sugar, milk, water and eggs together.
Save three egg whites for topping.
Bring to boil, then add cornstarch, mixed with a little extra water.
Cook until thickened.
Add vanilla.

title: cajun chicken creole
directions: Brown chicken in hot oil in a Dutch oven or deep skillet. Remove chicken from skillet and add onion, pepper and garlic. Saute until onion is translucent; stir in soy sauce, tomatoes and cayenne pepper.
Bring to a boil.
Arrange chicken pieces in sauce, cover and simmer 50 minutes.
Turn pieces over once; stir in okra. Cover and simmer 10 minutes, or until okra is tender.
Serve over hot rice.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: oreo cookie cake
directions: Crush cookies.
Reserve 1/2 cup for garnishing.
Add melted margarine to crushed cookies and press mixture in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix cream cheese and powdered sugar, beating well. Fold in 1/2 cup of Cool Whip.
Spread on top of cookie crust. Chill for 30 minutes.
Mix pudding with milk and spread on top of cream cheese mixture.
Chill for 1 hour.
Top with remaining Cool Whip and sprinkle with
1/2 cup
reserved
crushed cookies.

title: mincemeat
directions: Cook slowly on low heat for 2 hours, stirring often.
If you need more liquid, add grape juice.

title: rice casserole
directions: Brown meat well.
Mix all ingredients together and place in casserole.
Bake 1 1/2 hours in moderate oven.

title: french onion soup
directions: Melt butter. Add onion. Blend flour. Stir in broth, water and wine, then bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer 15 minutes. Put in individual bowls. Put slice of Mozzarella cheese on top. Put in 350° oven for 10 minutes to melt cheese.

title: hot milk cake
directions: Beat eggs until fluffy.
Add sugar and mix.
Add flour sifted with baking powder and salt.
Mix well and add hot milk (with large tablespoon butter melted in milk).
Add vanilla.
Bake in 8 or 9-inch pan at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: honey crunch
directions: Preheat oven to 250°.
Place popcorn and nuts in a 4-inch deep baking pan.
Keep warm in oven.
Lightly butter cookie sheet. Melt butter over low heat.
Blend in honey until well mixed. Remove popcorn mix from oven.
Set oven to 350°.
Pour butter-honey mixture over popcorn-nut mixture and mix well.

title: frozen fruit cups
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour into muffin cups.
Freeze until firm.
Store in plastic bag.
Makes about 1 1/2 dozen.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, creaming well.
Sift together flour and salt; add to creamed mixture, alternating with sour cream.
Add vanilla.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours or until done.

title: chocolate chip muffins
directions: Mix all the ingredients together.
Put in lined muffin pans. Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 400°.

title: tartar sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients and store in refrigerator.

title: sweet maple potato casserole
directions: Boil sweet potatoes until sot.
Drain and mash potatoes using a potato masher.
Add milk and salt.
Whip this all together and place into a well greased casserole dish.
Over the potatoes, pour maple syrup heated with butter.
Bake until top is carmalized at 400 degrees.

title: hot german potato salad
directions: Slice potatoes into 3/4-inch chunks.
Boil until fork tender; set aside.
Fry bacon until crisp; drain and crumble into bite-size pieces.
Keep 1/4 of bacon fat.
Heat 1/4 cup bacon fat and add onion.
Cook until translucent, about 2 minutes.
Blend flour, vinegar, sugar, salt, celery salt and dash of pepper in bowl.
Add mixture into skillet with 1 cup water; stir until mixture is boiling and has started to thicken.
Fold in bacon and potatoes and heat thoroughly.
Put into bowl and serve warm.

title: poppy seed loaf
directions: Blend all ingredients in a large bowl; beat at medium speed for 2 minutes.
Pour into 2 well-greased 8 x 4-inch loaf pans. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes before removing from pan.

title: escarole soup
directions: Boil chicken broth.
Clean escarole.
Lay out to dry.
Break escarole into boiling, salted water.
Cook until tender. Make tiny meatballs and put into broth.
Drain escarole and put into broth.
Combine eggs, cheese, salt, pepper and garlic powder.
Pour into soup mixture.
Cook about 15 minutes longer.

title: frozen strawberry salad
directions: Beat cream cheese at medium speed with an electric mixer until creamy.
Gradually add sugar, beating until smooth.
Fold in whipped topping and remaining ingredients; spoon into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Cover with aluminum foil.
Freeze until firm. Yield: 12 servings.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: Mix all together in 2 1/2-quart baking dish.
Pour boiling water over all so it melts cheese and oleo some.
Bake at 350° until liquid is absorbed and top nicely brown.
I have precooked broccoli a little if it appears to look tough.

title: death by chocolate cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Chop 8 squares of chocolate; set aside.
Microwave remaining 8 squares in large bowl on High.
Stir until melted and smooth.
Stir in sugar, butter, eggs and vanilla. Stir in flour and baking powder.
Stir in reserved chopped chocolate and nuts.
Drop by 1/4 cupfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake for 12 to 13 minutes or until cookies are puffed and feel set to the touch.
Cool on cookie sheet 1 minute.
Transfer to wire rack.
Makes 1 1/2 dozen.
YUM!

title: italian rice salad
directions: Put all ingredients except romaine lettuce in large bowl; toss to coat.
Let stand 1 hour or more to blend flavors.
Serve on lettuce, if desired.
Makes 4 main-dish servings.
tags: warm cooked long grain white rice

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix
all
ingredients
together
and
store in airtight container.	To make a cup of hot chocolate, mix 1/3 cup of mix with 2/3 cup boiling water.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Spray 4 small pans.
Cream sugar, oil and eggs.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into pans and bake at 350° for approx. 1 hour.

title: carob milk
directions: Put into blender.
Mix until smooth.
Serve cold or hot.

title: christmas brunch strata(perfect - it is prepared the day before!)
directions: Place 6 slices of bread in bottom of a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish. Reserve 1/2 cup cheese, then sprinkle remainder over the bread.
Add a layer of broccoli, then a layer of ham.
Layer remaining bread on top. Combine remaining ingredients; pour over bread and all. Top with sesame seed. Cover and refrigerate 6 hours or overnight.

title: gert's peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream peanut butter and shortening; add sugars.
Continue mixing until light and fluffy.
Add egg.
Add flour.
Drop by spoonfuls to cookie sheet.
Press drops in an intersection pattern with sugared fork.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill.

title: jerry's viva la chicken
directions: Mix well the ingredients in a huge, greased casserole.
Cover and let sit in the refrigerator overnight.
Next day, bake at 325° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Sprinkle with a little more cheese and serve.

title: nonfat sugar-free pistachio salad
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving juice.
In a deep bowl, add juice, pudding mix and nonfat yogurt.
With a wire whisk or rotary beater, mix 1 to 2 minutes or until well blended.
Stir in crushed pineapple and Mandarin oranges.
Pour at once into serving dish. If desired, garnish with maraschino cherries.
Best if refrigerated several hours before serving.
Makes 10 (1/2 cup) servings.

title: karo pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs.
Add rest of ingredients and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Reduce oven to 325° and bake until done, approximately 25 minutes.

title: recycled pickles
directions: Slice pickles, but not thin. Put in a jar along with onions. Bring sugar, vinegar and water to a boil. Add horseradish to jar. Pour vinegar mixture over all. Cool and keep in refrigerator. Crispy and delicious.

title: marinated fruit combo
directions: In a bowl combine melon, drained pineapple, and strawberries. Combine grapefruit juice, orange marmalade and orange liqueur. Pour mixture over fruits.
Stir gently.
Chill 1 to 2 hours. Makes 6 cups.

title: special mashed potato salad
directions: Peel, slice and boil potatoes.
Mash and add raw eggs while hot.
Add remaining ingredients and top with sliced eggs.
Add onion, relish, mustard and pepper according to taste.
Serve warm or cold.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: lentil-barley soup
directions: In a 4-quart Dutch oven, cook onion, celery and hot margarine or butter until tender.
Add water, undrained tomatoes, lentils, barley, bouillon cubes, oregano and pepper.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer for 45 minutes.
Add carrots and simmer for 15 minutes more or just until carrots are tender.

title: beef gourmet
directions: Roll the meat in flour, salt and pepper.
Add tomato soup and onion soup.
Cook 3 1/2 hours in 250° oven.
Add sherry wine and sauteed mushrooms.
Cook another 1/2 hour.

title: apricot bars
directions: In large bowl, cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs; mix well. In separate bowl, combine flour and baking powder.
Gradually add to butter mixture.
Add coconut, walnuts and vanilla.
Mix thoroughly.
Press 2/3 of dough into greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Spread preserves on dough.
Crumble remaining dough on preserves.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: moroccan carrot salad
directions: Scrub carrots well and cut tops and tips off. Steam carrots in a steamer until they can be cut easily with a spoon. Remove from heat and take 2 forks to break carrots crosswise into bite size pieces. Add the next 9 ingredients and toss until thoroughly mixed. Cover and refrigerate overnight or at least 3 to 4 hours before serving.
Makes about 3 to 4 cups of salad which, if served by itself as a salad or meal along with the Moroccan bread, serves 3 to 4 people.

title: chicken parmigiana
directions: Place each piece of chicken between 2 sheets of wax paper. Flatten each chicken piece to 1/4-inch thickness.
Combine bread crumbs, salt and pepper.
Dip chicken in egg and coat with bread crumbs.
Place chicken on a baking sheet; cover and chill 10 minutes.
Saute chicken in vegetable oil over medium-low heat 5 minutes on each side or until golden brown.
